Peel the onion, shallot, and garlic, and chop them.
Place the heads and shells in a pot with the oil and half the butter.
Start heating over high heat while stirring constantly.
Add the chopped onion, shallot, and star anise. Let brown for a few minutes, then thin down the tomato paste.
Pour in the white wine with 75 ounces of water and season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 25 minutes. Leave to infuse for 15 minutes, then strain the mixture through a sieve.
Pour the juice into a saucepan. Add the cream and reheat without boiling.
Adjust the seasoning as needed.
Cook crawfish tails with the remaining butter in a non-stick pan until the butter is lightly brown.
Brown the bacon in a little olive oil until crispy and cut into pieces (place them on a paper towel to remove excess fat).
Wash the apple by brushing it with hot water, wipe dry and cut into thin sticks keeping the skin.
Preheat soup bowls and divide the prawns in, pour the cream on top, sprinkle with sliced apple and bacon, add pepper and serve immediately.

title: chocolate chip and pomegranate muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Mix and sift flours, salt, and baking soda in a bowl, set aside.
In another bowl, whisk the eggs. Add the brown sugar and stir until obtaining a homogeneous mixture.
Pour in the vanilla extract, then add the Greek yogurt and the oil.
Mash the bananas, and mix with lemon juice and zest.
Mix the flour mixture with the mashed bananas and milk. Stir well until getting a creamy mixture.
Gently stir in the chocolate chips and pomegranate berries.
Pour spoonfuls of batter into cupcake pans without filling completely.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Let cool before unmolding.

title: chopped succotash salad
directions: On large shallow serving platter, arrange lettuce. Evenly top with remaining ingredients, arranging in rows. Just before serving, toss with Wish-Bone Light(R) Ranch Dressing

title: chicken wing salad
directions: Cook the wings according to the instructions on the package.
In a salad bowl, add the lettuce, tomato, pickles, and carrot. Place the chicken on top and pour dressing over the chicken.

title: pesto bread rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in some warm water with 1/2 teaspoon of sugar, allow it to proof for a few minutes. Stir once in a while until the foam on the top has formed.

Place the two types of flour in the mixer bowl with the salt, turn the mixer on quickly to combine, then add the yeast, the oil, and the pesto diluted with some hot water. Turn on the mixer again and knead the dough until it is of a soft consistency. Add some warm water if necessary.
Gather the dough into a ball, make a criss cross incision on top, brush lightly with oil, cover it in plastic wrap and place it in a warm area to rise, at least 2 hours.
Punch down the dough and knead it again for a few minutes, shape it into loaves 6 to 8 centimeters in diameter.
Cut the loaves into many small pieces.
Shape each piece into a round roll, brush with some oil, and add some pine nuts on top.
Place the rolls on baking sheets lined with wax paper, leaving some space between each.
Allow the rolls to rise again in a warm area.
Preheat the oven to 170-180C and bake the rolls for at least 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove the rolls from the oven and cool.

title: plum jam (from moimenta da beira) with honey and cinnamon - thermomix recipe
directions: Thoroughly wash and pit the plums.
Combine all ingredients in the Thermomix bowl, set to the stir setting for 10 seconds, speed 3.
Remove the measuring cup from the lid and put the basket in to prevent splashing and quickly boil the liquid.
Set for 20 minutes, temperature 100, speed 2.
Then program for 15 minutes, temperature Varoma, speed 2.
Then set 4 or 5 seconds on speed 4.
Immediately pour the jam in sterilized jars and seal.
Turn the jars upside down and let cool in this position.

title: strawberry tart
directions: Use an 8- or 9-inch tart pan with removeable bottom.
Firmly pat gramham cracker pie shell into tart pan.

Set aside. Blend milk with instant pudding mix in deep bowl using a whisk or an electric mixer. Continue mixing at low speed for 1 minute or until pudding is dissolved. Add grated orange rind. Let stand for 5 minutes and pour into pie shell. Let stand for 15 minutes or until set. Arrange strawberries or other berries decoratively over pudding shortly before This recipe is suitable for occasional use. Use unsalted margarine in pie shell.

title: hummus and mutabel
directions: Hummus preparation: put all the ingredients, except the oil and paprika which are used as garnish at the end, in a food processor and grind. If it is too thick, add a little liquid from the chickpeas or water.
Season with garlic and cumin according to taste. Transfer to a bowl. At serving time, sprinkle with paprika and add extra virgin olive oil to taste.
Mutabel preparation: repeat the process above.
Put all ingredients in the food processor, including a stream of extra virgin olive oil. Grind well and adjust the amount of garlic and cumin according to taste.
Serving suggestion: pita bread, slices of toast, carrot sticks, mid lettuce leaves.

title: hummus
directions: In a food processor, add the chickpeas, cumin, lemon zest, garlic cloves, tahini, water, and salt. Blend until smooth. If it seems too thick, add water 1 tablespoon at time until reaching desired consistency.
Serve with paprika sprinkled on top and a drizzle of olive oil.

title: hummus
directions: Drain and rinse the chickpeas. In a blender, mix them finely with the lemon juice, garlic cloves, olive oil, tahini, salt and a pinch of sumac. If the dough is a little thick, add a little water to make it less thick. If you want a smoother consistency, strain to remove the skin from chickpeas. Keep in a cool place for at least one hour before serving. Serve with pita bread or Lebanese bread.

title: chicken cassrole with hash brown topping
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°F. Boil the potatoes for 20 minutes or until tender. Drain and when cool enough to handle, remove skins.

Heat the oil in a frying pan and brown the chicken on all sides. Add the onions and mushrooms and cook for another 3 mins. Add the paprika, oregano, tomatoes, cream and sherry and bring to a gentle simmer. Season to taste and transfer to a shallow ovenproof dish.

Coarsely grate the potatoes over the chicken mixture. Sprinkle with the almonds and dot with the butter. Season to taste and bake for 35-45 minutes, or until potatoes are golden. Garnish with parsley.

title: beef with battered broccoli
directions: Divide the broccoli into large florets and boil in water until slightly tender. Set aside.

Place the beef into a covered skillet and cook in its own juices for approximately 10 minutes. Add the chicken broth, cumin, garlic powder, and tomato puree. Stir together and let simmer for 5 minutes. Add the cooked rice, mix, and set aside.
Separate the eggs, beat the whites with a pinch of salt until they form peaks. Add the yolks and mix together.
Dip each piece of broccoli into the egg mixture and fry in oil. Remove from pan and place on a paper towel. Blot to remove excess oil.
Add the broccoli to the beef and let cook together for 3 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Add tomato sauce, vinegar, honey, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, and onion powder in a bowl and mix well.
Add the chicken and peppers and mix well, coating the chicken pieces completely.
Place the pot on the stove and cook on medium-low heat for 25 minutes. Cook until the chicken becomes softened.
Remove the chicken from the pot. Allow it to cool off, and then shred it.
Place the shredded chicken into the pot and cook it until the sauce begins to boil. Serve warm in tacos, as sandwiches, or by itself.

title: brocciu cannelloni
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit.
In a saucepan, cook over low heat the tomato sauce with the star anise and the sugar (to correct the acidity of the tomato). Season with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, in a medium-sized bowl, mash with a fork the bush with beaten eggs, lemon zest, salt and pepper.
If you use dried cannelloni, cook it according to the instructions on the package. Use a spoon to stuff the cannelloni with the Brocciu mixture.

If you're using fresh lasagna, form a roll of stuffing on a sheet of lasagna at about 3cm from the edge. Roll the sheet to form a tube. Do the same with all the lasagna sheets. If you have excess stuffing, it's not lost ...
In a baking dish, place a bit of tomato sauce on the bottom, making sure to remove the star anise.
Arrange the cannelloni in a row in the dish, then cover it with sauce. If you have leftover stuffing, spread it on top.
Bake for about 20 minutes.
Serve with an arugula salad seasoned with olive oil and lemon juice.

title: blue crab cream soup
directions: Chop the vegetables and cook over low heat.
Add the blue crab and the brandy, slightly crush the crab.
Once the alcohol in the brandy has evaporated, add the rice and enough water to cover.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add the tomato sauce and salt to taste.

To blend: if you own a sturdy hand blender, blend in the pot, otherwise the blades could break. The other option is to remove the crab shells and leave only the crabmeat in the soup. The claws may be added whole as they become soft enough to be blended.
Blend thoroughly, strain several times to remove any traces of shells, and serve.

title: irish crab cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 220 degrees Celsius.
Drain the crab and discard all the liquid.
In a medium bowl, combine crab, mayonnaise, cream, mustard, egg, lemon zest, dill, and green onion.
Season with salt and pepper. Mix well.
Form the crab cakes and arrange them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Or use a cupcake tin to make them more uniform.
Bake for about 20 minutes until well browned.
Let them cool before unmolding.
Prepare the dressing. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, chopped dill, sour cream, lemon juice and lemon zest, and capers. Mix well.
To serve, slice the cucumber, leaving the skin, and place one crab cake on top of each cucumber slice. Top each cake with a dollop of dressing.
Let cool down until serving.

title: babamisu
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Separate the eggs.
In a medium bowl, with an electric mixer, beat the yolks with sugar until the mixture is pale.
Add the milk and oil. Mix well.
Add flour and baking powder .
Beat the egg whites with salt and gently add to the dough.
Grease the cupcake tins and fill with the batter up to 2/3.
Bake the babas for 20 minutes.
While tha cakes bake, make the syrup. In a small saucepan combine coffee and sugar. Cook over low heat to dissolve the sugar without boiling the coffee. Add the marsala.
Unmold the cakes while hot and quickly brush them with hot syrup.
Cover and let soak them for at least 8 hours.
Separate the remaining 2 eggs.
Mix the mascarpone with vanilla, sugar and egg yolks.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold them gently to the mascarpone mixture.
Fill the center of the cakes just before serving, sprinkle with a bit of cocoa.

title: vanilla cupcakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Line 12 muffin forms with paper cups.
In a bowl, mix the butter with the sugar until creamy. Add the eggs, one at a time, alternating with a little bit of flour, and whisk well.
Add the vanilla extract and the remaining flour, mixing well.
Add the milk, and mix until the batter obtains a consistency that can be dropped into the muffin cups.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until they are golden brown.
Remove from oven, and let cool before decorating.
Whisk the egg white until stiff.
Add the sugar and cheese, mix well, and spread on the cooled cupcakes.

title: nantais cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Cream the softened butter with the sugar. Stir in the ground almonds and vanilla powder. Then add the eggs 1 at a time. Gently mix in the flour and 2 centiliters of the rum.
Pour the batter into a buttered cake pan and bake for about 40 minutes..
Once the cake comes out of the oven, unmold it and sprinkle with 2 centiliters of rum.
After the cake has cooled, combine the remaining 2 centiliters of rum with the confectioner's sugar and water. Frost the cake then let it rest in the fridge.

title: vanilla and chocolate loaf cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 170C.
Add the sugar to the butter with a pinch of salt, and beat with an electric mixer until light and foamy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add a pinch of salt, the grated lemon peel, and the vanilla extract to the flour.
Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture, use the hook attachment or a wooden spoon.
Divide the batter into two parts, one weighing 250 grams and the other weighing 230 grams.
Add the sifted cocoa to the dough weighing 230 grams.
Butter a loaf pan well with some softened butter, line the pan with almond slices.
Place a strip of wax paper down the center of the pan and add half of the vanilla batter on one side of the paper and half of the cocoa on the other side.
Next add the other half of the vanilla batter on the cocoa batter and the remaining cocoa batter on top of the vanilla batter. Carefully remove the wax paper.
Bake for approximately 1 hour.
Remove the cake from the oven and cool on a wire rack.

title: cajun buffalo chicken dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Mix cream cheese, ranch dressing, hot sauce and 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese in medium bowl until well blended. Stir in chicken.
Spoon into glass pie plate sprayed with no stick cooking spray. Top with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until heated through. Drizzle with an additional 1 tablespoon of hot sauce and sprinkle with chopped green onions, if desired.

title: thai noodles
directions: Plunge the vermicelli into a pot of boiling water.
Turn off the heat and let the vermicelli soften in the water for 4/5 minutes.
Drain and refresh under cold water.
Cook the chicken breast in a skillet.
Dice the fresh pineapple.
In a bowl, mix the sugar with the nuoc nam and the lime juice. Add the chopped garlic clove.
Cut the cayenne pepper, and remove the seeds as well as the white pith (this will dampen the taste a bit, if a hot spicy taste is preferred, do not remove the seeds and pith).
Cut the pepper into thin strips and put it in the bowl with the sauce.
Be careful to wash hands well and not rub eyes.
Pluck the leaves off the mint and coriander and chop.
Mix all ingredients and serve.
To prepare this salad, do not immediately mix the sauce with the noodles, do it at the last moment, otherwise the noodles will absorb all the sauce.
This recipe can also be prepared with shrimp.

title: chicken wonton cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Place wonton wrappers on a flat surface and lightly coat with oil. Line 2 - 12-cup mini muffin trays with wonton wrappers. Bake for 10-15 mins, or until crispy. Let cool.

Fill a large deep frying pan halfway with water. Cut cilantro roots and 1 inch of stalk from bunch of cilantro and add to water. Add lemon slices and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and add chicken. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 mins. Remove from heat and let chicken cool in liquid.

Shred chicken then mix with onion, pepper, chopped cilantro and mint. Whisk lemon juice with chili sauce and fish sauce then toss with chicken mixture. Distribute between wonton cups. Garnish with chilies and cilantro. Serve.

title: onion-glaze baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend Lipton(R) Recipe Secrets(R) Onion Soup Mix, water, sugar, wine, Spread and parsley in small bowl; set aside.

Arrange ham in roasting pan. Score (lightly cut) fat with knife in diamond pattern; top with soup mixture. Arrange shallots around ham. Bake, stirring shallots and basting ham occasionally, 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and vegetables fideua
directions: Fry the chicken in a large pan with 1 tablespoon of oil. Once golden brown, remove and set aside.
Stir-fry the noodles for a couple of minutes. Remove and set aside.
Add another tablespoon of oil on medium heat. Add the chive, garlic, carrot, bell pepper, leek, and sprouts. Cook for 5 minutes and add the mushrooms. Cook for another 5 minutes.
Place the chicken and the noodles into the pan.
Add the chicken broth and bring to a simmer. Remove from the heat and let it rest for 10 minutes.

title: mediterranean salad
directions: Cook the potato in boiling salted water. After 4 minutes, add the carrots and cook until both are soft. Drain and place in chilled water.
Once the potato and carrot are cool, mix with the chickpeas, panela cheese, bell peppers, and parsley.
Separately, mix the vinegar with the olive oil and garlic. Season with salt and black pepper. Dress the salad with this mixture and serve.

title: ranch chicken pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F.
In a small bowl, combine the dressing, cream cheese and tomato paste.
Spread the mixture evenly on the pizza crust leaving a 1/2-inch border around the crust.
Top with the remaining ingredients and bake until cheese is golden and bubbly.

title: italian-style  chicken tostadas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Slice pitas horizontally to make 4 rounds. Arrange pitas on baking sheet cut-side up. Bake 6 minutes or until lightly toasted; set aside.

Meanwhile, in 10-inch nonstick skillet, melt Promise(R) Buttery Spread over medium-high heat and cook onion, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until starting to brown. Add roasted peppers and chicken and heat through. Stir in Parmesan cheese, basil and salt.
Evenly top pitas with chicken mixture, then sprinkle evenly with mozzarella cheese. Broil until cheese is just melted. To serve, cut into quarters.

title: beef and mixed bean enchiladas
directions: Cook the green beans in a pan of lightly salted boiling water until just tender. Drain well and rinse under cold water. Heat the oil in a frying pan and cook the onion, garlic, and chili over a medium heat for 6-7 mins until softened. Add the ground beef and cook until browned all over. Stir in the salsa and simmer for 10 mins.

Add the green beans, sweetcorn and kidney beans to the pan and simmer gently for another 10-15 mins, stirring occasionally and adding a little water if the mixture starts to stick to the base of the pan. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Preheat the oven to 400°F.

Fill the tortillas with some of the beef and bean mixture and roll up. Layer in a greased baking dish and spoon the rest of the beef and bean mixture around and over the top of the filled tortillas. Scatter cheese over the top and bake for 15 mins until crisp and golden at the edges.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, eggs and 1 2/3 cups water and knead until smooth. Let rest for about 30 mins.

Meanwhile, heat 1 tbsp lard in a pan and brown meat. Season and set aside. For tomato sauce, bring 2/3 chopped tomatoes, 1 red chili, 2 onions and 1 clove garlic to a boil then simmer for about 10 mins. Season with cumin.

Knead dough again and roll out into 8 thin tortillas using about 4 tbsp dough for each. Working in batches, heat remaining lard in a small frying pan and cook tortillas for about 2 mins per side. Set aside.

Preheat oven to 400°F. Distribute tomato sauce and ground beef between tortillas, roll up and transfer to an ovenproof dish. Mix cheddar and cottage cheese then spread over tortillas and sprinkle with 2/3 of the olives. Bake for about 15 mins.
For the guacamole, puree avocado, green chili, remaining onion, lime juice, 1 tbsp of olive oil and 1/2 the cilantro and season to taste. Serve garnished with lime wedges.

For chili dip, heat remaining olive oil in a pan and saute remaining garlic and chili. Add remaining tomato, bring to a boil then simmer for about 5 mins. Add 2/3 of the spring onions. Serve garnished with extra spring onions.
Serve enchiladas sprinkled with cilantro and dips on the side.

title: spicy potatoes
directions: Fry the potatoes in oil.
Heat oil in a separate skillet and add the tomatoes. Whisk the cornstarch into the water until mixed and add to the tomatoes along with the paprika. Cook for a few moments and add a pinch of salt.
Place the potatoes on a platter and cover with sauce to serve.

title: pork spring rolls
directions: Place the rice noodles in a heatproof bowl and cover with boiling water. Let sit for 4-5 mins then drain well. Meanwhile, heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan and brown the ground pork over high heat. Add the spring onions, garlic and vegetables and saute, stirring, for 4-5 mins. Add the noodles, prawns, soy sauce, sherry, cilantro and sugar and season.

Take one spring roll wrapper and place 2 tbsp of the filling in the center. Brush around the filling with beaten egg then fold in the sides and roll into a spring roll. Heat the remaining oil in a large frying pan and fry the spring rolls over a medium heat for 3-4 mins, turning frequently, until crisp and golden. Serve with sweet and sour and chili dipping sauces.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 celsius.
Beat the butter with the lemon rind until creamy and add the powdered sugar. Continue to beat, adding the lemon juice and the vanilla.
Add the flour, mixing gently to incorporate into batter.
Shape the dough into balls, pressing each one with the palm of the hand to form discs.
Bake at 180 C until the edges are slightly golden in color.
Remove from oven and place on rack to cool.

title: gourmet yogurt with stewed sweet and salty roquefort
directions: Cut the figs and apples into small cubes.
In a pan, heat the butter, then add the red onion. Cook for about 4 to 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring regularly.
Add the apple and figs, then the hazelnuts and ham. Cook for about 3 to 4 minutes, stirring regularly.
Add the tablespoon of balsamic vinegar. Stir, and lower heat to let it stew.
Let cool before pouring over the yogurt.

title: nut-flavored cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.

Beat the butter and condensed milk until creamy. Add the egg yolks and continue to beat. Add the sifted flour and baking powder, chopped nuts, and egg whites and mix gently. Line a baking dish with parchment paper and butter generously. Spread the batter in the baking dish and place it in the oven for 30 minutes.
To make the frosting, beat the butter in a mixer until lightened. Beat in the the cocoa powder. Slowly whisk in the condensed milk until the frosting is smooth and creamy.
Coat the cake with the frosting. Sprinkle the sides with chopped nuts. Finally, decorate with whole walnuts.

title: sweet potato brownies
directions: Line a small, square baking pan with parchment paper. Set aside.
Peel the potatoes, cut into cubes and cook for about 20 minutes until tender.
Place the potatoes and dates in a food processor and puree until smooth.
In a bowl, place the remaining ingredients and add the puree. Stir well.
Place the batter into the prepared pan. Smooth the surface with a spatula.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350°F for about 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out almost clean.
Allow to cool for about 10 minutes before unmolding.
Cut into squares and sprinkle with cocoa powder if desired.

title: cocoa brigadeiros
directions: In a saucepan, mix the condensed milk with cocoa.
Add the milk and butter.
Simmer on medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring constantly. The batter reduces and thickens slightly.
Pour into a greased baking dish and let cool.
Finally, grease your hands with oil, and use a tablespoon to scoop out small amounts.
Shape small balls with your hands and roll them in chocolate sprinkles.
Repeat the operation.
Store in the refrigerator. .

title: chorizo cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit.
In a bowl, mix the flour with the salt, turmeric, baking powder, and Espelette pepper.
In another bowl, whisk the eggs with the butter.
Make a well in the flour and pour in the egg and butter mixture. Mix well and then add the chorizo. Divide the dough into small molds or cupcake trays and bake for about 20 minutes.
In a bowl, mash the cream cheese with a fork.
Finely chop the chives and mix with the cream cheese. Add pepper to taste. Fill a pastry bag and decorate the top of the cupcakes once they have cooled.

title: ham, brie, and pine nut pasta
directions: Boil the pasta according to package directions.
In a saucepan, whisk together the Brie, cream, and pine nuts until melted. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve the drained pasta with the cheesy sauce on top. Garnish with pieces of ham and pine nuts.

title: chorizo cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Remove the casing from the chorizo and crumble.
In a bowl, beat the margarine and eggs until pale.
Add the milk and crumbled chorizo meat, stir to combine.
Add the flour and baking soda, mix well.
Pour the dough into greased and floured muffin pans.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal crusted fish and olive salad sandwiches
directions: Mix the olives, tomato, lemon juice and rind, olive oil, and pepper together. Set aside 20 minutes.
Put the flour on a plate and add salt and pepper. Whisk the egg and milk together in a bowl. Place the tortilla chips onto another plate.
Coat the fish with the flour, shaking off the excess. Next, dip them in egg. Finally, coat them with the ground tortilla chips.
Heat the olive oil in a skillet and fry the fish, flipping to cook on both sides.
Place a fillet of fish in each bread roll and spoon the olive salad on top. Serve with a slice of lemon.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Marinate the pork in a drizzle of soy sauce and sherry vinegar for 10 minutes.
Coarsely chop the vegetables and cook until golden brown.
Place all the ingredients over low heat for 5 minutes, add the cornstarch at the end and set aside. Add more sugar for a sweeter flavor or more salt and vinegar for a less sweet flavor.

Once the pork has marinated for 10 minutes, cover the pieces with flour and fry in very hot oil. Remove and use paper towels to absorb the excess oil. Place the pork in the sauce along with the vegetables to cook for 10 minutes to mix all the flavors in.

title: coca cola gums
directions: Put all the ingredients in a saucepan, and stir to dissolve. Bring to boil, stirring constantly for about 5 minutes.
Divide the mixture in small wet silicone molds (for ice or chocolates).
Refrigerate to solidify.

title: orange creamsicle cake with orange creamsicle frosting
directions: Blend cake mix, instant pudding mix, eggs, water and oil and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour batter into prepared pans and bake, following the chart located on the back of the Duncan Hines cake mix box. Cake is done when a toothpick insterted in center comes out clean.

While the cake is still hot, mix together orange Jell-O and one cup boiling water. When Jell-O is dissolved, poke holes in the cake with a straw or fork and pour hot Jell-O over cake. Let cake cool completely before frosting.
Frosting:

In a large bowl or mixer, beat instant vanilla pudding with 1 cup milk. Stir in the extracts. When the mixture becomes very thick, fold in the thawed Cool Whip. Spread frosting between layers and on top of cake. Refrigerate for at least two hours before serving.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Place the egg whites in a bowl with a pinch of salt, and beat until firm.
Gradually, add the powdered sugar until the egg whites form stiff peaks.
Gently mix in spoonfuls of coconut, beating upwards.
Line a baking tray with parchment paper, or other non-stick material.
Put spoonfuls of dough on the tray.
Bake for about 20 minutes, or until golden.
Remove from oven, and let cool.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cook ground beef in large skillet on medium-high heat 5 minutes or until cooked through, stirring frequently. Drain, if needed.
Stir in remaining ingredients and spices. Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: famous queso dip
directions: Combine ingredients in microwaveable bowl.
Microwave on HIGH 5 min. or until VELVEETA is completely melted and mixture is well blended, stirring after 3 min.

title: matcha latte cream
directions: Bring 34 centiliters of milk to a boil in a saucepan.
Turn off the heat as soon as it boils.
In a bowl, mix cornstarch with remaining 16 centiliters of milk.
In another bowl, whisk the egg yolks with the sugar until the mixture becomes pale.
Add tea and cold milk and mix well.
Mix in the cornstarch and milk combination.
Pour the mixture in a saucepan and whisk on medium heat for 3 minutes until the mixture begins to thicken.
Pour the mixture into glasses and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve very cold.

title: b'stilla (or pastilla)
directions: Add meat and stock to a pan; boil; then reduce heat to medium-low and cook, covered, 40 minutes.
Transfer meat to a cutting board; let cool, then shred, discarding skin and bones.
Simmer cooking liquid over medium heat until sauce is reduced to 1 cup, 30 minutes; then let cool and whisk in eggs.
Cook garlic and onion until golden in oil; then add the spices; cook 1-2 minutes and remove the sauce from the heat.
Stir in ground almonds, shredded meat, sauce, the herbs, salt, and pepper; set filling aside.
Heat oven to 400°F and grease a 9" springform pan with butter.
Fit 2 buttered sheets of phyllo into pan, with corners hanging over the edges.
Spread 1/3 filling over phyllo and repeat the layering process twice more, then fold corners of phyllo over filling.
Top with remaining 2 sheets of buttered phyllo; tuck corners around sides of pan; then bake until golden and filling is cooked through, 30 minutes.
Let cool, then unmold; dust with confectioners' sugar and cinnamon.
Serve and enjoy.

title: citrus, almond and matcha tea cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 180C.
Wash the citrus fruits, remove the skin and the pith completely, eliminate any seeds and blend them in a blender.
Beat the eggs with the raw sugar.
Add the almond flour, the citrus pulp, the grated peel of 1 lemon and 1 citron, the flour, potato starch, tea, oil, and milk.
Last, add the sifted baking powder.
Stir well to combine.
Butter and flour a cake pan or line it with wax paper and pour the batter inside.
Bake for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove the cake from the oven and cool completely.

title: small clementine houses
directions: In a bowl, beat softened butter with sugar to a pale cream.
Add the egg and mix until well blended.
Add clementine zest, then juice, stir.
Stir in flour, knead with your hands to make a big ball of dough.
Wrap with plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, create cardboard houses (Use your imagination, or download one from the Internet). Cut out the pieces.
Preheat oven to 350F.
Roll out the dough.
Using the cut-out cardboard patterns, cut out the shapes of each part of the houses using a knife.
Arrange them on a silicon mat or parchment paper lined baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
For the frosting, add the powdered sugar to a bowl, and gradually add in the beaten egg white (a thick consistency is a must).
Fill a piping bag with icing.
Group the shapes of the houses and assemble them with royal icing using the pastry bag.
Decorate however you want.
Sprinkle with edible glitter and powdered sugar.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Place chicken, mirin, soy sauce, and ginger in a resealable bag. Mix well and make sure the chicken pieces are fully coated. Place the bag in the refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours. Flip the bag on every couple of hours.
Add the oil to a skillet on medium heat. Add the chicken and saute for up to 15 minutes, until golden brown on all sides.
Serve on a plate with a salad or rice.

title: baked bbq chicken dip
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F.

In microwave-safe bowl, combine cream cheese, 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce, Ranch dressing (and onions, optional). Microwave on high for 1 minute. Stir to combine. Gently fold in 1/2 cup cheddar cheese and drained chicken meat.

In a baking dish (at least 4 cups), layer the cream cheese mixture, smoothing the top. Pour the remaining 3 tablespoons barbecue sauce, smoothing the top and sprinkle the remaining cheddar cheese on top. Bake for 15 minutes, until bubbly. Serve with crackers, tortilla chips or raw veggie sticks.

title: murcian-style salad
directions: Set the tomatoes on a baking tray and place under the broiler until the skins char. Let cool and peel.
Remove the hard part at the top of the tomatoes and chop. Transfer to a salad bowl with the scallion. Salt to taste.
Drizzle the vegetables with olive oil and vinegar to taste.
Add the egg, tuna, and black olives on top.

title: creamy chocolate passion fruit entremet
directions: Preheat oven to 170 degrees Celsius.
In a medium-sized bowl, mix the almond meal, the flour, and 85 grams of granulated sugar.
Whisk the 4 egg whites. When they start to foam, add 45 grams of granulated sugar. Keep whisking until the whites form peaks.
Pour the dry ingredients in the egg whites and stir gently with a spatula.
Spread the mixture on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes.
Allow to cool.
To prepare the gianduja pudding, start by placing 2.6 grams of gelatin in cold water.
Mix the 2 egg yolks with 10 grams of granulated sugar.
Heat the milk.
Pour the hot milk into the egg / sugar mixture. Stir.
Pour everything back in the saucepan. Keep over low heat until the mixture thickens.
Add the (wrung-out) gelatin, 20 grams of dark chocolate, and 160 grams of gianduja chocolate. Stir.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour so that it solidifies.
To prepare the passion fruit pudding, start by placing 4 grams of gelatin in a bowl of cold water.
Bring the the passion fruit puree to a boil in a saucepan.
Mix 6 eggs with 135 grams of granulated sugar.
Add to the fruit puree and cook until boiling, while whisking continually.
Add the (wrung-out) gelatin, and then 190 grams of diced, softened butter.
Mix the preparation and smooth it using a blender before letting it cool completely.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
To prepare the icing, start by placing 2 grams of gelatin in a bowl with cold water to soften it.
Boil the water with 90 grams of granulated sugar, cocoa powder, and heavy cream. Lower the heat and let it cook for 15 minutes.
Add (wrung-out) gelatin. Stir well so that the gelatin melts.
Let it cool down before frosting the cake.

When you are ready to assemble the entremet, cut a square or a circle of the cake base (depending on the shape you prefer). Spread cold chocolate pudding over the cake. Spread cold passion fruit pudding over the chocolate pudding. Store for 4 hours (or overnight) in the freezer. Top with the icing.
Place the cake on your serving dish, store in a cool place, so it defrosts during 3 hours minimum.

title: green pepper, grilled tomato, chicken, and cheddar mini pizzas
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Place the tomato slices on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet. drizzle oil on both sides of the tomato slices, along with a pinch of salt and black pepper.
Broil for for 5 minutes on each side. Watch closely so that the slices do not burn.
Add a tablespoon of oil to a skillet on medium heat. Add the shallot, bell pepper, and garlic and saute for 5 minutes.
Add the vegetables to a food process with the sugar. Puree until smooth and set aside. Set aside.
Roll out 40 gram dough balls to make thin mini pizzas
Cover the dough with the bell pepper sauce. Place the tomato sliced on top.
Top with chicken and cheese.
Raise the oven temperature to 200 C and bake for 15 minutes until the crust is golden. Serve hot.

title: grilled chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken breast cutlets in shallow baking dish. Season each side with salt and pepper.
On a hot grill, cook one side for 5 minutes, then flip to the other side.
Spread generous amount of sauce on each chicken cutlet.
Add shredded Mozzarella on top of the sauce and close grill lid. Cook for another 7-8 minutes until cheese is melted and chicken is cooked through.
While chicken is cooking, prepare zucchini noodles or "zoodles". Use spiralizer and shred zucchini.
In medium saucepan, heat 1/2 cup sauce on medium high heat for 5 minutes. Pour hot sauce directly over zucchini noodles.
Remove chicken from grill and serve hot with zucchini noodles. Enjoy!

title: jerk chicken
directions: Add everything but the chicken into a food processor and blend together.
Puncture the thighs in multiple places and pour the sauce over them massaging to make sure it gets completely absorbed. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Grease a baking dish and lay the chicken skin-side down in the dish. Pour a little of the marinade over each chicken piece.
Bake for 45 minutes flipping the chicken halfway through cooking.

title: pepper steaks with tomato gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F. Lightly spray an 8 x 8 inch shallow ovenproof dish with cooking oil.

For the tomato gratin, spray a large frying pan with cooking oil and heat on medium. Cook onion and garlic 3 mins, stirring, until onion is soft. Layer zucchini and tomatoes in prepared dish and season. Sprinkle onion mixture and cheese on top. Bake 15 mins. Broil 1-2 mins, until top is golden.
Meanwhile, coat one side of steaks with pepper. Heat a griddle pan on high and cook 4 mins each side, or as desired. Serve with tomato gratin and salad.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180C.
Beat the egg whites to stiff peaks.
Beat the sugar with the butter until foamy and light.
Add the flour, baking powder, egg yolk, water, and grated lemon peel and juice.
Last, fold in the stiff egg whites carefully.
Fill the mini-loaf cookie molds to 3/4.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes (until lightly golden).

title: slow cooker barbecued rabbit or squirrel
directions: Salt rabbit or squirrel pieces and place in slow cooker.
Dissolve instant chicken broth in small bowl with 6 ounces of water.
Add other ingredients to broth and mix well.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours.

title: razzberry mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in water, then heat over low heat until dissolved. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Puree frozen strawberries in food processor or blender. Add sugar and mix well.
Transfer to a mixing bowl and stir in cooled gelatin. Place in refrigerator until mixture starts to set.
Whip 1-1/2 cups of the cream.
Remove strawberry mixture from refrigerator, add BACARDI(R) RAZZTM and mix well. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 2-quart souffle dish or serving bowl. Refrigerate until firm.
Whip the remaining 1-cup of cream. Decorate the mousse with whipped cream, fresh raspberries and/or fresh strawberries.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Heat the butter in a saucepan, add the potato, onion and broccoli stalk. Saute for 2-3 mins. Pour in the milk and stock then simmer for 20-25 mins. Meanwhile, blanch two-thirds of the broccoli in a pan of salted, boiling water for 2 mins then drain and refresh under cold water.

Mix the cream cheese, garlic and lemon juice together until smooth then season. Sprinkle the pepper on the plate. Use two teaspoons to drop spoonfuls of the cream cheese into the pepper and lightly coat. Set aside.

Mix the parsley and nutmeg into the soup and season. Blend the soup with a blender until smooth. Toast the sunflower seeds in a pan without oil for 2-3 mins then remove from the pan. Divide the soup between 4 bowl then sprinkle with seeds, broccoli florets and parsley sprigs.

title: spinach & walnut - topped chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except chicken. On baking sheet, arrange chicken, then evenly top with mayonnaise mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Grease a large cake tin (I used a round one without a hole) with butter and sprinkle with flour. Set it aside.
Begin by combining the sugar and the eggs and beating them well.
Add the flour, baking powder, oil, and chocolate powder, and beat until it is mixed well.
Finally, add the hot water and beat again.
Pour the batter in the cake pan and bake about 45 to 50 minutes. Check the progress with a toothpick and, once finished, remove, take it out of the pan, and let it cool.
While the cake is baking, mix the frosting. I always do it by taste, so you can combine the ingredients as you prefer.
Combine all the frosting ingredients in a small saucepan and bring it to a very low heat, stirring continuously.
Once you have a smooth cream, it is ready.
When the cake and the frosting are only slightly warm, coverthe cake completely.

title: pork and beans
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet on medium heat.
Saute the chopped onion and garlic for two minutes.
Add the chorizo and cook it until it becomes slightly brown.
Remove the contents onto a plate lined with paper towel. Drain excess grease.
Add ingredients back to skillet and cook for another 5 minutes.
Add the beans and mash everything together.
Add a small amount of bean water, along with the cheese. Serve warm.

title: steak & arugula salad
directions: Pour 1/2 cup Wish-Bone(R) Robusto Italian Dressing over steak in large, shallow nonaluminum baking dish or plastic bag; turn to coat. Cover, or close bag, and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 3 to 24 hours.
Remove steak from marinade, discarding marinade. Grill or broil steak, turning once and brushing with 1/4 cup Dressing, until steak is desired doneness.
Toss arugula and onion with remaining 1/4 cup Dressing in large bowl. Top with thinly sliced steak and drizzle, if desired, with additional Dressing. Serve with bread.

title: tortellini with mustard-cream sauce
directions: In a medium pot, cook tortellini according to packaged directions. Drain and then toss with 1 tablespoon olive oil to prevent pasta from sticking. Set aside.
While tortellini is cooking, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a medium skillet. Add asparagus and saute until tender, about 5-6 minutes. Remove from skillet and cover to keep warm. Set aside.
In same skillet, combine chicken broth, heavy cream, mustard, salt and pepper. Whisk together.
Simmer for about 10-12 minutes, or until thickened.
Remove from heat and pour over tortellini. Add in asparagus and toss to coat. Serve immediately.

title: stir-fry ham and bok choy eggrolls with a sweet & sour pineapple-hot mustard dipping sauce
directions: 1. Place all ingredients into stainless steel mixing bowl.
2. Mix well by hand and refrigerate. Marinade up to one hour.
1. Place 1 fl oz peanut oil into large wok or frying pan.
2. Heat oil until just under the smoking point.
3. Pour excess marinade off of ham. Toss ham into wok and stir-fry until ham is heated throughout.
4. Remove ham with tongs from the wok and reduce all liquid in wok until thick and bubbly.
5. Pour over ham.
6. Clean wok. Add 1 fl oz peanut oil and heat oil until just under the smoking point.
7. Toss vegetables in wok and cook until slightly crisp.
8. Add ham back to vegetables and toss well to combine.
9. Remove all from wok.
10. Place on sheet pan to cool.

title: oven-baked sonoran dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Set a wire roasting rack in a sheet pan. Wrap a strip of bacon around the length of each frank and arrange them with the ends of the bacon strips down on the roasting rack.
Bake franks on middle rack of preheated oven until bacon is fully cooked and crisp at the edges, 23-28 minutes. Meanwhile, prepare toppings.
Juice lime into a small bowl. Add mayonnaise, sour cream, hot sauce, and garlic powder and whisk until blended. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Dice tomato. Finely dice onion. De-seed the jalapeno, if using, and cut it crosswise into thin strips. Mince cilantro, if using.
When franks are done, remove sheet pan from oven. Set each frank in a bun and set them back on the rack in the sheet pan. Rinse and drain pinto beans, then spoon 2 Tbsp. onto each frank.
Bake franks on middle rack of oven until beans are warm, 2-3 minutes.
Check that franks are done. Remove from oven or add time as needed.
Transfer franks to a serving platter. Top with tomato, onion, jalapeno, and cilantro. Drizzle with lime mayonnaise, and serve.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Pre-heat the oven to 170C.
Place the 2 tbsp. sugar in a pudding mold and gently heat until it caramelizes. Ensure it covers the entire base of the mold. leave to cool.
Crush the amaretti biscuits in the food processor. Alternatively, place in a plastic and smash with a rolling pin.
Beat the eggs with the remaining sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the biscuit crumbs and cocoa powder and mix well with a wooden spoon, taking care not to take in too much air.
Slowly add the milk, stirring continuously.
Transfer the mixture to the pudding mold.
Heat some water in a large baking tray, about 3/4 full.
Cook for 45 minutes-1 hour. Do not allow the water to boil.
Leave to cool completely and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before removing from the mold.

title: alfajores (dulce de leche sandwich cookies)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the flours, baking powder and salt.
With an electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until pale for about 2-3 minutes.
Add the orange zest and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture. Mix until fully incorporated.
Add iced water (60 to 70 ml) and mix for about 1-2 minutes to obtain a flexible dough.
Divide the dough in half and form two discs.
Wrap them in plastic and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat the oven to 175 degrees Celsius.
Bring dough to room temperature.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface to a thickness of 0.5 cm.
Bake on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper for about 6-8 minutes until lightly browned.
Let them cool on a wire rack.
Arrange the cookies, spread half with "dulce de Leche". Form the "sandwiches".
Melt the chocolate, add cream and stir for about 2-3 minutes over very low heat.
Wait a few seconds before dipping the cookies to coat them. Tap gently to remove the excess.
Allow to harden at room temperature.

title: cookies with caramel candy bars
directions: Cut 15 caramel candy bars into small squares.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees Fahrenheit.
In a bowl, mix brown sugar and softened butter until the mixture is pale.
Add the egg, mix until batter is fluffy.
Mix the flour and baking powder together in a different bowl.
Beat 1/3 of the flour mix into the butter and sugar mixture. Gradually add remaining flour mixture, beating continuously.
Add vanilla extract.
Add the small caramel candy bar squares, gently fold to evenly distribute throughout the dough.
Form balls of dough and space them on a silicon mat or parchment paper lined pan.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes at 300 degrees Fahrenheit.
Eat warm or cold.

title: rice noodle salad with chicken
directions: Cook the rice noodles in boiling water as instructed on the package. Drain and let cool.
Roughly chop the chicken breasts and cook them in a frying pan with a 1/2 tablespoon of vegetable oil. Let them to cool evenly and put them aside.

Mix in a small bowl the sugar, fish sauce, and lime juice. Mix well until the sugar is fully dissolved. Chop the chili finely and remove the seeds (this is the spiciest part). Add it to the sauce with the kaffir lime leaf, minced shallot, stem of spring onion and grated carrots.
Mix the noodles with the chicken and the sauce. When it's ready to serve, add the peanuts and the chopped herbs.

title: vietnamese chicken drumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375 F. Spray rimmed baking sheet with vegetable cooking oil spray.

Arrange drumsticks in single layer in shallow glass dish. In small bowl, whisk together caramel sauce, soy sauce, lime juice, chili garlic sauce, ginger and pepper. Pour mixture over chicken, turning to coat. Let chicken marinate for about 20 minutes.
Arrange chicken on prepared baking sheet. Place in oven and cook, turning occasionally, about 50 minutes or until done.

While chicken is baking, prepare apple slaw by stirring together in medium serving bowl lime juice, rice wine vinegar, brown sugar, soy sauce and vegetable oil. Whisk to combine. Add coleslaw, apple, cucumber, cilantro and mint; toss gently to coat. Refrigerate until serving with drumsticks.

title: jewel biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper. Place the marzipan, butter, sugar, vanilla extract, and salt in a mixing bowl and beat with an electric hand mixer until smooth and creamy. Stir in the eggs, followed by the flour, ground almonds and almond extract.

Divide the mixture into two portions. Transfer one half into a piping bag with a star-shaped tip. Pipe figure-8 shapes onto one baking sheet and repeat using the remaining dough. Bake 15-18 mins until golden and cooked through. Cool on wire racks.
Heat the apricot jam and pass through a fine sieve. Discard the solids. Repeat the process with the raspberry jam. Spoon 1/2 tsp of each jam onto the cooled biscuits and allow to set. Serve.

title: roasted chicken wings with mustard and beer
directions: Preheat the oven to 200C or 180C with a fan.
Wash and cut the tips of the wings and leave to drain.
In a small bowl, combine olive oil, mustard and honey and stir to mix.
Rub in the drained wings with salt and pepper and arrange in a shallow baking pan.
Spoon the mustard mixture over the wings, as trying to spread evenly.
Add carefully the beer and water without washing the marinade from the wings (if using a deeper baking pan, the liquid amount could probably be reduced :)

Add the peppercorns and bake on the lowest grill into the preheated to 200C or 180C with a fan oven for about 40-45 minutes or until the sauce has almost evaporated, as after the 30th minute, if necessary, cover the wings with an aluminum foil to prevent burning.
Remove from the oven and cover with an aluminum foil for about 3-4 minutes.
Serve the wings warm, sprinkled with the saucse from baking.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pie Crust Preparation:
Put the flour, margarine, water, salt, sugar, and poppy seed in a food processor, and pulse until the dough forms a ball.

On a floured surface, roll out the dough, and cut out a piece of dough the size of the pie pan. Line the pie pan with butter or parchment paper, add the dough, and use your fingers to press the dough to the pan. Prick the bottom with a fork.
Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Filling Preparation:
Break the pumpkin into small pieces, and steam in a double boiler. When the pumpkin is soft, drain the water, and put the pumpkin in a food processor or electric mixer.
Add the sugar, and mix until the pumpkin is completely blended.
Add the butter, and mix some more.
Whisk the eggs, and add to the pumpkin mixture.
Sift the flour.
Turn on the processor, and gradually add the flour, and then the baking powder.
Pour the filling in the pie crust, and bake for about 45 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the enter of the pie comes out clean.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a bowl until mixed well into a dough.
Form into balls of approximately 1 tablespoon of dough each, and place onto a baking sheet covered with aluminum foil approximately 3 centimeters apart.
Bake at 180 Celsius for 15 minutes.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: In the mixer, mix the chicken (cut into small pieces), cream, and egg white.
Salt and pepper.
Roll out about a 25 centimeter plastic wrap on your work surface. Place about 2-3 tablespoons of stuffing next to each other to form a blob about 3 centimeters in diameter.
Roll it (tightly) in plastic wrap, and tie the ends with freezer strings.
Heat some water in a large saucepan.
Place the sausages in a bamboo basket, and steam cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
The sausages are cooked when they have a more compact texture.
Allow to cool slightly before unwrapping the sausages.
Cut into 1 centimeter thick slices.
Place flour, bread crumbs, and eggs (whisked, with olive oil and salt) into separate bowls. Roll each nugget in flour, then in egg, and then in breadcrumbs.
Heat some oil in a large frying pan, and fry the nuggets in small batches until they are golden brown.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in a nonstick frying pan and brown ground meat. Season then add onion and garlic and cook for 2-3 mins. Add tomato paste and cook for 2-3 min. Add tomato juice and chopped tomatoes and simmer for 2 mins. Add beans and corn, season and simmer for 3-4 mins. Serve with a dollop of creme fraiche (or sour cream, if using). Garnish with sliced chili pepper and rosemary.

title: chicken with pumpkin
directions: Cut the chicken into pieces
Peel and chop the shallot and garlic.
Dice the pumpkin.
In a large frying pan, heat a little oil, add the pumpkin and brown.
Remove the pumpkin from the pan and set aside.
In the same pan, brown the chicken with a little water.
Add garlic and shallot.
Mix constantly, making sure the garlic does not burn.
Add the wine and reduce the sauce on high heat for a few moments.
Lower heat and season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 40 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
After 40 minutes, add the pumpkin and tarragon.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Mix gently and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: roast pork grenadine
directions: Rub nutmeg & thyme on top and sides of roast. Place in shallow pan and roast for 45-60 minutes (20 minutes per pound) in a 350 degree F. oven, until internal temperature on a thermometer reads 145 degrees F. Remove roast from oven; let rest about 10 minutes. Baste roast with 1/2 cup grenadine syrup several times during roasting.

Meanwhile, prepare the sauce by combining the remaining 1/2 cup grenadine syrup with vermouth, orange juice, mustard, onions and ginger. Stir until blended. Mix cornstarch well with water, add to sauce and stir over low heat until thickened.
To serve, arrange slices of roast on each plate. Serve with sauce and garnish with pomegranate seeds.

title: a crock of butt roast
directions: Heat the vegetable oil in a fry pan on med-high heat until hot.
Salt and Pepper pork as desired and sear on all sides in the fry pan
Remove the pork from fry pan and place in the bottom of the crock pot.
Place the Sausage links into the same pan and sear on all sides.
Remove the Sausage links and place in the same crock pot.
Drain potatoes and pour into crock pot with the sausage and roast.
Add 3 cans of kraut to the crock pot.
Pour in the bottle of Guinness, the liquid should just cover the kraut.
Add Salt and Pepper as desired.
Put lid on crock pot and put on high until the liquid begins to simmer
lower heat to low and cook for 5-6 hours depending on the cut of meat and your altitude. The meat should fall apart easily with a fork, If not continue to cook checking in 15-20min increments,

title: kasetorte pops
directions: Bring the milk to a boil with the instant coffee and sugar. Add the pudding mix and prepare the pudding according to the instructions on the package.
Cool the mixture to warm and add the ricotta cheese, previously put through a sieve, combining well with a whisk to avoid lumps. The result should be a smooth, thick cream.
Fill the Zoku Mini Pops Molds with the cream mixture, add the sticks and place them in the freezer for at least 3 hours.
To serve, remove the pops from the molds and place each on a cookie, wait 5 to 8 minutes (they must not be too frozen) and sprinkle with bittersweet cocoa.

title: bakers brothers’ chocolate cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 160 degrees Celsius.
Lightly grease an 18- to 20-centimeter diameter high-sided cake pan.
In a large bowl, whisk together the cake flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and sugar.
Mix in the Golden Syrup and milk.
Separately, whisk together the eggs and the oil.
Stream this into the first mixture constantly, beating until well combined.
Fill the cake pan to no more than 2/3 its height and bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
While the cake bakes, make the ganache frosting.
Pour the chocolate chunks, cream, and Golden Syrup into a double boiler.
Boil the water underneath making sure the water never touches the top pot.
Stir until the ganache is smooth and shiny.
Set aside to cool.
Once done, let the cake cool inside the cake pan, then invert.
Slice horizontally.
Spread ganache on the top of the bottom half of the cake.
Place the other half of the cake on top and frost the whole cake with the rest of the ganache.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Start by heating the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Roll the pie crust out on baking paper and prick it with a fork so that it breathes during baking. Set it aside.
Separate the egg yolks from the whites.
Whisk the yolks well, mixed with the sugar.
Add the cream cheese, cocoa powder, vanilla extract, and hazlenuts to the egg yolks and sugar and whisk again. Set the mix aside.
Whisk the egg whites until they peak, then gently mix in rest of the batter and stir carefully with a spoon from the bottom to up.
Pour the filling into the pie crust and bake it in the oven for about 35 minutes or until it is cooked.
Remove, take it out of the tin, and serve cold.

title: chocolate pots de creme
directions: In medium bowl, whisk milk, 1/2 cup of the cream, eggs and Stevia In The Raw until completely smooth. Pour in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Cook over medium-low heat until mixture thickens and thermometer reads 160°F, stirring constantly with wire whisk. Do Not Let Boil. Remove from heat. Stir in extract and chocolate until melted and mixture is smooth. Pour into 8 small (1/4-cup) dessert dishes. Refrigerate 2 hours or until completely chilled. When ready to serve, whip remaining 1/2 cup whipping cream with remaining 1 tablespoon Stevia In the Raw until stiff peaks form. Top each serving with whipped cream and garnish with raspberry and mint.

title: baked country chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350^. In skillet, poach the chicken breasts until tender.

Set aside. Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in skillet. Stir in flour and cook for 3 minutes. Slowly add cream and chicken stock, stirring until smooth and thickened. Season with the salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese and herbs. Set aside. Saute mushrooms in remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Place the chicken in a 2 quart casserole and top with mushrooms. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour sauce over and bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with almonds. Return to oven for 10 minutes. Peel and

title: mexican-style meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat and cook onion, stirring occasionally, 4 minutes or until tender. Remove onion from skillet and let cool.

Combine ground beef, zucchini, egg, cooked onion, remaining 2 tablespoons jalapeno peppers, 1/2 cup sauce mixture and black pepper in large bowl. Shape into loaf in 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan. Top with 1/2 cup sauce mixture.

Meanwhile, bring Pasta Sauce and 2 tablespoons jalapeno peppers to a boil over high heat in same skillet. Reduce heat to low and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 4 minutes. Stir in 2 tablespoons cilantro; set aside.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons cilantro and garnish, if desired, with additional pickled jalapenos. Serve with hot rice and remaining sauce mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: “caprichosa” salad
directions: Place the lettuce, artichoke hearts, mushrooms, tomato, peas, and onion in a salad bowl
In another bowl, add pesto, lemon juice, lemon zest, and olive oil. Mix well.
Pour the dressing onto the salad ingredients and mix well
Finally, cover the salad with cheese and the strips of pastrami.

title: red lentil stew scented with pennyroyal
directions: Stew the chopped onion, diced tomato, and carrot slices in a little water.
Add the minced garlic, ginger, and salt. Simmer for a few minutes to bring out the flavors.
Add the lentils, tomato paste, bouillon cube, and enough water to cover (or slightly more) the lentils.
Simmer until the lentils are cooked, from 10 to 15 minutes.
To serve, sprinkle with lemon juice, and sprigs of pennyroyal.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Place sausage links on a broiling tray and broil until golden brown.
While sausage is browning, in a large skillet heat 2 tablespoons or so of oil and add peppers and onions. Cook veggies until slightly golden brown.
Add browned sausage and veggies to crockpot. Add between 2 to 4 cups spagehtti sauce stir and cook on HIGH for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: pizza bites
directions: Kids will love these...and adults will too! Top New York Style Bagel Crisps(R) with pasta or pizza sauce, add a slice of pepperoni and sprinkle on shredded mozzarella cheese. Serve cold or bake until cheese melts. Want more options? Go Hawaiian with a slice of ham and a pineapple chunk. Substitute BBQ sauce and sliced chicken for BBQ Chicken Pizza. The possibilities are endless...and delicious.

title: sparkrecipes is powered by sparkpeople.com trackers | articles | community high protein, fiber and low fat breakfast burrito
directions: Portion the turkey as soon as you get home from the market and place in ziplock bags for easy use and portion control for this recipe.

Brown the turkey in a skillet coated with some pam. Add the bell pepper and onion and saute until softened. Add the 3 egg whites and cook to desired firmness. Add desired hot sauce to skillet and toss to coat.
Take the tortilla and heat in microwave for 10 seconds. Place all the skillet ingredients down the center of the burrito. Add the cheese and cilantro and finally roll up like a burrito. Enjoy!

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add the eggs, one by one, continuing to mix. Add the vanilla.
Stir in half of the flour, continuing to mix. Turn the dough out onto the countertop, add the rest of the flour, and knead, forming into a ball.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Remove from the refrigerator, roll out the dough until approximately 1 centimeter thick, and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake for 8 minutes, until slightly brown around the edges. Place onto a baking rack to cool.

title: croque mademoiselle
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees Fahrenheit.
Preheat a stovetop grill on high heat.
Sprinkle olive oil, salt, black pepper and Provencal herbs on the slices of zucchini.
Place the zucchini on the grill and cook each side for 4 minutes. Set them aside for later use.
Melt the butter in a separate pan. Add the flour and cook it on low heat for 1 minute.
Add milk and stir it until it becomes a thick texture. Add the mustard and nutmeg, and set the mixture aside for later use.
Spread some butter on each slice of bread.
Add 6 tablespoon of cheese on the side of the bread that is not buttered.
Place the slices of zucchini on the cheese, and then add another 6 tablespoons of cheese onto the zucchini.
Place the other slice of bread on top making sure that the side with butter on it is facing out. Grill the sandwich on a skillet or toaster oven for about 3 minutes on each side.

Place the sandwich in a casserole dish and pour the sauce on top of it. Add in the remaining cheese onto the sandwich. Bake the sandwich for about 5 minutes or until the cheese on top melts. Serve hot.

title: a great test of a cod pudding recipe
directions: Cut the cod into large cubes, mix finely and add the fish stock, lemon juice, potato starch and 2 eggs.
Salt and pepper.
Add the milk gradually while mixing.
Mix it for about 5 minutes so that mixture thickens slightly.
Arrange in the middle of a cling film (heat resistant) 2 csp of the mixture and a peeled crayfish.
Roll the pudding while holding the ends.
Tie each end and squeeze a little to chase the air (I tied it with freezer bags strings ) and prepare similarly all the rolls until all the stuffing has been used.
Then steam the puddings for 10 minutes.
(I used a bamboo basket which I use for Chinese dumplings).
I tried to take pictures at each step to make it a little clearer for you.
Pull the puddings out of the bamboo basket.
In a pan heat a piece of butter, brown a chopped shallot, add the rest of the crayfish.
Stir and cook for 4/5 minutes and add the baby spinach.
Stir and cook, add 2 tablespoons of cream cheese (or cream).
Arrange the cod "sausage" and spinach with the crayfish sauce on a plate.
The next day I had some "sausages" left, I felt like cooking them differently.
They are cut into thick slices, passed in egg yolk and breadcrumbs then they are cooked in a pan with a little olive oil.
Serve eith tomato sauce and olives and fried baby potatoes.
This version has had more success with my girls because it was crispier but nevertheless the two versions were very much appreciated and I really want to test it with other fishes.

title: smoky black bean dip
directions: Place beans, adobo sauce, salt and garlic pepper in a food processor, and pulse until just broken up.
Add the tomatoes, lime, jalapeno, red onion and cilantro into food processor with the beans and pulse until just combined.
Serve with a fresh grated cheddar, cilantro, a dollop of low fat sour cream and some organic blue corn chips.

title: thai green curry
directions: Chop the bunch of coriander (stems too).

In a wok, heat a dash of oil. Fry the coriander stems and half of leaves for a few seconds. Add the curry paste and stir until the mixture becomes fragrant. Pour the coconut milk and reduce the heat. When it starts boiling, add the chicken and cook for 20 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add fish sauce, sugar, and shredded kaffir lime leaves. Stir and cook for 5 more minutes.
Before serving, add the remaining cilantro and basil leaves.
Serve with sticky rice.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Prepare the artichokes by removing the tough exterior leaves and washing them well.
Place them in a stockpot with water and the lemon juice, blanch them and remove them from the water as soon as it starts to boil. Let them cool.
In the meantime, wash the dried mushrooms and soak them in some warm water. Soak the crumbs in some broth.
When the artichokes have cooled, remove the stems and the centers.
Chop up the stems and the centers of the artichokes and place them in a bowl.
Squeeze the excess water from the mushrooms and chop them.
Chop up the chicken livers, break up the sausage into small pieces, squeeze the excess broth from the crumbs, and place all these ingredients in the bowl with the chopped artichoke.
Add chopped onion, parsley, and bacon to the mixture in the bowl.
Add the egg yolk and season with salt and ground pepper and stir well to combine.

Fill the center of the artichokes with this mixture, place the artichokes in a baking dish with a generous amount of olive oil, add a few pieces of butter, and some ground white pepper, cover and bake at 200C.
Add the wine after 30 minutes and allow it to evaporate in the covered baking dish.
The artichokes can be serve as an appetizer, a side dish, or a first course.

title: caesar salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. To make the croutons, toss together the bread cubes and oil, then spread over a baking tray and bake for 12 mins, shaking tray once or twice, until golden. Set aside to cool
To make the caesar dressing, whisk the lemon and anchovies together. Season to taste and gradually whisk in the oil until slightly thickened.

Cook the eggs in a pan of simmering water on low heat for 3-5 mins. Remove and set aside. In a salad bowl, toss the lettuce with croutons and dressing. Carefully crack the lightly cooked eggs in half and scoop the egg out from the shells, and add them to the salad. Add the parmesan, toss gently, season to taste and serve.

title: spicy chicken and potato salad
directions: Boil the carrots and potatoes until tender. Remove from heat and add the peas and corn. After 2 minutes, drain the vegetables and remove from pan.
Mix the drained vegetables with the onion, mayonnaise, and mustard. Add salt and pepper.
Prepare the chicken according to the directions on the package.
Melt the butter and mix together with the salsa. Dip the pieces of chicken into the butter mixture.
Place the lettuce on a serving dish and layer with the potato salad and the chicken.

title: vanilla shortbread cookies
directions: Mix all the "dry" ingredients in a medium-sized bowl (flour, almond meal, brown sugar, a pinch of salt, and vanilla seeds).
Make a well and pour in the egg yolks and the butter.
Mix the dough with your fingertips and knead until obtaining a ball.
If you have a food processor, place all the ingredients into the bowl with the hook at once and run on medium until the dough forms a ball and comes away clean from the sides.
Wrap the ball in a cling film and put it in the refrigerator for 2-3 hours.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Take out the dough ball and take one third of it (it will be easier to manage).
On a floured surface, thinly roll out the dough with a rolling pin.
Using cookie cutters, cut out cookies.
If you want to use the cookies as Christmas tree ornaments, remember to poke a small hole at the top (using a straw for example), so that you can hang the cookies on the tree.
Bake the cookies for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let them cool completely before decorating.

In the pastry aisle of your grocery store, you can find special pencils to decorate the cookies. If you prefer, use powdered sugar for the icing: mix 200 grams of powdered sugar with 2-3 tablespoons of water (to color the icing, use food coloring or replace the water with grenadine syrup).

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, whisk eggs with 1/3 cup water. Add hot sauce. In a separate shallow dish, combine flour and pepper. Season chicken with garlic powder, onion powder and 1 tsp salt. Dip in egg then coat in flour.
Heat oil to 350°F. Fry chicken until lightly browned and crispy.

title: pork chops with pesto stuffing
directions: With a sharp knife cut opening in the rib side of each chop. Insert knife in each opening and cut a pocket without cutting through to other side of chop. Set chops aside.

Place basil, parsley, Parmesan cheese, pine nuts and garlic in blender container or food processor bowl. Blend or process about 30 seconds or until finely chopped. With blender or food processor running, add 1 tablespoon olive oil. Transfer mixture to a small bowl; stir in bread pieces. Sprinkle water over bread mixture, tossing lightly to combine.

Spoon about 1/2 cup stuffing mixture into each chop. In a large skillet, brown chops on each side in the remaining hot oil. Place chops in a large baking dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake, uncovered, in a 350 degree F. oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until tender.

title: tined filhoses
directions: Pour flour In a large bowl, and make a well in the middle, add sugar, butter, orange zest, ginger and eggs in the well.
Mix well, then gradually add milk and orange juice.
Whip for a few more minutes until custard is uniform and creamy.
Dip whey in a frying pan with hot oil for a few seconds (this step is really important).
Drain a little, and then dip in dough without fully covering it.
Place whey in a little oil and stir until the dough is freed.
If the filhoses are too thin, steep a few more seconds in the dough, or add a little more flour until the desired consistency is attained.
Fry on both sides until golden.
Remove and place on a paper towel to absorb excess grease.
Once slightly cooled, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon to taste.

title: pork chops with corn stuffing
directions: Cut an opening in each chop from the rib side, widening the pocket, without cutting through the other side of the chop. Set aside.
Cook onion in butter in a medium saucepan 2-3 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in crumbs, corn, thyme and pepper. Fill pocket in each chop with an equal amount of stuffing.
Heat oil in a large skillet; add chops and brown on each side. Pour off drippings. Add water; cover tightly and cook over low heat 20-30 minutes. Allow to pork to rest 5 minutes before serving.

title: nutty blue cheese-stuffed pork chops
directions: For stuffing, stir together carrot, pecans, 1/4 cup blue cheese, green onion and Worcestershire sauce in small bowl. Cut opening in each chop from the outer side; widen opening into pocket, being careful not to cut through the other side of the chop. Fill pockets in chops with equal amounts of the stuffing. Secure with toothpicks. Grill, covered, over medium fire for about 12-16 minutes or until internal temperature is 145 degrees Fahrenheit, followed by a 3-minute rest time.

For sauce, stir together yogurt and flour in small saucepan. Whisk in milk, bouillon granules and pepper. Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, whisking constantly. Cook and whisk for 2 minutes more. Stir in 2 tablespoons blue cheese, if desired. Remove toothpicks from chops. Spoon sauce over chops.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 150C.
Line a loaf tin with parchment paper.
In large bowl, add the flour, salt, baking powder, and baking soda, and make a well in the center.
Heat the milk and molasses on low heat until dissolved, stirring continuously.
Add the milk to the well of dry ingredients, and gradually mix together with a spoon until the dough is smooth.
Fill the loaf tin with dough up to 3/4 full.
Bake for at least 1 hour. Test with a skewer-if it comes out clean it is done.
Leave to cool on a cooling rack.
Best eaten the same day.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 190 degrees Celsius.
Mix the butter, vegetable oil, and 150 grams of sugar in a large bowl. Then slowly add the eggs and milk.
Add the white flour, yeast, a pinch of salt, granulated sugar, vanilla extract, and blueberries. Do not overbeat.
Mix the Quark cheese, 50 grams of sugar, vanilla pudding powder, and lemon zest in a small bowl.
Fill the muffin molds halfway with the batter, spread 1 tablespoon Quark cheese mixture on each, then finish filling them with batter.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove them from the oven, sprinkle powdered sugar on top, let them cool off, and serve.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Place chopped bittersweet chocolate in blender. Add 1/4 cup boiling water and process 30 seconds on speed 2 (chop).
Add 1/4 cup heavy cream, vanilla, espresso powder, and 1 egg. Process 15 seconds on speed 3 (mix). Divide between 4 small bowls. Chill 1 hour.
Place chopped milk chocolate in blender. Add 1/4 cup boiling water and process 30 seconds on speed 2 (chop).
Add 1/4 cup heavy cream, vanilla and 1 egg. Process 15 seconds on speed 3 (mix). Pour onto bittersweet layer. Chill 1 hour.
Place chopped white chocolate in blender. Add 1/4 cup boiling water and process 30 seconds on speed 2 (chop).
Add 1/4 cup heavy cream, vanilla and 1 egg. Process 15 seconds on speed 3 (mix). Pour onto milk chocolate layer. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 170 Celsius.

Melt the chocolate and butter together in a double broiler. Separate the eggs and yolks and beat the whites into peaks with half of the sugar. Beat the yolks with the other half of the sugar until white and fluffy. Add the melted chocolate to the yolks, beating constantly until well mixed.
Sift the flour and yeast together and fold into the yolk mixture. Add the almonds and stir. Carefully fold in the whites little by little.
Pour into a greased and floured pan and bake for 25 minutes, until an inserted toothpick comes out clean. Remove from oven and let cool on a rack.
Make the syrup by combining the water, sugar, and brandy in a saucepan on low heat. Let cool and set aside.

Whip half cream with the sugar and the stabilizer. Whip the other half of the cream with the mascarpone. Add the food coloring to the mascarpone mixture and then carefully combine with the sweetened cream.
Cut the cake in half horizontally, drizzle with syrup, and fill with the cream.

Make the glaze by placing the cream into a pan. When it begins to bubble, remove from heat and add the chocolate and butter. Stir until the chocolate is completely melted. Pour over the cake and allow to solidify.
Decorate with strawberries before serving.

title: express 2 minute coffee cup cake
directions: Soften the butter in the microwave for 10 seconds, add sugar, and mix together with a fork.
Add the fresh cream and mix.
Add the egg, then flour and baking powder. Mix until you get a smooth dough.
Pour in cups filling to 2/3 full, the cake will inflate while cooking.
Prepare the streusel with your fingers, mixing butter, sugar, and flour to a coarse sand. Drop on each cake.
Microwave for about 1 minute, then for 10 to 50 seconds so that the cake is perfectly cooked, and doesn't explode in your microwave.
Flavor the cake with vanilla, and the streusel with cinnamon.
Serve with a strawberry salad.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Place all ingredients in a tall saucepan or pot and cook at low/medium heat. When the mixture starts boiling, lower the heat slightly and let simmer, stirring occasionally.
When the strawberries are soft, remove the cinnamon stick and mix the jam with a hand blender. Do not remove from heat.

Cook until the jam is ready. To check if the jam is ready, drop a bit on a smooth surface and pass a spoon through it. If the jam leaves a "road" (which doesn't disappear immediately) when a spoon passes through it, it is ready.
Remove from the heat and place immediately in sterilized jars.
Turn the bottles upside down until they cool completely.
To serve: spread on bread or crackers, or use to fill cakes and pies.

title: kiwi jelly
directions: Gently pulse kiwi in a blender and set aside. In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and 1 cup water and stir on low heat, until sugar has dissolved. Increase heat to high and boil 2 mins. Add kiwi and lime juice. Cover and cool 5 mins. Sprinkle in gelatin and stir until dissolved. Strain mixture through a fine sieve. Pour into small glasses or serving bowls and chill 3 hours, until set. Top with small scoops of sorbet to serve.

title: spicy (or not) pork ribs
directions: Start the process 1 day ahead of time. Cut the ribs American style so there are 3 ribs on each section.
In a blender, blend together the onion, garlic, chili peppers (optional), dried oregano, cumin, ketchup, brown sugar, dark beer, and a pinch of salt.
In a large Dutch oven add the rib pieces and pour the blended mixture on top. Bring to a boil. Partially cover and simmer on low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Taste the sauce and add salt or chili to taste.
Pour the ribs and the sauce into a dish that is not aluminum or metal and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Line a baking pan with parchment paper.
Remove the ribs from their marinade and try to shake off as much of the marinade as possible. Lay the ribs out on the baking tray and bake about 20 minutes until golden.
Put the reserved marinade in a saucepan and simmer until reduced.
Garnish the ribs with fresh parsley or cilantro and serve the sauce on the side. Grilled potatoes and guacamole make a great accompaniment.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes in water with a pinch of salt for 15 minutes, until tender. Mash and add the butter.
Heat the broth and add to the potatoes.
Saute the mushrooms and onion in a little olive oil in a skillet. Add to the potato mixture, reserving a few of the mushrooms. Season with salt, pepper, nutmeg, and thyme.
