Ladle the soup into serving bowls and garnish with the reserved mushrooms and additional thyme.

title: spiced peach daiquiri
directions: Add ice to blender carafe, cover and use highest speed to crush.
Add peaches, light rum, lime juice and agave nectar.
Blend until smooth and slushy.
Pour into cocktail glasses.
Drizzle 1/2 oz spiced rum over top of each drink.

title: fast and easy sweet-and-sour fried chicken
directions: Cut the chicken breasts into small pieces, place in a bowl
Combine soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch for marinade. Add to chicken. Stir.
Prepare the sauce in a bowl, combine tomatoes, vinegar, soy sauce, 1/2 tablespoon cornstarch, and sugar. Set aside.
Peel the peppers and remove the seeds.
Cut into small cubes.
Heat a frying pan with 1 tablespoon of olive oil in it, brown the chicken pieces.

Remove from pan, pour in the second tablespoon of oil, fry the peppers over low heat until tender (about 5-7 minutes). Add chicken, the drained pineapple, and then the sauce. Mix, add a little water to obtain a texture that's not too thick (cornstarch will help thicken quickly, do not hesitate to add water).
Cook about 15 minutes.
To serve, sprinkle chicken with sesame seeds, and accompany with white rice.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Mix panko and seasonings in shallow dish. Moisten chicken with milk. Coat evenly with panko mixture.
Place chicken in single layer on foil-lined 15x10x1-inch baking pan sprayed with no stick cooking spray. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: roast chicken and baked rice
directions: Chicken Preparation
Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Cut the tomatoes in quarters, and spread in a baking pan.
Cut the onion in quarters, slice the leek, and add to the baking pan.
With a knife, press the garlic cloves to crack the shell, and distribute them over the vegetables.
Season with a pinch of salt, thyme, and parsley.
Remove the skin and bones from the chicken breast, and cut it in medium-sized pieces. Save the chicken skin.
In a bowl, mix the olive oil, vinegar, salt, and pepper. Mix the chicken thoroughly in this sauce.
Place the chicken on top of the vegetables, and mix everything.
Bake for 1 hour, until the chicken is golden.
Rice Preparation:
In a saucepan, heat salted water.
When boiling, add the chicken carcass, chicken skin, carrots, garlic, and bay leaf.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Heat a casserole, without plastic handles, on the stove-top with a little olive oil.
Add 1 cup of wild rice, and fry for 2 minutes, stirring to avoid burning.
Add 2 cups of the broth, prepared with the chicken carcass, and stir.
Check the seasoning, and let boil.
Once it starts to boil, transfer the casserole to the oven, and finish cooking (about 10 minutes).

title: caesar salad
directions: Cook the egg for 1 minute in boiling water. Let cool.
In a bowl, mix the oil, vinegar, mustard, lemon juice, salt, pepper, and 1 clove of crushed garlic. Mix vigorously until the mixture is smooth. Add the egg, and beat again.

Cut the baguette lengthwise, and rub each half with the remaining garlic clove. Then cut the baguette into cubes. In a pan, heat the olive oil with the garlic used for the bread. When the oil is hot and fragrant, remove the garlic, and brown the croutons. Stir regularly and remove from heat when golden.
Put the cut lettuce leaves on the bottom of the bowl, then place on top the croutons, chopped anchovies, and the chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, and serve the sauce on the side.

title: southwest chicken and black bean salad
directions: Brush chicken with 2 tablespoons of the oil. Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of the Seasoning.
Broil or grill over medium heat 6 to 8 minutes per side or until cooked through. Cut chicken into thin strips.

Mix remaining 1/4 cup oil, lime juice and remaining 4 teaspoons Seasoning in large bowl. Add chicken, beans, tomatoes, corn and onion; toss until well coated. Divide lettuce among 6 plates. Top with chicken mixture.

title: oat groats
directions: Bring 3 or 4 cups of water to a boil.
Add oat groats and boil uncovered for about 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When water starts to take on a milky, slightly thicker appearance, the groats should be cooked.
Strain cooked groats, and immediately begin steaming for another 5-7 minutes.
Separately, peel and dice apples.
Place in frying pan with enough oil to coat the pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon, cloves, and nutmeg on top to taste.
Fry on low to medium heat until softened but still slightly crunchy.
Combine oats (after steaming) with fried apples, and serve hot with maple syrup to taste.

title: citrus tart: grapefruit and blood orange tart with lemon cream
directions: Sweet Dough Preparation:
Sift the flour and the baking powder in a large bowl.
Mix the butter with sugar.
Add the butter and sugar mixture to the flour, and stir until the dough has a sandy texture.
Add the egg and mix again until the dough is crumbly.
Form a ball and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Freeze any leftover dough.
Filling Preparation:
Carefully cut the orange and grapefruit supremes.
Lemon Cream Preparation:
Beat the egg yolks, sieve, then pour in a saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice and sugar.
Over medium heat, stir for ten minutes with a spatula until the mixture thickens slightly.
It will continue to thicken as it cools.
Remove the pan from heat, stir in lemon zest and diced butter.
Stir until butter is completely melted.
Cool the lemon cream in a small glass container, cover when it is very cold.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
Roll out the dough and spread in small pie pans. (Prick with a fork before baking).
Bake the tart shells for about 15 minutes. Let cool.
Pour the lemon cream into each pie shell, garnish with grapefruit and orange supremes.

title: butternut squash soup.
directions: Peel the onion, cut it into small pieces.
Peel the squash and cut it into cubes.
In a small saucepan, heat the olive oil.
Add onion and squash, saute over high heat for about 5 minutes.
Add cumin, coriander, ginger, and cinnamon, stir and cook for another 4 minutes.
Add the chicken stock to cover the vegetables.
Peel the apple and cut it into quarters, add to the soup.
Cover and cook for 25-20 minutes over medium heat, until squash is tender.
Transfer to a blender, and blend until smooth, adding a little more broth if necessary.
Add cream and mix for 3-4 minutes.
Divide the soup into soup bowls, garnish with remaining apple cut into sticks.

title: turducken with apple cider gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a medium baking dish.

For the stuffing, heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Saute shallots for 1-2 mins, until tender. Add apples, sage and cinnamon. Cook for 8 mins, stirring occasionally. Add breadcrumbs and syrup. Chill for 10 mins then mix in egg.

For the turducken, arrange prosciutto on a cutting board, slightly overlapping, into a large rectangle. Place turkey breast on top followed by chicken then duck. Spread stuffing over 2/3 of meat. Tightly roll up to enclose filling, ensuring prosciutto wraps around outside. Truss with butcher's twine at 3/4 inch intervals to secure.

Transfer to prepared dish and brush with oil. Add 1 cup cider to dish. Bake for 1 hour 20 mins, basting every 20 mins. Brush with maple syrup and bake for another 10 mins. Let rest, covered loosely in foil, for 15 mins.
Meanwhile, strain pan juices into a small saucepan. Add remaining cider and simmer over medium heat for 8-10 mins, until reduced by 1/2.
Serve turducken, sliced, with apple cider gravy.

title: creamy pate
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet on high heat. Add onion and garlic; cook 2-3 mins, until onion is tender.

Add chicken livers; cook 5-7 mins, until brown and cooked through. Transfer to a food processor. Add cream cheese and cognac or brandy. Season to taste. Process until smooth. Fold in thyme leaves. Spoon into a bowl. Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Sprinkle with additional thyme and serve with crackers.

title: pasta marco polo
directions: Combine sauce ingredients.
Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add oil & heat.
Stir fry chicken until it begins to lose raw color.
Add scallions.
Add sauce.
Add cooked pasta and stir until blended.

title: zucchini soup with tarragon and three cheeses
directions: Boil the zucchini in the water or broth with the tarragon and allow to simmer for approximately 15 minutes, until the zucchini is tender.
Let cool slightly before blending in the blender. Return the mixture to the pot, salt and pepper to taste, and allow to come to a slight boil.
Divide the cheeses in 4 portions and place 1 portion in the bottom of each of the serving bowls. Spoon the soup over the cheese.

title: salty muffins
directions: Mix the butter with the brown sugar, pepper, and salt in a large bowl.
Add the white flour, yeast, eggs, and beer, and mix.
Heat a skillet with a dash vegetable oil at medium flame, add the onion and bacon, and cook while stirring occasionally until the onion looks transparent.
Add the onion, bacon, and sun dried tomatoes to the dough, mix, and let it sit for 30 minutes.
Mix the garlic, vegetable oil, basil, and 2 tablespoons pesto sauce in a small bowl. Add the cherry tomatoes and let it sit for 30 minutes.
Fill the muffin molds halfway with the dough, then spread the cherry tomato mixture on top.
Add the remaining pesto sauce to the dough, then fill the other half of the muffin molds with it.
Sprinkle mozzarella cheese on top of each muffin and let them sit for 15 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Bake the muffins for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove them from the oven, let them cool off, and serve.

title: bacon and cheese stuffed bread - thermomix recipe
directions: Begin preparing the dough by pouring into the cup the milk, margarine and sugar.
Mix 1 min., temp. 37 spd.2.
Add the fresh yeast, undoing a bit with your hands and involve 10 sec., spd.2.
Add the flour and the salt and stir for 20 sec., speed 6. Then, knead for 3 min., speed Cob.
Remove the dough to a lightly floured counter and stretch it with the roller to a rectangular shape.
Sprinkle the dough with a little bit of olive oil and cover with the bacon broken into small pieces and slices of Flemish cheese.
Roll the dough like a pie, "gluing" the end of the dough with a little bit of water.
Make some cross cuts along the surface of the dough.
Put in a warm place (away from drafts and cold air) and cover with a cloth until it increases the volume, for about 1:30h.
After this time turn the oven to 180°C.
Brush the dough with egg yolk and sprinkle with sunflower seeds and sesame seeds.
Bake in the oven already heated up about 30 minutes or until golden.
Eat hot, warm or cold!

title: banana and peanut butter ice cream
directions: Cut 4 very ripe bananas and freeze for 4 hours, or overnight.
Place the frozen bananas in the food processor or blender. Use the metal blade in the food processor. Turn on the pulse button, and leave on until the bananas become creamy.
Add 1 tablespoon of peanut butter, or chocolate/chocolate chips, and stir some more.
To serve, garnish with peanuts.

title: slow cooker mashed potatoes
directions: Spray inside of 6-quart slow cooker with no stick cooking spray. Add potatoes, stock and bay leaves. Cover.
Cook 4 hours on HIGH or until potatoes are tender, stirring after each hour. Remove bay leaves. Stir in butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cover. Let stand 5 minutes.
Beat potatoes with electric mixer on medium-high speed or mash with potato masher, gradually adding milk, until smooth. Stir in parsley. Top with additional butter, if desired.

title: japanese salmon patties
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice, drained and flaked salmon, half the breadcrumbs, egg, ginger, soy sauce and chopped cilantro, green onions and chili. Mix well. Shape into 12 even-sized patties. Toss in the remaining breadcrumbs to coat. Chill until needed.

Heat enough vegetable oil in a pan for shallow frying. Cook patties in two batches, for 3-4 mins each side. Drain on paper towel. Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine mayonnaise and wasabi. Serve patties with wasabi mayonnaise, salad and lime slices.

title: baked goat cheese salad
directions: Pour the olive oil onto a plate.
Mix the breadcrumbs with the paprika, tarragon, and ginger. Set aside.
Dip each slice of cheese into the olive oil and then coat with the bread crumbs. Place into a baking dish. Broil until the cheese begins to melt and the bread crumbs begin to brown.
Prepare the vinaigrette by whisking together the mustard, vinegar, oil, salt, and pepper.
Place the lettuce onto serving plates and drizzle with vinaigrette. MIx to coat. Place the cheese on the bed of lettuce and sprinkle a little vinaigrette on top. Serve.

title: spinach, rice and feta cheese burgers!!!
directions: Heat a large frying pan with a drizzle of olive oil. Place the chopped onion and garlic in the pan to saute. When the onion softens add the creamed spinach to thaw.
In a large bowl combine two of the eggs, bread crumbs, crumbled feta cheese and the cooked rice. Mix these ingredients together.
Add the sauteed spinach, onion and garlic to the bowl.
Place the flour in a shallow bowl and the egg plus a splash of water in another shallow bowl.
Form the spinach and rice mixture into patties. Coat the patty dipping first in the flour and then the egg wash and back in the flour.
Heat a frying pan with about one inch of vegetable oil for frying the patties.
Carefully place the patties in the hot oil. When the patties are a beautiful golden color on one side, carefully turn them.
Place on a paper towel to absorb any excess oil.

title: orange-scented butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, form the dough into a ball, cover, and refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Roll the ball out into 1/2 centimeter thickness and cut out shapes with your favorite cookie cutter. Lay each cookie on the baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes until golden. Let cool on a wire rack before enjoying.

title: iberian pig, camembert cheese, and red bell pepper sauce tapas
directions: Preheat the oven to 170 degrees Celsius.
Coat the bell pepper with oil and season with salt. Add to a baking dish and roast for 1 hour. Turn every 15 minutes.
Remove the bell pepper from the oven and place in a resealable plastic bag. After 20 minutes, peel and seed the bell pepper.
Place the bell pepper flesh in the blender along with its juices and the sugar. Puree until smooth.
In a skillet, add a tablespoon of oil. Pan-sear the steaks for 5 minutes on each side.
Toast the slices of bread and add the Camembert cheese slices on top.
Once the steaks are done, place them top of the cheese so it will melt. Plate with some roasted pepper sauce on the steaks.

title: stove-top loin chops
directions: In a skillet, heat the olive oil, and cover for 2 to 3 minutes. Uncover, turn over the chops, and simmer for 2 minutes or more.
Sprinkle on top, the garlic, onion, and pepper.
Season with salt, and add the mustard, spreading over the onion.
Cover, and cook on low heat.
After about 10 minutes, mix every thing well, and sprinkle with white wine.
Simmer uncovered another 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve with white rice.

title: ruth's whipped shortbread
directions: Cream (6 on mixer) butter.
Add flour and icing sugar.
Whip (6-8 on mixer) until light and fluffy, upto 10 minutes
Pipe or spoon onto 1 inch balls. Top with decoration, (ie. kiss, chocolate ginger, jam, choclate coffee, etc)
Bake for 10-12 minutes, until just starting to golden on the edges.
Remove from pan, cool on rack.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven in 180 degrees Celsius.
Line pie dish with parchment paper.
With a food processor or a blender, grind the cookies to get fine crumbs.
In a medium bowl, combine cookie crumbs, sugar and melted butter. Mix well.
Press this mixture into the bottom and sides of the pie dish, with the back of a spoon.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes, then bake 15 minutes. Let cool.
With an electric mixer, beat egg yolks.
Gradually add condensed milk and keep beating for 3 minutes.
Add lemon juice, beat until well incorporated.
Pour the milk mixture over the cold pie crust.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature. Then, refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
With an electric mixer, whip the cream until stiff peaks form.
Using pastry bag fitted with a fluted tip, decorate the pie with whipped cream.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 160C.
Grease a 2.36 liter mold.
Beat together all the ingredients until smooth using a food processor or by hand. Ensure the coffee is piping hot so as to react with the soda and melt the butter.
Pour the cake mixture into the mold and bake for 50 minutes or until a skewer comes out clean.
Ensure the mold is never more than 3/4 quarters full otherwise it may overspill.
Leave to cool in the mold and cover with milk chocolate topping or white chocolate topping made with 50 milliliters cream, heated up, and add 100 grams white chocolate, stir until completely melted.

title: coffee ice cream
directions: Mix the coffee, cream cheese, and Mascarpone cheese well in a bowl.
In another bowl, beat the sugar and egg yolks until frothy.
In still another bowl, whip the cream and vanilla.
Combine the 3 mixtures in a bowl and cover. Place in the freezer for 4 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cocoa powder and serve.

title: tuna and sweet potato balls
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Mix the mashed sweet potato with the tuna fillets, breadcrumbs, egg, cumin and ginger.
Stir all of the ingredients together well.
With floured hands, form the mixed ingredients into small balls.
Place the balls on a greased baking sheet and put them in the oven for 15 minutes or until they are a nice golden brown.
Serve with a fresh salad.

title: new potatoes with beef stew
directions: Grease the slow cooker with some oil.
Add the red onion, the meat, the new potatoes, a handful of peas, the wine, the water, and a pinch of chopped rosemary.
Season with salt and stir.
Cook on low for 6 hours, then cook for 1 hour on high.

title: calhoca-style roast hake
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Place hake slices on a baking tray.
Add onion, garlic, bay leaf, Jamaica pepper, tomatoes, red pepper, and green pepper. Sprinkle with parsley.
Season with salt, pepper, and cumin.
Drizzle with wine and water, but do not cover the fish entirety (2/3 wine and 1/3 water).
Distribute pieces of butter on the fish, and sprinkle with a little of olive oil.
Bake for 20-25 minutes at 200 C, or until the cooking liquid bubbles, and the onion browns.
Accompany with potatoes and a salad.

title: braised lamb shanks
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Dust the lamb shanks with the seasoned flour, shaking off any excess.

Heat the oil in a Dutch oven on high heat. Cook the lamb shanks in batches for 4 mins, turning, until browned. Remove from pan. Reduce the heat to medium. Add the onion and cook for 5 mins, stirring, until softened.
Increase the heat to high. Add the balsamic vinegar and boil rapidly until reduced by half. Add the wine and bring to a boil. Stir in the tomato and anchovies.
Return the lamb shanks to the pan with the carrot and celery and top with thyme. Cover tightly with the lid or foil.
Bake for 1 1/2-2 hours, until the meat is falling off the bone. Uncover and cook for another 20 mins. Serve with mashed potato and lemon peel to garnish.

title: quick wedding soup
directions: Place the chicken breasts in 8 cups salted water and bring to a boil. Add the onion, carrots, bay leaf and peppercorns and simmer for about 45 mins. Remove the chicken breasts and leave to cool slightly. Strip the meat from the bones and cut into pieces. Strain the stock through a sieve, then bring back to a boil.

Cook the rice according to the packet instructions, adding the raisins 10 mins before the end of the cooking time. Add the frozen vegetables to the stock, bring to a boil and cook for about 15 mins. After about 5 mins, squeeze the sausages from the skins and add to the stock as meatballs. Add the asparagus and chicken pieces.

Beat together the eggs and milk and season with salt, pepper and a pinch of nutmeg. Heat a little oil in a 10 inch frying pan, add the egg mixture and cook over a low heat until set to form an omelette. Remove from the pan, allow to cool slightly then cut into diamond shapes.
Drain the rice and stir into the soup with the omelette triangles, green onions and chervil. Season and serve.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place stock, soy sauce and chili pepper in a medium saucepan on high heat. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Add chicken; simmer, uncovered, 5 mins or until chicken is cooked through.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions. Divide among 4 serving bowls.
Ladle soup into bowls. Top with onion, cilantro and bean sprouts. Serve soup with lemon wedges.

title: goulasch
directions: Place the oil and butter into a pan and saute the onion and garlic on medium heat for approximately 3 minutes, until soft. Add the paprika powders, tomato paste, sugar and bouillon. Once mixed well, add the tbsp. flour. Mix well.
Add the beer and the broth, allow to boil and then lower the heat to low. Simmer on low heat, covered, for approximately 5 minutes.
Add the carrots and the potatoes. Season the meat with a tbsp. of salt and a little pepper and add it to the pan. Also add the bay leaves, cumin and oregano.
Leave simmering, covered, for approximately 1 1/2 hours until all the ingredients are well-incorporated and the meat is softened.
Serve each bowl with a tbsp. of sour cream and a piece of bread.

title: white bean salad
directions: Soak the beans in water overnight.
Drain the beans and place into a saucepan and cover with water. Boil for 15 minutes on high heat, lower the heat, and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add salt and simmer for 5 minutes more, until tender. Set aside to cool.
Place the white beans, green beans, tuna, pimiento, and onion into a bowl. Add the salt, olive oil, and vinegar. Mix well.

title: thai fried rice
directions: Bring Knorr(R) Menu Flavors Rice SidesTM - Thai Curry, coconut milk and water to a boil in medium saucepan. Reduce heat to low and simmer covered 7 minutes, or until rice is tender. Let stand 2 minutes.

Meanwhile, heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and cook onion and red pepper, stirring occasionally, just until tender, about 3 minutes. Move vegetables to edge of skillet. Add egg in center of skillet and stir until cooked through.
Stir rice mixture into skillet and cook until rice is lightly browned, stirring occasionally. Stir in basil and lime juice.

title: walnut and potato chip crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Beat the butter with the sugar until the mixture is creamy.
Add the vanilla extract, and beat until well mixed.
Add the flour, chopped nuts, and finely chopped chips.
Beat on low speed until lightly mixed.
Form small balls, and place, spaced, on a baking pan lined with parchment paper, or a silicone mat.
Put some sugar crystals in a bowl.
Grease the bottom of a glass with butter.
Dip the glass in the bowl with the sugar, and press the glass on a ball of dough until it has the desired thickness, more or less flattened.
Repeat dipping and pressing with the remaining balls.
Bake in the middle of the oven at 180 C for 12 minutes, or until they appear to be dry on surface, with golden edges.
Remove from oven, and let cool.

title: the quarterjack
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a cocktail shaker.
Pour into a glass.
Garnish with a slice of pineapple and serve.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat 3 eggs together with the butter, sugar and vanilla. Add the flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder. Mix well. Set aside 1 cup of the mixture.
In a separate bowl, beat 1 egg with the cream cheese, milk, small amount of sugar and the peanut butter.

Pour the cocoa batter (minus 1 cup previously set aside) into a greased baking pan. Pour the peanut butter batter on top and then the last cup of cocoa batter. Use a fork to swirl through the batter, mixing slightly.
Bake for 30 minutes at 180 C.
Let cool and then cut the brownies.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Thoroughly beat the eggs, and then add the sugar.
Beat the egg and sugar mix, and then add the chocolate powder, flour, boiling water, cooking oil, and baking powder.
Bake mix at 180 degrees Celsius for 20 to 25 minutes.
In a pot, combine all of the ingredients for the frosting and bring them to a boil. Make sure to stir consistently until the mixture thickens.
This frosting recipe will be sufficient if you decide to make a cake with the cupcake mix instead of cupcakes.
For cupcakes, spread the frosting on each one, sprinkle with chocolate sprinkles, and serve.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Melt 2 tablespoons I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!(R) made with Olive Oil Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking pan in oven about 2 minutes. Spread to coat bottom of pan; set aside.

Lightly beat 2 eggs in large bowl. Stir in hash browns, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper. Press potato mixture into bottom and up sides of prepared pan. Bake 30 minutes or until potatoes are crisp.

Meanwhile, melt 1 tablespoon Spread in 12-inch skillet and cook mushrooms, red pepper and onion over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes or until vegetables are golden. Stir in 1/4 teaspoon salt; set aside and cool slightly.

Beat remaining 7 eggs, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon black pepper and vegetable mixture in same bowl. Pour over potato crust. Bake 10 minutes. Top with cheese and bake an additional 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: homemade breakfast pizza
directions: Slice the mushrooms, onions, frankfurters (or sausages when using) and tomatoes.
Fry the onion with bacon for 2-3 minutes until the onion turns brown and the bacon is cooked.
Place the pizza dough on a baking tray lined with baking paper. Spread baked beans over, followed by the rest of the sliced ingredients. Finally, crack a small egg on top of it.
Bake in a preheated oven @ 220C for 12-15 minutes or until ready. If using shop-bought dough then follow packet instructions.

title: sugar glazed pork
directions: Cut the pork into thin strips. Finely chop the onion and mince the garlic.

Caramelize the sugar in a pan with some water. Once the caramel has become golden, add the meat and stir over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes. Remove the meat with a slotted spoon (the meat may stick to caramel: this is normal and will disappear) and let the juice evaporate a little. Add onions and garlic and brown for a minute. Put the meat back in the pan and add the ginger, oyster sauce, and soy sauce. Mix and cover tightly. Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Serve with white rice.

title: hot southern apple pie spice
directions: In a small sauce pan over medium heat, add the water, apple pie spice, sugar and coffee.
Stir well to dissolve sugar and apple pie spice. Bring to a boil for 2-3 min.
Remove from heat, add creamer, pour into a mug and serve.

title: easy lemon pepper scampi
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium heat. Add garlic; cook and stir 30 seconds or until fragrant. (Do not brown.) Add shrimp and Seasoning; cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over cooked pasta or rice, if desired.

title: hearty lentil stew
directions: Heat Olive Oil in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat and cook carrots and celery, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes.
Add lentils and cook 1 minute. Stir in 2 cups water. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 25 minutes.

Stir in Lipton(R) Recipe Secrets(R) Savory Herb with Garlic Soup Mix blended with remaining 1 cup water. Simmer covered an additional 10 minutes or until lentils are tender. Stir in vinegar. Serve over hot couscous.

title: potato wedges & sweet chili sauce
directions: Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius/ 400 degrees Fahrenheit. Clean the potatoes very thoroughly, cut them into wedges, 6 to 8 edges pro potato depending on size. Place the potatoes in a large pot with cold water, bring everything to a boil and let the potatoes cook for about 10 minutes. They should be soft but shouldn't begin to disintegrate. Drain the potatoes and pat dry with kitchen paper. Place the potatoes in a roasting pan.

Mix together the olive oil, microplaned garlic, ground coriander, smoked and sweet paprika until you obtain a paste. Add 1 more tablespoon oil if you feel is necessary to get the right pasty consistency. Pour this over the potatoes and rub the all over with your hands. Place the tin in the oven for about 25 minutes or until the potatoes are crisp, brown and cooked through.

Meanwhile make the sweet chili sauce. Combine 1/4 water with the rice vinegar, sugar, minced garlic clove and chili flakes in a small saucepan. Bring everything to a boil and let simmer for about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Combine the rest 1/8 cup water with the cornstarch and whisk the mixture into the boiling sauce stirring continuously for 1 minute. Turn of the heat and let the sauce cool down before serving.
Serve the potatoes and sweet chili sauce with a salad on the side.

title: chickpea arancini
directions: Heat the oil in a small skillet on medium heat. Add the onion and crushed garlic from 2 cloves and saute for 3-4 mins until softened. Transfer to a bowl. Add the cooked rice, herbs, egg, cumin and 3 tbsp of the chickpeas.

Puree remaining chickpeas with 1 tbsp water in a blender or food processor. Add to the rice mixture and mix well. Season to taste. Refrigerate mixture for 20 mins. Meanwhile, for the tahini dip, mix yogurt, tahini and remaining garlic. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

Using damp hands, roll 2 tbsp of rice mixture to form 18 balls. Heat oil in a wok or large saucepan on high heat. Deep-fry the arancini in batches for 2-3 mins until golden and crispy. Drain on paper towels. Serve with the tahini dip, bread and salad.

title: chicken tikka masala
directions: To make the marinade, mix together the garlic, ginger, 1/4 cup cilantro, mint and 3 tbsp of olive oil, 1 tbsp of cumin, 1 tsp of salt, the oregano, Garam Masala and 2/3 cup of yogurt. Mix the chicken pieces into this mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat the oven to 400°F. Put the marinated chicken on a baking tray lined with parchment paper and bake for about 20 mins, or until cooked through.

In a large saucepan, combine 6 tbsp of mashed banana, 2/3 cup of yogurt, 6 tbsp olive oil, and the tomatoes and bring to a boil. Simmer over a low heat for 8-10 mins. Add the ground almonds, 1 tsp of salt and the coconut milk and bring back to a boil. Add the cooked chicken, stir well, and add the chili powder, 1/2 tbsp cumin, honey, turmeric and tandoori seasoning. Bring the mixture back to a boil and stir in the cream and remaining cilantro.
Serve garnished with extra cilantro with some naan bread on the side.

title: lemon bars
directions: To prepare the crust, preheat the oven to 180C.

Place the flour in a bowl with the powdered sugar, the grated peel of 1 lemon, and the salted butter, cut into pieces, use the tips of your fingers to combine the ingredients into an oatmeal-like consistency.
Line an 18 x 18 centimeter cake pan with wax paper and place the crust inside pressing it well and evenly with your hands or by using a weight.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes.
To prepare the lemon filling, use a whisk to beat the eggs with the sugar in a bowl.
Incorporate the two types of flour, add the lemon juice and peel and mix well.
Pour the filling over the warm crust and bake for an additional 25 to 30 minutes at 180C.
Remove the cake pan from the oven and cool completely.
Cut the lemon bars into small squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: chicken with parsley and hot sauce salad
directions: Mix the parsley, Valentina sauce, oil, and garlic. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Marinate the chicken in this mixture for 15 minutes in the refrigerator.
Roast the chicken in a hot skillet until golden brown on both sides. Let it cool and cut into strips.
Mix the mayonnaise, capers, a pinch of dill, and the mustard. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix the lettuce, bell pepper, tomato, onion, and cucumber. Dress the salad and toss carefully using tongs. Add the chicken strips and serve.

title: spinach salad with chicken, avocado, and corn
directions: Saute or grill the chicken in a pan on medium heat until it is done. Set aside and allow to cool for 5 minutes. Cut the chicken into cubes and add to a bowl.
Add the spinach, corn, tomato, avocado, and cheese to a bowl and toss well.
Add the mustard, vinegar, and a pinch of salt and black pepper to a small bowl and mix well. Slowly drizzle the oil into the bowl, whisking as you do,
Arrange the salad on a plate, pour the dressing onto the salad, and serve.

title: fishy pasta
directions: Place the fish in a roasting tin with the milk and water.
Cover lightly with foil hang the tin on the third set of runners from the top of the roasting ovenand poach for 15 to 20 minutes until cooked.
Heat water for pasta and cook according to instructions.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and fry the mushrooms until cooked.
Remove them to a plate with a slotted spoon and keep warm in the simmering oven.
Stir in the flour cook for 1 minute and then gradually beat in the fish cooking liquor. Stir and boil the sauce then add the mushrooms spring onions parsley and seasoning.
Simmer gently for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile remove the skin and bones from the fish and then flake the flesh into largish pieces.
Gently fold the fish and prawns into the sauce.
Cover and keep warm in the simmering ovenwhile the pasta is cooking.
Drain the pasta and top with the fish sauce.

This fish sauce is served with tagliatelle but it can also be used as a base for a fish pie. Top with finely sliced parboiled potatoes or mashed potatoes and bake in the roasting ovenfor 20 yo 30 minutes until piping hot and golden brown.

title: peanut butter and banana bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 180C.
Work the peanut butter with the raw sugar, then incorporate the mashed bananas.
Add the eggs, vanilla extract, and rum.
Sift the flour together with the baking powder, adding it to the batter and stir until it has been completely incorporated.
Add the chocolate, chopped coarsely.
Butter and flour a cake pan or line it with wax paper, pour the batter into the pan.
Bake for approximately 50 minutes.
Remove the cake from the oven, let it cool completely and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans. Line bottom and sides with parchment paper.

Sift flours into a large bowl. Add brown sugar, cinnamon and baking soda; mix well. Whisk eggs and sour cream in a large bowl. Stir in butter and banana. Stir egg mixture into flour mixture until smooth. Pour into prepared pans. Top with nuts and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake for 50-55 mins or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 mins. Remove from pans; cool completely on wire rack.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and line an 8x4 inch loaf pan with parchment paper.

Sift together flour and cinnamon. Add sugar. Combine bananas, butter, eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix into dry ingredients until just combined. Transfer to prepared pan, smooth top and bake for 40-45 mins, until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 5 mins then turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely.
Serve sliced with butter, if desired.

title: chicken curry
directions: Make a stew with olive oil and chopped onion.
Add the spices and keep stirring to release their aromas.
Add the chopped peeled tomatoes and let it cook for a little. Add the chicken and cut it into small pieces.
Cook over medium heat and with the covered pan to creating some sauce.
If necessary, add a little water.
Finally add the coconut milk, salt and let boil.
Garnish it with chopped coriander.
In a pan put the rice and twice as much water, a pinch of salt and the lemon and dried parsley.
Cook for capped and moderate heat.
As the water is evaporating it will create a hole, this is a sign of running out of water.
Turn off the heat and separate the rice with a fork.
Garnish with fresh chives and lemon bud.
While the chicken cooks, you can prepare the bread.
Just mix the flour with the melted and cooled butter, water and a pinch of salt.
Knead until it's a smooth dough and well connected.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 equal parts and shape balls.
Sprinkle the kitchen counter with flour and spread with the rolling pin until they are with a thin thickness.
Heat a pan (without no fat whatsoever) and toast it both sides.

title: swiss-style chicken
directions: Spritz a skillet with cooking spray and saute the onion and garlic over medium heat. When the onion is transparent, add the paprika, rosemary, ketchup, soy sauce, broth, lemon, and bay leaf. Cover and cook 4 minutes. Taste for seasoning and adjust.
Spritz another skillet with cooking spray and cook the chicken until golden brown on all sides. Sprinkle with the flour and stir one minute to cook the flour.
Add the chicken to the sauce, and cook for 2-3 minutes until the sauce thickens. Add the cream, stir to incorporate, and remove from heat.
Serve the chicken over the pasta. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: strawberry and mint slush
directions: In a sauce pan, place the strawberries, mint leaves, lemon juice, a pinch of salt, water and sugar.
Boil for at least 10 minutes, and using a fork keep crushing the strawberries to extract the juice, remove from heat and let cool completely.
Remove the mint leaves, and strain the strawberries to extract the juice. (The pieces of strawberry left in the strainer can be saved for an ice cream topping or a dessert).
Chop the ice finely in the blender. Pour ice into serving cups, and cover with the strawberry juice.

title: red velvet cupcakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius and place the cupcake liners in the cupcake pan.
Cream the 120 grams of butter with the sugar in a bowl using a hand mixer. Add the eggs, one at a time.
In another bowl, combine the cocoa with the food coloring and the vanilla extract and add this mixture to the butter, incorporating them well.
Sift the flour with the salt and add it to the butter, alternating with the buttermilk or yogurt.
Combine the vinegar with the baking soda and quickly add it to the batter. MIx well.
Fill the cupcake molds 2/3 full and bake them for approximately 20 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in the pan, remove the cupcakes from the pan and then cool them completely.
Melt the white chocolate with the remaining butter and mix well. Frost each cupcake.
Garnish with a candied cherry cut in half, and coat with the colored sprinkles.

title: fer’s mexican breakfast
directions: Brown the turkey ham slightly, for 2 minutes, in a skillet with a tsp. of vegetable oil. Add the onion and saute for 1 minute on medium heat, then add the celery, tomato and onion. Cook for 5 more minutes.
Mix the eggs in a separate bowl with a fork with salt and pepper and add them to the vegetables.
Add the beans and little more salt to taste and carefully mix in wide strokes so that the eggs remain fluffy.
Serve with flour tortillas and spicy salsa verde.

title: homemade granola
directions: Preheat oven to 160 ° C.
In a bowl, mix all the ingredients.
Spread the on a baking sheet covered with parchment paper.
Bake for about 45 minutes. Turn off the oven and leave the sheet in the oven until it has cooled completely.
Keep granola in an airtight container.

title: vegetable and feta couscous
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Toss sweet potatoes, zucchini and eggplants with olive oil. Season. Roast for 10 mins. Add tomatoes. Roast for another 10 mins, until vegetables are golden and tender.
Meanwhile, combine couscous and stock. Cover and set aside for 5 mins. Fluff with a fork. Add vegetables, spinach and vinegar. Toss to combine.
Serve topped with feta, pine nuts and parsley.

title: frisella with tomato and onion
directions: Dissolve the dry yeast in the water.
Place the bran in a bowl with the cornstarch and the salt.
Add the yeast and the water and combine well until a thin batter forms.
Place the batter in two rectangular parchment paper-lined loaf pans and set them aside to rise for 2 hours.
Preheat the oven to 190 degrees Celsius.
Place the loaf pans in the oven and bake for 25 minutes.
Remove the friselle bread from the loaf pans and broil for 2 minutes to brown the tops.
Place the tomatoes and onions in a bowl with some torn basil leaves.
Add the bread, broken into pieces, and the yogurt (or oil), plus a pinch of salt and black pepper and a teaspoon of balsamic vinegar.
Set aside for approximately 15 minutes.
Serve chilled but not cold. Add diced tuna, grilled tofu, or turkey for added protein.

title: fresh berry tart with coconut crust
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius and, unless they are silicon, grease the muffin tins with margarine or olive oil.
Combine the oatmeal, coconut, and brown sugar, and margarine in a bowl and mix well with a wooden spoon.
Place a small scoop of the crust dough in each muffin tin, tapping it down gently with a metal spoon to get the desired crust shape.

Bake for about 15 minutes or until the edges are a light golden brown. Remove them from the oven and allow them to cool for a few minutes before taking them out of the tin. Very carefully remove them from the tin and allow them to cool completely.
In a bowl, mix the Greek yogurt with the honey, jelly, and coconut and set it aside.
Fill the tart crusts with the yogurt mix and place the berries on top to taste. Refrigerate until it is time to serve.

title: english muffins
directions: The night before, make a fermented starter of 100 grams flour and 100 grams water with all the yeast. Stir, cover, and let sit overnight.

The next day, add the fermented mixture to the remaining 270 grams flour, 200 grams water, honey, and salt. Knead either with a kitchen stand mixer or by hand until the glutens start to form. Cover and let sit until doubled in volume.
Heat a large skillet or flat grill pan on medium heat.

Take 7- to 8-centimeter-diameter cookie cutters (as many as will fit in 1 skillet all at once) and grease them. Place them on the skillet to preheat. If the skillet is not a nonstick skillet, sprinkle it with cornstarch first.
Pinch off a section of dough and place it inside the cookie cutter. You may need to use your fingers to spread it out a bit. Do not make it thicker than 1 inch.
Toast the English muffin for at least 5 minutes. When the first side is toasted, flip and toast another 5 minutes. Remove from the cookie cutter mold and transfer to a baking rack to cool.
Repeat with the rest of the dough, making sure to grease the cookie cutters before each use.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: In a blender, add the strawberries, yogurt, ice cubes, and basil leaf. Blend until mixture is creamy. The basil's acid cuts some of the strawberries sweetness. Add more sugar if desired. Pour into a glass and serve immediately.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Combine refried beans, taco seasoning mix and onion in a medium bowl.
Divide bean mixture among 4 containers. Sprinkle with lettuce and tomato. Spoon salsa evenly over each.
Mash avocado with lemon juice in a small bowl. Spread over dips. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover with lid and refrigerate.
Preheat the oven to 400°F. Arrange tortilla wedges in a single layer on a foil-lined baking pan. Spray with no stick cooking spray. Bake 2-3 mins, until light golden. Cool. Serve with dip.

title: tuna gratin
directions: Mix the tuna, onion, bouillon and milk in a bowl with a little salt.
Prepare the rice, or buy precooked.
In a medium-sized baking dish, place in layers:
Half the tuna mixture, half the cooked rice, half the cream, half the cheese. Repeat with the other half of ingredients.
Bake at 200 C for approximately 15 minutes, until the cheese
browns slightly.

title: roasted garlic chicken & vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 425 F.
Blend Knorr(R) Homestyle Stock Reduced Sodium Chicken with olive oil and rosemary in small bowl. Toss mixture with remaining ingredients in 13 x 9-inch shallow roasting pan or dish.
Roast uncovered 45 minutes. Remove chicken to serving platter. Mash garlic, then stir into vegetable mixture. Top chicken with vegetables, then drizzle with juices in pan.

title: thai fish cakes
directions: Finely chop the red chilli and the fresh coriander.
To make the dip, stir together 1 dollop of Hellmann's Real mayonnaise, 1 tablespoon of soy sauce, the red chilli and fresh coriander and leave to stand whilst you make the fish cakes.
To make the fish cakes, put all the remaining ingredients into a food processor and blend until smooth
Then shape the mixture into about 12 cakes
Heat a tablespoon of oil in a frying pan. Add the fish cakes and cook over a medium heat for about 15 minutes, turning occasionally, until golden brown on both sides and nicely cooked through.

title: turmeric ginger beer
directions: Infuse Syrup: Grate ginger and turmeric. Place all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove pan from heat and let spices sit and infuse in the syrup while it is brought up to room temperature.
Strain syrup: I find it easiest to strain the syrup twice- first through a regular strainer, then through a fine-mesh teas strainer. Refrigerated, the syrup will keep for several weeks

Mix: Measure 2 Tablespoons of syrup into an eight ounce glass. Lightly crush the lemon peel and mint leaves with the back of a spoon. Squeeze the juice from one quarter of a lemon into the glass. Top with ice and soda water.

title: fried chicken and potatoes picnic box
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Toss potatoes with 3 tbsp of the oil in a large bowl. Season to taste. Divide evenly among 2 baking pans.
Bake for 25-30 mins, switching position of pans halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, place flour, combined milk and eggs, and breadcrumbs in 3 separate dishes. Coat chicken in flour, shaking off excess. Dip chicken into egg mixture and then into breadcrumbs, pressing firmly. Refrigerate for 15 mins.
Heat remaining 3 tbsp oil and butter in a large skillet on medium heat. Cook chicken in 2 batches, for 2-3 mins each side until golden.
Transfer chicken to a baking pan. Bake for 5 mins until cooked through. Slice into strips.
Serve chicken and potato wedges in paper boxes with lemon wedges.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Boil the macaroni until al dente.
Drain and set aside.
In a bowl, add the cheese, evaporated milk, eggs, and nutmeg.
Beat together.
Then add the salt and pepper to taste and beat again.
Pour the pasta into a baking dish and pour the cheese sauce on top. Stir everything together and sprinkle dried oregano on top.
Bake 15 minutes until the pasta is golden and the sauce is bubbly.

title: gluten free cinnamon scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a large bowl, mix together the almond flour, tapioca flour, salt, xanthan gum, baking powder, baking soda, and cinnamon.
Cut in the cold butter with a pastry cutter or 2 forks until it resembles tiny pea-sized balls.
In a small bowl, whisk together the egg, agave nectar, and vanilla.
So lets prep before we mix the wet and dry ingredients: Tear off 2 large pieces of parchment paper. Use one to line a baking sheet and dust the other one with tapioca flour.
Pour the wet ingredients into the flour mixture and mix using your hand.
Transfer to tapioca dusted parchment paper and roll in flour then form a circle about 1/2 in to 1 in. high.
Mix together the topping ingredients.
Use a pizza cutter and cut into 8 equal parts. Then drizzle the topping on and spread out with a spoon or your hand, which is what I prefer.
Carefully transfer the scones to the baking sheet place about an inch apart.
Bake for 8-10 minutes.
Dust with extra cinnamon and serve with coffee!

title: pumpkin fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions, adding green peas during the last 2 minutes of cook time. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water to thin sauce, if necessary.

Meanwhile, heat olive oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and cook chicken, stirring occasionally, until chicken is almost done, about 5 minutes . Remove chicken with slotted spoon and set aside.

Cook onion in same skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently, until onion is tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in pumpkin and cook, stirring frequently, until pumpkin is slightly darkened, about 2 minutes. Stir in Sauce. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and stir in fettuccine; toss to coat. Stir in sage and nutmeg. Thin sauce, if necessary, with pasta cooking water.

title: chicken cordon bleu alfredo
directions: Season chicken, if desired, with salt and ground black pepper. Evenly top chicken with prosciutto and cheese; roll up and secure with wooden toothpicks. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then bread crumbs, coating well.
Heat Olive Oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and brown chicken, turning occasionally. Remove chicken and set aside.

Stir in wine in same skillet and cook 1 minute. Stir in Sauce. Return chicken to skillet. Reduce heat to low and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 6 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked. Serve, if desired, with hot cooked rice or pasta and garnish with chopped parsley.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 10 mins. Drain and mash. Set aside to cool.
Combine salmon, potato, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce, pickles, lemon zest and parsley. Season. Shape into 12 patties and chill for 30 mins.
Dredge patties in flour, beaten eggs and breadcrumbs, pressing lightly until coated. Heat oil and cook patties for 3-5 mins, until golden, then flip and lightly cook other side, about 2 mins.
Serve salmon patties with mayonnaise, steamed mixed vegetables and lemon wedges.

title: mario batali's turkey sausage stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Bring 8 quarts water to the boil in a large pot and add 3 Tbsp.salt. Drop the shells into the water and cook until 3 minutes short of the suggested cooking time, then drain them in a colander and shock them in ice water until very cold. Place in a colander lined with paper towels to dry and rest.

In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium heat and add the sausage and cook until it begins to brown in its own fat. Add the flour and stir to distribute well and cook 5 minutes. Add the milk, bring to a boil and then reduce heat to a simmer. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring regularly, then remove from heat and allow to cool.
Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg and stir in the egg, the ricotta, the mayonnaise and the Romano cheese and mix well. Set aside.

Grease a 10 x 12-inch baking dish with extra virgin olive oil and set aside. Carefully stuff each shell with 2 to 3 Tbsp. of the turkey sausage mixture and lay each one open side up in the baking dish, next to one another, but not too crowded to squeeze each other. Spoon a good Tbsp. of the tomato sauce over each shell and then sprinkle grated Romano cheese over all.
Bake in the oven until bubbling hot, about 30 minutes. Remove; let rest 5 minutes and serve.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In a skillet on medium heat, add the oil and saute the shallot for a few minutes.
Add the potatoes and speck or ham and cook until golden brown.
Set aside a spoonful of potatoes, and then add the milk, stock, and a pinch of salt.
Cook on a low heat for about 1 1/2 hours and then place in a blender together with the creme fraiche and chives. Puree until smooth.
Serve hot in soup bowls with the remaining potatoes as garnish.

title: easy chili con carne
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook until translucent. Add the beef and potatoes, season with salt and pepper and cook until the beef is browned, breaking up the pieces with a wooden spoon. Spoon off the excess fat. Add the bell peppers and corn and cook for 5 mins. Add the tomato paste and stir for 1 min. Add the broth, diced tomatoes, cherry tomatoes, paprika and chili powder. Increase heat and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 20-25 mins until the flavors have blended. Sprinkle with the parsley and serve.

title: chocolate chip cakes
directions: Bring the water to a boil with the butter, a pinch of salt, the vin santo, and 25 grams of sugar.
Add the flour and stir continuously and keep the dough on the heat until it no longer sticks to the saucepan while sizzling lightly.
Place the dough in the mixer bowl and allow it to cool.
Knead the dough with the mixer's hook attachment and add the eggs, one at a time, lemon zest, and chocolate chips (or raisins), and vanilla.
Heat the oil and add the dough in small spoonfuls. The dough will puff up and the interior will be almost hollow.
Drain the cakes on paper towel, coat them with powdered sugar, and serve hot.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef, onion, and garlic in 3qt sauce pan over medium heat for 8-10 minutes, stirring occasionally until beef is browned then drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except beans. Heat to boiling then reduce to simmer. Cover and continue simmering for 60 minutes.
Once the 60 minutes are up, stir in the beans. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes uncovered, stirring occasionally until you reach your desired thickness.
*** I like to throw in some fresh jalapenos for some heat and top it off with some sharp cheddar.

title: spring chicken
directions: Preheat oven 375°F.
Mix Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Real Mayonnaise, mustard, garlic and rosemary together. Rub the outside of each breast and then coat in breadcrumbs. Place on a roasting rack.
Toss carrots and onions in olive oil. Season carrots and onions with salt. and pepper and place on same rack.
Roast in the oven for 20 minutes or until the center of the chicken is 165°, or until thoroughly cooked.

title: italian flavored chicken meatballs
directions: In a bowl, mix the ground chicken, eggs, Parmesan cheese, and tomato tapenade with a fork. Add salt and pepper.
Make small balls with a 2 centimeter diameter.
Saute chicken balls in a hot pan with 2 tablespoons of olive oil until brown.
Cover the pan, and cook on a low heat for 10 minutes.
In a saucepan, heat tomato sauce and diced tomatoes.
Add basil and zucchini, salt, and pepper. Cook for 10 minutes, zucchini should be crunchy.
Pour the sauce over the meatballs, and stir.
Just before serving, remove from heat, and add the mozzarella balls.
Serve with polenta or pasta.

title: at-home, no-butter caramel popcorn
directions: add vegetable oil to medium saucepan and warm on low heat
add granulated sugar and stir with spatula until melted
add brown sugar and vanilla extract and combine -- mixture will still be grainy
add honey and stir continue stirring until sugar is completely melted -- a syrupy consistency will be achieved
remove saucepan from heat
spoon popcorn directly into the pan and use a spatula to roll it around until most of the popped kernels are covered in the caramel mixture
spread corn onto a baking sheet covered with wax paper and sprinkle with sea salt
allow to cool completely -- serve in a bowl

for a quicker option, you may alternatively put the popcorn in a bowl and drizzle the hot caramel mixture over the top and mix it in with a spatula -- sprinkle with sea salt and allow to cool before serving

title: ice cream cake
directions: Whip together heavy cream and condensed milk. Add brandy, if using, and spice mix. Fold in raspberries, glace fruit, chocolate and nuts. Line a large glass bowl with plastic wrap then add mixture. Smooth surface, cover with plastic wrap and chill until firm.
Meanwhile, to make the sauce, gently heat heavy cream and chocolate until melted and smooth. Set aside.
Turn ice cream cake out onto a chilled serving platter. Discard plastic wrap and smooth edges with a palette knife. Pour sauce over top and decorate with cherries.

title: japanese style cheesecake
directions: Line a 20 centimeter cake pan with parchment paper.
In an oven-proof dish large enough to hold the cake pan, cover the bottom with water.
Preheat the oven to 170 degrees Celsius and add in the water covered dish.
Mix the cream cheese and milk together.
Add in 50 grams of sugar, the egg yolks, cornstarch, lemon juice, and baking powder. Mix well.
Separately, in a large bowl whisk the egg whites with a pinch of salt until soft peaks form. Then whisk in the remaining 30 grams of sugar until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold the egg yolks into the cream cheese mixture.
Pour the batter into the cake pan and introduce in the cake pan into the water-covered pan in the oven.
Bake 25 minutes. Then shut off the oven and let sit in the heat another 10 minutes.
Serve with jam or fresh berries on top.

title: risotto "campestre"
directions: Laminate fresh mushrooms.
Make a stew with butter, onion and garlic.
First add the rice and golden, then white wine and mushrooms.
When the wine evaporates, cover again the rice with vegetable broth, previously boiled.
As the broth evaporates add a new amount of broth to cover and repeat 1 more time.
When it is cooked, but still with broth, connect with butter, cherry tomatoes and spinach leaves.
Add the grated parmesan and season to taste.
If needed add more broth or water.
The risotto should be falling off the spoon. Sprinkle with more cheese and serve immediately.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, heat water, salt, lemon peel, and margarine and bring to a boil.
Add the rice and stir.
Let grains expand for a few minutes. In a small saucepan, heat milk.
When the water has almost fully evaporated, add about 1/3 of the hot milk.
Stir constantly to prevent the rice from sticking to the bottom of the pan.
Gradually add remaining milk and keep stirring.
When almost cooked, add sugar and cook for a few more minutes, stirring carefully, so that rice grains do not break.
Remove lemon peels and place in serving dish.
Let cool.
To serve, garnish with cinnamon.

title: carrot cake log
directions: Preheat oven to 150 °C
Separate the egg whites from yolks.
Whip up egg whites, when they start to foam gradually pour 80 grams of sugar, continue to beat to make them stiff.
In another salad bowl whisk the yolks and remaining 100 grams of sugar for 3/4 minutes.
Add cinnamon, raisins.
Add a large spoonful of egg white and actively mix it to make the mixture frothier before adding the rest of the whites.
Carefully lift the whites not to break them but incorporating them
Pour the mixture onto a baking sheet lined with greaseproof paper, smooth the surface with a spatula. Bake for 30 minutes.
Prepare syrup by heating 4 tablespoons of orange juice with 1 tablespoon of powdered sugar.
In a food processor bowl, pour the Philadelphia, orange juice and granulated sugar, process until smooth.
Remove cake from the oven, turn it onto a damp cloth and using a brush, brush the cake, let it cool and cover with half of the cream cheese frosting.
Roll it up gently (it is a bit more fragile than a conventional jelly roll). Place it on a plate and frost with the remaining cream cheese icing and store it in the refrigerator.
Place small chocolate carrots for decoration.

title: seafood macaroni soup
directions: Start by heating a drizzle of olive oil in a medium pot. Add the onion and garlic and saute until it is lightly browned.
Add the carrots and cabbage and let them saute for a few minutes.
Add water to approximately one inch above the vegetables.
Once the water is boiling, add the cod fillets and the chickpeas.
Adjust the seasoning to taste. If necessary, add a pinch of salt, then stir in the paprika and tomato paste and let it boil.
Add the macaroni and cook for approximately 10 minutes or to taste. If necessary, add a little water.
Place in bowls and serve as a hot soup.

title: baked rice casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.
Mix the ground beef, rice, sour cream, half the cheese, and the pickled jalapenos together in a bowl. Salt and pepper.
Place the mixture into a baking pan and sprinkle with the rest of the cheese. Bake for 15 minutes, until the cheese melts and browns slightly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
In a bowl, cream the butter and sugars. Once the mixture is fluffy and creamy, add the egg and vanilla and continue to beat. Then, add the peanut butter and mix.
In another bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, and salt. Slowly add to the butter mixture and mix well.
Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Shape the dough into 2-centimeter diameter balls and place on baking trays, separated from each other. Press down using a fork.
Bake for 9 to 12 minutes until golden brown on the edges.
Take out of the oven, let the cookies rest on the baking trays for 2 minutes, and then place on an oven rack to cool completely.

title: chicken, mushroom and corn soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine stock, water, sherry, ginger, garlic and sugar on high. Bring to boil. Simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken, mushrooms and corn. Season to taste. Simmer for another 5 minutes.
Add choy sum, onions and chili. Simmer 1 minute. Serve immediately with a drizzle of soy sauce, if desired.

title: tomato soup
directions: Combine the pepper and onion in a food processor and grind for several seconds.
Heat the olive oil in a pot, then add the ground pepper and onion and saute for approximately 8 minutes.
Add the can of tomatoes, with the juice. Season the mix with salt, add the sugar, and cook on high for approximately 30 minutes, stirring regularly.
After 30 minutes, puree the mix using a hand mixer or food processor for about 3 seconds on medium to low speed.
Add the bread and the cilantro, mint, or basil and stir well for a few seconds.

title: warm tomato and kale pasta
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions. Set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add onion; cook and stir until tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, kale, vegetable broth, lime juice, chili powder, garlic salt and crushed red pepper.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine hot pasta, tomato mixture, feta cheese and cilantro in a large serving bowl.
Toss lightly and serve.

title: mixed bean and tomato gratin
directions: Heat oil in a large pan over moderate heat.
Add onion and pepper and cook, stirring, 3 minutes, or until onion is soft. Add tomatoes and beans and cook, stirring, 5 minutes, or until mixture thickens slightly. Season with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, combine breadcrumbs, thyme and parmesan in a small bowl.
Preheat broiler to high. Transfer bean mixture to a 6 cup ovenproof dish and sprinkle with breadcrumb mixture. Cook under broiler for 1 minute, or until lightly browned.
Serve gratin sprinkled with extra thyme.

title: greek roasted chicken & tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Mix lemon juice, oil and seasonings in large bowl. Add chicken, tomatoes and olives; toss to coat well.
Arrange chicken, tomatoes and olives in single layer on foil-lined 15x10x1-inch baking pan sprayed with no stick cooking spray.
Roast 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Sprinkle with feta cheese.

title: raspberry eton mess
directions: Preheat the oven to 150 degrees Celsius.
Whip the egg whites and a pinch of salt at medium speed. Once they have hardened, add the sugar by spoonfuls. Increase the speed and whip until the sugar dissolves, for 7 to 8 minutes.
Place the egg whites in a pastry bag.
Line a baking sheet with parchment and make the meringues to the desired size.
Bake for 1 hour.
Remove from the oven and let them cool. Once cool, place in a resealable plastic bag and crush using a rolling pin.
In a bowl, crush half the raspberries and add the sugar.
Whip the cream to soft peaks.
Mix the cream and crushed raspberries. Add the rest of the raspberries and the crushed meringue and mix carefully
Serve in dessert cups or glasses.

title: mini frozen bites of white chocolate and ricotta
directions: Grate the white chocolate.
With the help of a food processor, mix the ricotta, sugar, grated coconut, orange blossom water and vanilla extract, until a homogeneous mixture is obtained .
Add the grated white chocolate, cranberries and white chocolate chips.
Whip the cream in a bowl and add it gently to the previous preparation.
Pour the obtained preparation into the mold.
Keep in the freezer for about 4 hours.
Unmold the ice log on a serving plate and garnish with a few cranberries and white chocolate chips.
You may serve it with a fruit coulis.

title: baltic white chocolate raspberry
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Roughly chop almonds and set aside.
Whisk the yolks and sugar until they turn white.
Add the ground almonds, baking powder, cornstarch, and a pinch of salt. Whisk.
Whisk the egg whites.
Stir first about 1/3 of the whites into the mixture to make it more flexible. Mix.
Then, with a spatula, gently stir in the remaining egg whites.
Add chopped almonds.
Use a soft square mold for baking. It is important that your cake is a little wider than the metal frame that you will use to raise it.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Turn out upside down on a greaseproof paper placed on a baking tray.
Place your circle or square on the cake and press to cut it.
In the bowl of the blender, mix raspberries with the sugar, 2 eggs and flour, mix.
Pour the batter onto almond base and bake for 30 minutes at 160 C.
Allow to cool and slide the cake onto a plate.
Heat the chocolate in the microwave.
Place the cereal between two sheets of parchment paper, and crush with a rolling pin.
Pour cereal in the hot chocolate, and add the Nutella.
Let cool for 5 minutes before adding to the cake.
Chocolate Mousse Layer Preparation:
Soak the gelatin in cold water.
Pour the cream in the mixer bowl and whisk until fluffy.
Pour the milk in a saucepan, and heat without boiling.
Drain the gelatin.
Pour the gelatin in hot milk, and stir until it melts completely.

Put chocolate in a bowl, pour in milk, and mix. Check chocolate temperature (35 C, you can dip your finger in and feel neither a warm nor cold sensation, it is important to get a beautiful foam, if it's too hot the cream will melt).
Add whipped cream, and stir gently. Pour into mold.
Store your cake to cool overnight with plastic wrap on the surface to protect from the odors in your refrigerator.
Pass a knife gently along the frame.
Remove the metal frame, and decorate your pie with cocoa and some Valrhona chocolate chips.

title: alyce ann's scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in medium bowl. Cut in I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!(R) Spread with pastry blender or two knives until mixture is size of very coarse crumbs. Stir in cranberries and ginger. Stir in milk with fork until mixture just holds together.

Gently knead dough on lightly floured surface with floured hands and shape into 8- or 9-inch circle, about 3/4 inch thick. Cut dough with floured knife in half crosswise, then cut each half into 4 or 5 wedges. Arrange wedges on parchment paper lined cookie sheet. Brush tops with egg and, if desired, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 17 minutes or until golden. Cool 2 minutes on wire rack. Serve warm.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a skillet, heat the olive oil, add the onion, garlic, and red pepper and saute.
Add the bacon and ground beef.
Cook until browned. Stir well.
Put the mixture in a tagine or dutch oven.
Add the canned tomatoes with juice from can.
Add cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper.
Cover the pan, and simmer for 2 hours 15 minutes.
Mix in drained kidney beans.
Cook another 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan and brown the ground beef. Add the onion, garlic, tomatoes and peppers and fry for 3 minutes. Add 1 cup water and stir in the chili con carne mix. Bring to the boil and simmer over a low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the kidney beans and sweet corn and season with salt and black pepper. Garnish with parsley and serve with warm tortillas.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
In a bowl, beat the egg and add the butter, flour, and sugar. Mix well. Knead for about 10 minutes with your hands or electric mixer.
Make around 20 balls, about 25 to 30 grams each.
Coat each ball with cinnamon.
Place on a baking sheet and press them down slightly.
Bake for 23 to 25 minutes.

title: tuna casserole/goulash
directions: Open all the cans and drain the tuna.
Combine the tuna and cream of mushroom soup in a large (microwave safe) bowl and stir.
Add all the seasonings to the tuna and cream of mushroom soup mix and stir.
Cook pasta according to the instructions on the package.
Put the tuna and cream of mushroom soup mix in the microwave for 4 minutes. Remove when done and stir.
**OPTIONAL STEP: Cook peas separately and add to the completed recipe if you so desire.
Drain the pasta and add to the tuna and cream of mushroom soup mix.
Stir until thoroughly mixed and serve!

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a saute' pan place 2 Tbsp. butter to melt.
Take onion and chop in half and place in your blender with a small amount of water to chop or in your food processor.
After chopping place this in the pan with your butter and cook until tender and sweet. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Set aside in bowl.

In a large stock pot mix in remaining butter and flour. Cook for about 3 minutes until the butter is melted and the flour is all wet. It should be thick. While whisking slowly pour in the bone broth until it is combined and no lumps remain. Do the same thing for the milk and the cream. Set on burner and let simmer for about 20 minutes on medium / low. Stir frequently and do not allow this to boil.
In small pan steam broccoli and carrots while the soup simmered. Set aside.
When the soup has simmered 20 minutes add the onion, broccoli and carrots to the stock pot. Stir to mix well and simmer another 20 to 25 minutes.
Ladle into your favorite bowl and top with shredded cheese.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat the oven to 170 degrees Celsius.
Remove the stems from the mushrooms and wash them well to remove all grit.
Place some Brie cheese in the cap of each mushroom and cover with diced ham.
Place mushrooms on a baking tray and bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top, switch the oven to broil, and then bake the mushrooms until just melty.

title: mario batali's asian barbecued shrimp
directions: Marinade/Shrimp: Place Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Creamy Balsamic Mayonnaise Dressing, lemon zest and juice, garlic and soy sauce in resealable plastic bag. Add shrimp and massage gently to mix well and refrigerate at least an hour and up to overnight.

Meanwhile make the Sauce: In a medium bowl stir together the Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Creamy Balsamic Mayonnaise Dressing, the honey, orange juice and sesame oil and let stand in the fridge for an hour.

When ready to serve, heat a broiler, a grill or a nonstick pan. Drain the shrimp well and thread them onto skewers. Place the skewers over high heat on the grill or in a pan for a minute a side and then turn and cook until just cooked through.
Pile the shrimp on a platter and drizzle with half the Sauce; sprinkle with sesame seeds and scallions and serve the rest of the Sauce in a little bowl for dipping.

title: spongata pie
directions: The filling is to be prepared the day before so the flavors are enhanced:
Chop the nuts, the almonds, the pine nuts, and the hazelnuts.
Place the honey in a small saucepan and melt it over very low heat.
Add the wine to the saucepan with the honey and bring it to a boil.
Add the chopped nuts and the raisins, previously soaked in warm water.
Add the crumbled cookies and mix all the ingredients together.
Add a pinch of nutmeg and cinnamon (you can also add black pepper and ground clove).
Once the mixture is uniform in consistency, remove it from the heat and let it cool.
Place the mixture in a bowl and refrigerate it for a day (two is even better).
Prepare the dough the next day:
Preheat the oven to 190C.
Place the flour on the work surface, add the butter and the sugar to the center and begin to knead the ingredients together.
Add a pinch of salt and the white wine.
Continue kneading until the dough is compact and uniform in consistency.
Divide the dough into two parts, one larger than the other.
Roll out the larger piece of dough and line a pie plate, which has been buttered and floured.
Place the filling prepared the day before in the pie plate, and cover with the the other piece of dough, previously rolled out.
Seal the edges together, use a toothpick to make holes in the top of the pie and brush it with some oil.
Bake the pie for approximately 30 minutes, the crust should be lightly golden.
Cool the cake completely and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: creamy turkey steaks
directions: Season the steaks with a little bit of salt, lemon juice, and garlic cloves. Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Heat a friyng pan with margarine. Fry the steaks on both sides, then remove from pan, and set aside on a serving plate.
After frying all the steaks, add a little bit more of margarine, and the mushrooms to brown.

When mushrooms are soft, add the package of cream. When the cream begins to boil, add the Port wine, and bring to a boil again. Simmer until wine almost completely evaporates. Once the mushroom sauce ready, pour on the steaks, and serve immediately.

title: stuffed tofu with arugula salad
directions: Cut each block of tofu in half to create 4 pieces, then, with a sharp knife, slice horizontally along each piece to create a pocket. Into each pocket place 2 tomatoes and a slice of mozzarella and 2-3 arugula leaves and season with salt.

Heat the oil in a large, non-stick frying pan and saute the tofu slices, turning, for about 6 mins until they are golden brown. To make the salad dressing, mix the vinegar with the honey, then add 3 tablespoons of oil from the sun dried tomatoes. Put the rest of the arugula in a bowl with the basil leaves and green onions, and dress with the vinaigrette. Season with salt and pepper. Serve a portion of salad with a slice of fried tofu.

title: goat cheese and lentil salad
directions: Place the lentils in a bowl with cold water and let it sit overnight.
Boil the lentils in a small cooking pot at medium heat for 10 minutes.
Strain them and soak with cold water.
Mix the lettuce (as much as you want), cherry tomatoes, beet, and corn in a salad bowl.
Heat the goat cheese in the microwave for 5 seconds. Add to the salad, then salt to taste.
Mix the mustard, apple vinegar, olive oil, and honey in a small bowl.
Pour the dressing over the salad and serve.

title: blueberry ice cream
directions: In a saucepan, bring the blueberries, sugar, and lemon zest to a boil.
Let simmer on low heat until the blueberries start to melt and release their juices, probably about 10 minutes.
Grind this mixture in a blender or with a hand blender until homogeneous.
Let completely cool in the refrigerator.
Once cold, add the yogurt and the whisked cream.
Place the mixture in an ice cream maker and follow the machine's instructions.
Place in the freezer to solidify.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
If you don't have an ice cream machine, place the mixture in a freezer-safe container, and beat the ice cream with a fork, every 15 minutes, for 1 1/2 hours, to prevent ice crystals from forming.

title: minute ice cream with red fruits without ice cream maker
directions: Place the fruits and the lemon juice in a bowl.
Mix with a blender until you get a thick fruit puree.
Add the yogurt and the honey, and mix 1 to 2 minutes to obtain a homogeneous ice cream. Serve immediately in bowls.
Serving option: Add 200 grams of grated cheese for a thicker version of this dessert.

title: chicken pad thai
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions; drain. Rinse under cold water; drain again and set aside.
Meanwhile, heat 2 tsp of the oil in a wok on high heat. Add egg; swirl to coat sides. Cook for 30 seconds, until set. Slice.
Heat remaining oil in wok. Stir-fry garlic, onion and chili sauce for 1 min. Add chicken; cook for 4 mins, until cooked through.

Add noodles and combined lime juice, fish sauce and palm sugar. Cook until heated through. Remove from heat. Add egg, green onions and cilantro; toss well. Sprinkle with peanuts and serve with lime wedges.

title: chocolate raspberry torte
directions: Preheat the oven at 180 degrees Celsius.
In a bowl, whisk the eggs and 90 grams of granulated sugar.
Add the cocoa powder and the flour. Stir well.
Pour the batter into a pan of 22 centimeters in diameter (either in silicone or lined with parchment paper).
Bake the cake for 30 minutes.
Let the cake cool and unmold onto a wire rack.
Start preparing the mousse by first letting the gelatin sheets soften in cold water.
Whip the cream until it turns into whipped cream.
In the mixer bowl, pour the mascarpone (keep 2 tablespoons for the gelatin ), the fromage blanc, 100 grams of granulated sugar, and the vanilla sugar.
Whisk to obtain a homogeneous mixture.
Wring the gelatin. Heat 2 tablespoons of mascarpone in the microwave to melt the gelatin in it. Mix well with a fork.
Gradually add this mixture to the mascarpone / cream cheese and sugar preaparation.
Add the whipped cream by gently lifting the mixture with a spatula.
Cut your cake in 2 pieces across the width.
Leave a first half in the bottom of a cake ring.
Cover with half of the mousse, then top with the raspberries (approximately 375 grams), and pour the remaining mousse.
Cover with the second half of the cake.
Cover the mold with cling film.
Refrigerate for at least 5 hours.
When ready to serve, place a knife inside the pastry ring to unstick.
Grate a bar of chocolate to get the decoration chips of the top and add the raspberries.

title: roast pork loin with apples
directions: Mince rosemary and sage, and mix in olive oil. Save some of the herbs for garnish.
With a knife, make cuts on the back of the pork tenderloin, and stuff with sliced garlic.
Rub the entire surface of the pork with salt, pepper, a little mayonnaise, and lemon.
Then coat the entire pork loin with the olive oil and herb mixture.
Preheat oven to 190 degrees Celsius.
Place the pork loin in a baking pan, top with the sliced onion, 1 sprig of rosemary, and sage leaves.
Add a few pieces of butter, and drizzle with a little bit of white wine.
Bake for 1 hour or until done, to taste.
20 minutes before turning off the oven, add the apples.
Before serving, garnish the pork loin with pomegranate seeds, and side with roasted young potatoes.

title: brownie
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.
Melt the chocolate in a double boiler along with the butter. Add the sugar, stir well, and remove from heat.
Gently fold in the eggs, one by one, and then stir in the flour.
