Pour the batter into a greased and floured baking pan and bake for 20 minutes, until firm to the touch.

title: chocolate orange brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large microwave safe bowl, melt butter in microwave. Stir in cocoa and orange juice.
Add sugar, orange pulp and vanilla to bowl and stir to combine.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour batter into greased 9x13 pan and bake 23-25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into middle removes cleanly. Let cool completely.
In a small microwave safe bowl, add chocolate chips, whipping cream and orange zest and microwave on HIGH for 1 minute. Whisk together until smooth.
Spread ganache evenly over top of brownies and refrigerate until set. Return brownies to refrigerator after serving.

title: homemade toritillas with spicy ground beef
directions: Mix the flour and cornmeal in a bowl with 1/2 tsp salt. Add the margarine in small flakes, then stir in 6 3/4 tbsp lukewarm water. Mix to a dough then knead on a lightly floured surface until smooth, adding a little more water if the dough is crumbly. Wrap in plastic wrap and leave to rest for 30 mins.

Meanwhile, heat half the oil in a frying pan and saute the onion, garlic and serrano pepper for 4-5 mins. Add the beef and saute over a high heat until browned all over, stirring all the time. Stir in the kidney beans, corn and salsa. Simmer for 15-20 mins, stirring occasionally until thickened.

Divide the dough into 8 balls and roll out into thin 8 inch diameter round tortillas. Use a little of the remaining oil to lightly grease a heavy-based frying pan and fry one of the tortillas, for 1-2 mins on each side until brown patchy spots appear. Repeat to make 8 tortillas in total, adding more oil as needed. Fill the tortillas with the spicy beef mixture and serve garnished with serrano peppers.

title: beef wraps with salsa verde
directions: To make the salsa verde, peel the tomatillos and score the base of each fruit with a small knife. Place in a saucepan of boiling water for 20 seconds, then cool under cold water. Remove and discard the skins. In the same boiling water, cook the whole, peeled tomatoes and chilies for 1-2 mins. Drain and place with the remaining ingredients in a blender. Pulse until smooth and season to taste.

Heat a grill pan or grill to high. Lightly spray steaks with oil and season to taste. Cook for 1 min each side, or to desired doneness. Remove from the pan and leave to rest for a minute, then slice into strips. Toss the steak in a bowl with the beans, tomatoes, pepper, cilantro and 2 tbsp of salsa verde.
Plate the beef, tortillas, remaining salsa verde, chilies and lemon separately and assemble at the table.

title: mini beef wraps with guacamole
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Heat the oil in a saucepan and brown the beef until crumbly. Season with salt and black pepper. Add the scallions, half the garlic and half the chili pepper and fry for 1 min. Add the tomatoes and simmer for 5 mins. Allow to cool.

Wrap the tortillas individually in aluminum foil and bake for 10 mins. Allow to cool slightly, unwrap and lay flat on their foil on a work surface. Top each with a lettuce leaf, some beef mixture and a sprinkling of cheese. Roll up tightly and chill for 30 mins.
Place the avocados in a blender with the lemon juice and remaining garlic and chili and puree. Season with salt. Remove the wraps from the foil and cut each into 3 pieces. Serve with the guacamole.

title: osso buco
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly coat carrots, celery and onion with oil. Heat a large frying pan over medium heat, add vegetables and garlic. Cook for 4-5 mins then transfer to a large baking dish.
Toss veal in flour then cook, in batches, until browned. Transfer to baking dish.
Whisk together tomato puree, tomatoes, stock and bay leaves. Pour over veal and vegetables in baking dish. Bake, covered, for 1 hour 30 mins, or until tender. Season.
Distribute couscous between shallow serving bowls. Top with osso buco. Garnish with lemon zest and oregano. Serve at once.

title: trattoria la palazzina’s tiramisu
directions: Add the egg whites to a bowl and whip using a whisk or electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
In another bowl, whip the heavy cream.
In a separate bowl, add the egg yolks with the sugar and mix well. Add the mascarpone and mix well.
Use a spatula to incorporate the egg yolk mixture into the beaten egg whites. Add the whipped cream by folding them together carefully to be sure they remain light and airy.
Make 6 cups espresso. If you like you may add a teaspoon of rum.
Dip the cookies into the warm coffee and place a layer of cookies in a baking dish. Add a layer of the cream, and alternate cookies and cream until the dessert is complete.
Sprinkle the top with cocoa powder.

title: baked cheesy chicken wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a baking pan with baking paper.
In a large bowl, toss chicken, sweet corn, kidney beans and half the salsa together. Divide among tortillas and roll to enclose filling.
Arrange in dish and spoon remaining salsa over. Sprinkle with cheese and drizzle with sweet chili sauce.
Bake for 10-15 mins, until cheese has melted and filling is hot. Garnish with cilantro leaves and serve with lime wedges.

title: apple cremes
directions: Place the apple cider and sugar into a pot and bring to a boil.
In a blender, add the apples and some of the cider. Blend.
Add the apples back into the cider mixture in the pot. Cook the apples down into a jam-like consistency by boiling for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove the pot from the heat and add the egg yolks at once, whisking the entire time.
Cool and serve in individual containers.

title: smoked salmon blini and stuffed eggs
directions: Whisk together milk, butter, yeast and sugar. Sift flour into a large bowl then whisk in milk mixture and egg yolk until smooth. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside in a warm place for 45 mins, or until batter has doubled in size.
Whip egg white to soft peaks then fold into batter.

Heat a large frying pan over medium heat. Lightly coat with oil. Working in batches, spoon heaped teaspoonfuls of batter into pan and cook for 1 min, until bubbles form on surface. Flip over and cook another 30 seconds, or until golden. Let cool.
For the topping, combine cream cheese, lime juice and dill. Spread over blinis. Top with salmon and chives.
For the stuffed eggs, combine egg yolks with mayonnaise and mustard powder. Add anchovies, herbs and lemon zest. Pipe into egg whites and top with a little paprika and trout roe.

title: crab corollas
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.
Cut the phyllo dough sheets into strips, then into squares.
Brush the squares with olive oil using a brush.

Using a mini-muffin or mini-cannele pan, place a square of phyllo dough in each space so that you can form a small corolla. If you cannot bake all the squares at once, keep them well packaged as the phyllo dough tends to dry quickly in the open air. Cook for 10 minutes or until small petals are golden brown.
In a medium-sized bowl, gently mix the crab meat with finely chopped chives, lemon zest, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Peel and seed the cucumber and cut it into sticks. Add the cucumber to the crab mixture and store in the refrigerator.
When serving, garnish each corolla with a little crab and serve immediately.

title: rice paper omelette rolls
directions: Heat a 7 inch nonstick skillet on medium-low heat. Brush with a little oil. Pour 2 tbsp egg into pan and tilt to make a thin omelette. Cook for 1-2 mins or until set. Transfer to a plate. Repeat with remaining egg and oil to make a total of 8 omelettes,

For each roll, dip 1 rice paper sheet into a bowl of hot water to soften. Place on a clean work surface. Top with an omelette, then 1/8 each of the carrot, cucumber, spinach, red pepper and cilantro. Fold in 2 opposite sides then roll up tightly to enclose. Serve with plum sauce.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut the onion into small cubes and its stem into thin slices.
Finely chop the coriander.
Place the avocado In a small bowl and mash with a fork. Pour in the lemon juice and mix well. Finally, add the remaining ingredients, and mix well.
Serve with tacos or for a change, on toasted baguette slices.

title: kasetorte cheesecake
directions: Place the flour, cold butter, milk, baking powder, 2 egg yolks, 80 grams of sugar, a pinch of salt, and the zest from 1 lemon into a bowl and knead until the dough is smooth and uniform.
Cover the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Butter and flour a 24 centimeter springform pan.
Roll out the dough, place it in the pan, covering the sides as well.
Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Add the egg whites to a bowl and beat until stiff peaks form.
Add the remaining egg yolks with the sugar into another bowl and mix well.
Add the cheese, melted butter, pudding mix, and bourbon. Mix well.
Add the beaten egg whites, folding them in carefully.
Pour the mixture into the cake pan.
Bake for approximately 60 minutes.
Cool the cake in the oven, removing it from the pan once it has cooled completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, add the melted chocolate, slice and serve.

title: chef rudolph's club sandwich
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, ketchup, chopped parsley, whiskey, salt, and freshly ground pepper thoroughly. Set aside.
Toast the six slices of whole wheat bread.
Generously spread the dressing on each slice of toasted bread.

On top of the first slice of toast, place 6 cucumber slices and some arugula leaves. Place another slice of toast on top with the dressing side up. Add 6 tomato slices, a bit more arugula leaves, and two slices of chicken breast. Finish the sandwich with a third slice of toast, but this time with the dressing side down.
Press it down with the palm of your hand. Insert toothpicks to make cutting the sandwiches easier.

title: cuban sandwich
directions: Grease a skillet with cooking spray and preheat on medium flame.
Cut open the baguette and spread the mayonnaise on the lower half.
Fill with the pork meat, turkey breast, cheddar cheese, pickles, and mustard, and cover it with the upper half of the baguette.
Place the sandwich on the skillet and put some weight on it, like a baking stone.
Once the bread toasts, turn the sandwich upside down.
When both sides are toasted, remove the sandwich from the skillet, cut in half, and serve.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Attach Fresh Prep Slicer/Shredder Attachment to KitchenAid(R) Stand Mixer, and attach slicing
blade. Position large bowl under attachment to catch cucumber slices. Fill feed tube with
cucumber sections. Turn stand mixer to speed 6 and process. Repeat with remaining cucumber
sections. Set aside until ready to use.

In small bowl, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic, kalamata olives and Italian parsley. Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese olive spread over each baguette slice. Top with 3 cucumber slices. Serve immediately.

title: thai chicken soup
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan and fry the garlic, chili and ginger for 2 mins. Add the stock and coconut milk and bring to a low boil. Add chicken and cook for 15 mins, or until chicken is cooked through. Add lime juice and season to taste.
Ladle into bowls and top with bean sprouts and cilantro. Serve garnished with lime slices.

title: roast beef sandwich
directions: Spread 1 1/2 tbsp tartar sauce on 1 slice of bread and top with the lettuce, cucumber, tomato and beef. Top with the remaining tartar sauce and watercress. Place the second slice of bread on top.

title: spaghetti tortilla
directions: Whisk the eggs and egg yolk, and season with salt, pepper, and a pinch of garlic powder.
Add the diced pepper, chopped parsley, and Parmesan cheese, mix well.
Add pasta to the egg mixture, and mix until the pasta is well coated.
In a skillet, saute the onion until translucent.
Add the pasta egg mixture, and cook until golden on both sides.
Serve with a salad.

title: papaya salsa
directions: Peel and seed the papaya and cut it into 1/4-inch dice. Place in a medium-size bowl. Gently fold the tomatoes, jalapeno, red onion, cilantro and lime zest into the papaya. Toss in the lime juice. Refrigerate, covered, until ready to use, no longer than 4 hours.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Blend all ingredients besides 1/2 of the banana
Lightly spray a frying pan or skillet with cooking spray and put on a medium heat
Pour the batter in a circle and cook for 2-3 minutes until light brown
Flip and cook other side for 2-3 minutes
Remove from pan and top with other half of banana and any other toppings of choice

title: hot dog muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 190C.
Combine the flour in a bowl with the baking powder, parmesan cheese, salt, and ground pepper.
Beat the eggs lightly in another bowl and add the melted butter and the milk.
Add the two mixtures and beat quickly just enough to combine.
Add the hot dog slices and the Emmental cheese, and stir.
Spoon the batter into the muffin liners and bake for approximately 25 minutes, until lightly golden.
Remove the muffins from the oven and serve warm.

title: stewed tomato sauce
directions: Grill the tomatoes and the pepper. Once they are completely roasted, liquefy them in a blender with the garlic and salt.
Place a pot on the stove and add some cooking oil. Saute the onion and then pour in the sauce.
Once the sauce comes to a boil, serve it with quesadillas, beans, or for making chilaquiles.

title: salted salmon danish recipe
directions: Prepare the marinade by mixing salt, water, and peppercorns.
Soak the salmon in the marinade for 3 hours.
Remove the salmon, and wipe with paper towel.
Preheat oven to 90 degrees Celsius.
Coat the salmon with a thin film of canola oil, pepper, and bake for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Wash the fennel, slice thinly with a mandolin.
Wash the cucumber, and cut out small balls with a melon baller.
Set aside.
Mix the dill and cream cheese in order to get a green sauce, season with salt and pepper.
Cut the slice of rye bread into cubes.
In a skillet melt the butter, add the bread cubes, fry until browned.
Place the salmon in a baking dish, decorate with the sliced fennel, cucumber balls, pea shoots, and bread cubes.
Add some dill sauce, and possibly lemon.
Serve with new potatoes, just boiled.

title: spiced red lentil soup
directions: Bring 3 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan. Drain the lentils and add to the pan along with the turmeric and carrots. Reduce the heat to low; cover and simmer for 15 mins, adding more water if necessary.
Add the tomatoes, onion, ginger and spices. Simmer for 15 mins. Season with salt and ladle into bowls.

title: red lentil soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan on medium-high heat. Saute onions and garlic for 5 mins. Add carrots and thyme and saute for 2 mins. Stir in lentils and season with salt, pepper and paprika. Pour in stock. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low. Simmer, covered, for about 25 mins.

Melt butter with the curry powder in a small skillet. Cook the diced bread 2 mins until golden. Remove from pan and set aside. Stir mint into the yogurt in a small bowl. Season with salt, pepper, cumin and lemon juice.
Serve soup in bowls sprinkled with sesame seeds and a dollop of minty yogurt. Garnish with croutons and green onions.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Wrap the potatoes in foil and place on a baking pan. Bake for about 1 hour until tender. Cut an X in top of each potato, then squeeze open. Stuffing with filling.

For the spinach filling, blanch the spinach in boiling salted water for 2 mins. Drain well, squeezing spinach dry. Melt the butter in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Saute the onion until tender. Add the spinach, white pepper, nutmeg and season to taste. Cook until heated through. Fill 4 potatoes with the spinach mixture. Top with 1 tbsp of creme fraiche, a few shrimp and dill leaves.

For the scrambled egg filling, fry the bacon in a medium skillet until crisp. Remove from the pan. Drain on paper towels then crumble. Beat the eggs and season to taste. Pour the eggs into the pan and scramble in the hot bacon fat. Fill 4 potatoes with scrambled eggs. Top with the bacon and chives.
For the ham filling, mix the mayonnaise, mustard and curry powder and season to taste. Stir in the ham and gherkin slices. Fill 4 potatoes with ham mixture and garnish with parsley.

For the cottage cheese filling, mix the cottage cheese and cream and season to taste. Stir in the green onions. Fill the last 4 potatoes with cottage cheese filling and garnish with the cherry tomatoes.

title: savory herb spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!(R) Spread in medium bowl.

Combine mixture with Spread in medium bowl. Serve, if desired, with grilled bread or use as a dressing on any sandwich. Try a spoonful on top of grilled fish, roasted chicken or a bowl of pasta just before serving.

title: strawberry kiwi fizz
directions: 1. In a food processor or blender process sugar until superfine. Combine with strawberries and pulse until coarsely chopped. Mix yogurt with lemon juice and pour gradually into the machine through the feed tube or top of blender. Process until smooth and creamy.
2. Using an ice cream scoop, divide strawberry frozen yogurt between four glasses. Add sparkling water. Garnish with kiwi slice .

title: marinated chicken with potato salad
directions: Mix the chipotle pepper, lemon juice, brine, garlic powder, and a pinch of salt using a food processor. Add the mixture to a large bowl.
Place the chicken breasts in the bowl and marinate for 30 minutes.
Heat a skillet with cooking spray on medium heat, grill the chicken breasts until they are golden brown on each side, and turn off the stove. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Boil the potatoes in a large cooking pot at high heat until they soften. Drain, and let them cool off completely.
Mix the potatoes, celery, eggs, pickles, and onions in a large salad bowl.
Mix the mayonnaise, mustard, brine, and a pinch of salt, and black pepper in a small bowl. Add this dressing to the salad bowl and mix.
Cover the salad bowl with plastic film and let it sit in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
Remove the salad bowl and chicken breasts from the refrigerator and serve.

title: chicken satay
directions: Soak the kebab sticks in water so they do not burn during cooking.
In a bowl, mix together the vegetable oil, sesame oil, soy sauce, and lemon juice. Add the chicken and stir well. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator as long as possible.
Heat up the 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil in a skillet and add the onion. Saute until softened then add the garlic stirring everything together.
Add in the peanut butter, water, and lemon or lime juice. Simmer on low heat a few minutes constantly stirring until the consistency of heavy cream. If too thick, add a bit more water.
Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Spear the marinated chicken onto the kebab sticks.
Grill or cook under the oven's broiler for 15 minutes turning frequently.
Serve with the satay sauce sprinkled with cayenne pepper.

title: homemade granola
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit.
In a large bowl, mix oats, rice, and almonds.
In a small saucepan heat the mixture of water, honey, and oil.
When hot (not boiling), pour it on cereals.
Spread the cereal on one or two baking sheets and bake for about 20 minutes, turning the mixture from time to time: it is ready when the granola is golden. Once cooled, add the chocolate.
Store the granola in an airtight container to keep crisp.

title: pancakes
directions: In a bowl, mix the sugar, flour, and baking powder. Make a well in the center and add the eggs one by one. Then gradually add the milk, then the melted butter, and then the salt. Whisk until the batter is smooth. Let stand 30 minutes.

Pour small heaps of the batter onto an oiled griddle, make two by two. When the pancakes begin to form small holes on the surface, you can turn them over. When the second side is golden brown, the pancakes are cooked.
Traditionally served with maple syrup, but a small container of blueberries can also be added to the dough (after the pause time, just before cooking) .

title: baked fish & chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Coat 2 large baking sheets with cooking spray.
Place potato wedges on one baking sheet and lightly coat with cooking spray; season to taste with salt and pepper. Bake until golden brown and tender, about 45 minutes.
Whisk milk and mustard together in a shallow dish. Place bread crumbs in another shallow dish and put flour in a third shallow dish.
Season both sides of fish with salt and pepper. Place fish in flour and turn to coat. Place fish in milk mixture and turn to coat. Place fish in bread crumbs and turn to coat.

Transfer fish to second prepared baking sheet and lightly coat with cooking spray. Bake fish until fork-tender, about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve fish and potato wedges with vinegar on the side. Yields 1 fillet, 4 potato wedges and 1 tablespoon of vinegar per serving.

NOTE: Give fish and chips a Creole accent by serving it with remoulade sauce instead of vinegar. Here's a quick, light version of the Louisiana classic: Combine 1/3 cup of fat-free mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons of sweet pickles, 1 tablespoon of mustard and a dash of hot red pepper sauce. Makes eight 1 tablespoon servings.

title: yorkshire salad
directions: Coarsely chop the onion and the cucumber put into a medium sized bowl and sprinkle with the sugar, then cover with vinegar and leave for a few days, will keep for a few weeks, if there is any left.
Serve on Yorkshire puddings or suet dumplings.

title: vanilla  almond hearts
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
In a medium bowl combine flour, butter, sugar, egg, almonds, orange zest and vanilla.
Mix the ingredients with your fingertips to get a ball of dough. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Place dough in cookie press. Form desired shapes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8-10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.

title: vanilla french toast
directions: Using a fork, whisk eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla in a large, shallow dish.
Melt half the butter in a large frying pan. Dip 2 slices of bread into egg mixture, turning to coat both sides. Let excess egg drain. Cook over medium heat for 2 mins each side or until golden brown.
Transfer to a warm plate and cover loosely with foil to keep warm. Repeat with remaining butter, bread and egg mixture. Serve immediately with strawberries, maple syrup and cream.

title: egg curry
directions: Heat oil in a pan; when hot, add all the dry seasoning ingredients, chilies, ginger and curry leaves.
Saute for few seconds, then add onions and fry until they turn translucent. Add salt and mix well.
Now add eggs and toss until they are well coated and covered. Allow to cook on low flame for about 4-5 minutes.
Taste, adjust salt and seasonings accordingly, and remove from heat.

title: spicy potatoes
directions: Wash the potatoes and cut in half lengthwise. Cut into wedges.
Boil water in a saucepan and add the potatoes. Cook for 5 minutes. Drain and let cool.
Mix the oregano, thyme, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika with the flour. Coat the potatoes with the spice mixture.
Spread the potatoes out onto a baking sheet and drizzle with oil. Bake until tender and crunchy.

title: chicken parmesan pasta toss
directions: Heat Pasta Sauce in 2-quart saucepan.
Combine hot Sauce, pasta, chicken and 1 cup cheese in large serving bowl. Top with remaining 1 cup cheese and serve immediately.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a KitchenAid(R) Skillet, saute the bacon and sausage in olive oil over medium heat, about 2-3 minutes, on a KitchenAid(R) Electric Convection Slide-In Range. Add in the peppers, mushrooms, and onions and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until tender. Toss in the spinach and cook until wilted. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Remove from heat.

Lightly spray a medium casserole dish with cooking spray. Line the bottom of the dish with the slices of bread. Preheat your KitchenAid(R) Convection Microwave oven using the Vegetable Casserole Bake option at 1.5 quart.

In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, and 1 cup cheddar cheese that was shredded in the KitchenAid(R) Pro Line(R) Series Food Processor. Add the cooked vegetables to the bowl and mix to combine. Pour the mixture over the bread in the casserole dish. Top with the remaining shredded cheese.
Place the dish in the heated Microwave and bake for 40-45 minutes, or until the egg is cooked and a skewer inserted comes out almost clean.
Serve immediately.

title: penny cap mushroom risotto
directions: Soak the mushrooms for a few hours if they are dehydrated. If so, save the water the mushrooms were soaked in. If the mushrooms are fresh there is no need to hydrate.
Finely chop the onion and saute over low heat until lightly golden. Add the mushrooms and salt as needed, continue to cook for a few minutes.
Separately, heat the broth, adding the water where the dehydrated mushrooms were soaked in.
Add the rice to the mushrooms, along with the wine. Once the alcohol has evaporated, slowly add the broth and constantly stir the rice to loosen the starch for a creamy texture.
Preheat the oven to 180C.
Sprinkle grated parmesan cheese on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Place in the oven for a few minutes, being careful not to burn. Let the cheese cool and serve with the cream soup.

title: green rice
directions: Boil 1 cup of water. Remove from heat and add the rice. Set aside for 3 minutes, drain, and wash until the water comes off clear.

Spritz a pan with cooking spray and saute the rice until it changes in color. Add 1 1/2 cups water and the bouillon and stir. Lower the heat, cover the pan, and cook for 15 minutes, until the rice is cooked. Remove the rice from the heat and let cool.
Defrost the peas. Mix with the rice, bell pepper, poblano, and scallions. Add salt and pepper and serve.

title: ginger wonton soup
directions: Cook pork in small nonstick skillet over medium-high heat 4 minutes or until no longer pink. Cool slightly; stir in ricotta cheese, cilantro, black pepper and 5-spice powder.

Place 1 teaspoon filling in center of each wonton skin. Fold top corner of wonton over filling. Lightly brush remaining corners with water. Fold left and right corners over filling. Tightly roll filled end toward remaining corner in jelly-roll fashion. Moisten edges with water to seal. Cover and set aside.

Heat oil in large saucepan. Add bell pepper and ginger; cook 1 minute. Add chicken broth and soy sauce; bring to a boil. Add pea pods, baby corn and wontons. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 4 to 5 minutes or until wontons are tender. Sprinkle with onions.

title: peanut pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Grease and flour a pie pan.
In a bowl, add the flour, sugar, butter, and milk. Beat with a spoon or an electric mixer.
Spread the dough in an even layer in the pie pan and bake for about 15 minutes.
To prepare the topping, bring the sugar, butter, and milk to a boil in a small saucepan. Lower the temperature and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the peanuts and boil for an additional 2 or 3 minutes.
Place the topping on top of the dough and bake for another 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pickled eggs in pickled beet juice
directions: Select small, young beets. Wash. Leave 3 inches of tops on and roots.
Cook until skins slip easily (about 15 minutes).
Pack beets into jars within 1/2 inch of top. Pour boiling liquid syrup over beets to within 1/2 inch of top of jar. Process for 30 minutes in boiling water bath.

After the beets have had time to "cure" (about 2 months), we then eat about 1/2 of the beets out of a quart jar, drop hard- boiled eggs into the pickled beet juice, and put into the refrigerator for about 2 weeks. By then, the beet color will have penetrated into the whites of the eggs nearly to the yolk area. Of course, a much simpler way would be simply to buy a large jar of pickled beets, eat about 1/2, and drop in hard- boiled eggs; then, refrigerate and leave for a couple of weeks until the beet juice has penetrated.

title: spicy chicken with spaghetti
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients in a small bowl and stir.
Preheat Oven 350 degrees:
Place chicken in a baking pan and rub with the spice rub.
Bake for 30 35 minutes, or until juices run clear.
Veggies for the Spaghetti:
Prepare the spaghetti as directed while preparing the veggies.
Heat a large frying pan with the olive oil. Add the mushrooms and saute until the mushrooms get a little golden.
Add the sliced onion and garlic. Continue to saute for another minute or two.
Drain the spaghetti and add to the veggie pan. Slice the chicken and top the spaghetti with the chicken.
Drizzle a little olive oil and add the lemon juice and toss.

title: fried shrimp and asparagus salad
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Cut off asparagus tips (about 1 centimeters), leaving about 7 centimeters of asparagus, wash the asparagus.
Cut the remaining stalks into thick slices.
Fry the cut stems in 1 tablespoon of olive oil.
Add salt and pepper, and cook over high heat, stirring often, for 7 to 8 minutes so they stay slightly crunchy.
Set aside on a plate.
Add another tablespoon of olive oil to the frying pan, and cook the prawns.
Add the asparagus slices to the pan.
Mix gently.
Place the asparagus spears on a baking sheet.
Lightly oil the asparagus and bake for 8 to 10 minutes so they become slightly crunchy.
Prepare the vinaigrette by mixing the juice of 1/2 orange with an equal amount of olive oil.
Season with salt and pepper. If you want you can add a little vinegar.
In each plate, place some arugula leaves and pour dressing on it.
Arrange the asparagus on top and then add the dill, the young shoots. Add some thinly sliced radishes .
Pepper and drizzle with vinaigrette.

title: goat cheese and quinoa salad
directions: Combine quinoa and 3 cups water in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil on high heat. Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, 15 mins, or until grains are tender. Let stand 5 mins. Fluff with a fork and transfer to a large bowl.
Combine nuts in a shallow bowl. Roll heaping teaspoonfuls of cheese into flattened patties. Coat in nuts. Refrigerate until firm.
For the dressing, whisk all ingredients in a small bowl. Season to taste.
Add arugula, beans, tomatoes, cucumber and currants to quinoa; toss to combine.
Heat oil in a medium skillet on medium heat. Coat goat cheese patties a few seconds each side, until golden. Drain on paper towels. Add to salad. Top with sprouts, mint and a drizzle of dressing.

title: fresh diet pasta
directions: Cook the spaghetti in salted water, drain, and set aside.
Drain the tuna, and place in a bowl.
Add the garlic, onion, peppers, chopped coriander, and mix.
Add the tomatoes, sprinkle with a little olive oil. Mix well.
Add the spaghetti, and mix evenly.

title: decadent chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly oil 12-inch round cake panand dust with flour.
Addsugar and butter to Bowl ofKitchenAid(R) Artisan Stand Mixer. Attach Bowl and Flat Beater to Mixer. Turn to Speed 3 and beat 4 minutes or until well blended.
Continuing on Speed 3, add eggs and egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each until light and fluffy. Mix in vanilla.

Combine flour, cocoa powder, salt and baking powder in separate bowl. Alternately add buttermilk and flour mixture to egg mixture in three additions, mixing on Speed 2 until just incorporated. Stop Mixer; scrape side and bottom of Bowl. Add chocolate chips. Turn to Speed 2 and mix 1 minute. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.Invert cake onto wire rack; remove pan. Cool 30 minutes.Refrigerate 1 hour.

Cut cake into 3 layers, each about 1-1/2 incheshigh.Brush each cake layer with maple syrup. Stack cake layers on serving plate, filling with some of the buttercream. Spread remaining buttercream on top and side of cake for a rustic look.

For the Espresso Buttercream: Add sugar, butter and cocoa to Bowl of KitchenAid(R) Artisan Stand Mixer. Attach Bowl and Flat Beater to Mixer. Turn to Speed 3 and mix until smooth and well blended. Stop and scrape bowl.Turn to Speed 4 and slowly drizzle in cream and milk; mix until well blended. Stop and scrape bowl. Add vanilla and espresso powder; mix until well blended.

title: creamy baked pork chops
directions: Can be made either in oven or in electric skillet. For skillet; brown chops on both sides, pour off drippings. Add soup and water. Cover and bake for about 45 minutes or until tender.
For oven: Place chops in baking dish. Cover with soup. Add water and bake until tender. The juice may then be thickened for gravy.

title: fat tuesday express buttermilk waffles (without rest periods)
directions: Preheat the waffle maker.
In a bowl, mix butter, sugar, vanilla sugar, and a pinch of salt.
Add eggs. Add flour and baking powder.
Add buttermilk gradually to obtain a homogeneous paste.
Lightly butter waffle maker hot plates with a brush.
Cook waffles until nicely browned...

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Heat a waffle iron.
Beat the margarine, sugar, vanilla, and egg yolks until frothy.
Separately, mix the flour, yeast, and milk. Add a small amount of chocolate sprinkles and cinnamon to taste.
Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture.
Separately, beat the egg whites to soft peaks. Fold into the batter.
Pour the batter into the waffle iron and cook.
Serve warm.

title: waffles
directions: Melt the butter and let it cool.
In a bowl, whisk the eggs, then add the milk alternating with the flour.
Add the milk and flour gradually to a smooth mixture.
Then add the yeast, sugar, a pinch of salt, and cooled butter.
If possible, let the batter stand for 1 hour
Cover with a clean cloth or a lid.
Heat your waffle iron. Use a ladle to pour in the batter.

title: basic waffles
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, and salt together.
Combine the eggs, butter, and milk in a separate bowl.
Add the liquid mixture to the dry mixture, stirring to combine.
Follow the instructions on your waffle maker to make waffles.

title: grilled pork chops with watercress
directions: In a bowl, place the watercress and endive cut into thin slices. Season with salt, and add the cashews last.

For the sauce, whisk the mustard in a bowl, and add the olive oil little by little stirring constantly until the sauce gets creamy. Season with ground oregano and salt. Add lime zest, and finally the chives.
Serve on top of grilled pork chops with coarse salt, and two warm brown bread buns.

title: baked quark cheese in bed of bread and roasted vegetables with salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 160 degrees Celsius.
Line a dish with the stale bread.
Blanch the asparagus in boiling water just to soften them.
In a pan, saute the garlic, zucchini, and eggplant until golden brown.
Place the sauted vegetables on a paper towel to drain the excess grease.
Place some salmon inside the cored tomato.
Place the quark cheese and tomato in the middle of the bread-lined dish. Season with salt and oregano.
Garnish with grated cheese and asparagus.
Arrange the zucchini, apple, eggplant, and peppers around tomato and quark cheese.
Place strips of smoked salmon on top, to taste.
Drizzle with olive oil and honey, and sprinkle with more oregano.
Bake just until crispy.

title: light chocolate mousse made from egg whites
directions: Melt the chocolate and keep it at a temperature of 30 ° C.
Meanwhile, mix the egg whites with the lemon juice. Whisk the egg white mixture to form stiff peaks.
Add the melted chocolate to the egg whites mixture and mix.
Put it in the refrigerator for at least 8 hours before serving.

title: valley eggplant parmigianino
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
In a bowl, combine the ricotta cheese together with the seasoning mix, and eggs, and stir until well blended.

Brush two baking sheets with one tablespoon of the oil. Arrange the eggplant slices in a single layer on each baking sheet and bake about 20 minutes or until the eggplant is fork tender. Remove the eggplant form the oven and let cool slightly.

Brush a 13x9x2-inch baking dish with olive oil. Layer half the eggplant in the dish and spread with half of the ricotta mixture. Sprinkle half the bread crumbs over the ricotta. Repeat with the remaining eggplant and ricotta mixture. Pour the tomato sauce over the ricotta and top with the mozzarella and remaining bread crumbs. Bake until the cheese has browned and is bubbly about 30 minutes.
Remove from the oven and let stand for 5 minutes. Sprnkle with the parsley and serve immediately.

title: rice in a pressure cooker
directions: Put water to warm until it starts to boil (kettle).
In the pressure cooker, put the chopped garlic and the chopped onion and bay leaves.
Sprinkle with olive oil generously.
Light the fire and let it brown.
Add the rice and fry.
When the rice starts to get translucent, add a little boiling water to release the bottom of the pot.
Add the remaining water and season it with salt.
Stirring and closing the pressure cooker.
When it starts boiling ("whistling") lower the heat to low and let cook for 5 minutes (if you have a lot of rice, for more than 6 people, increase to 7 minutes).
At the end of that time, turn off the heat and wait 2 minutes to remove the steam.
It's ready to serve.

title: red fruit crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.
Rinse and cut strawberries in half. Mix them in a bowl with the raspberries and with about a tablespoon of sugar (to taste).
In another bowl, prepare the crumble topping: crumble the biscuits and add the butter previously cut into pieces. Mix with your fingers until obtaining a sandy texture.
Divide the fruit into four ramekins. Cover the fruit completly with the crumble paste. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: almond cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
In a bowl, mix the flour, sugar, eggs, baking powder, vanilla, orange zest, and a pinch of salt. Knead until a smooth and elastic dough forms.
Add the almonds, and work into the dough until thoroughly incorporated. Add a teaspoon of milk if the dough appears too dry.
Shape into 3 long rolls, place on a well greased, parchment paper-lined baking sheet, and brush with lightly beaten egg yolk.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from the oven, leave to cool, and cut diagonally to a thickness of 1 centimeters.
Lower the oven heat to in the oven at 150 C.
Allow to cool, then return to the baking sheet and bake for 5 minutes.
Allow to rest in a cool, dry place before serving.
Store in a sealed container.

title: tomato and chili spaghetti pasta
directions: Blend the chipotle chilies and place in a glass container. Set aside 1 tablespoon for the sauce. The remainder can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 1 month and used a little at a time.
Heat a drizzle of oil in a heavy-bottomed pan. Add the garlic, stir well, and then add the tomatoes, chipotle chilies, sugar, and vinegar.
Season with salt, and break up the the tomatoes with a wooden spoon.
Cook on low for 20 minutes until the sauce thickens.
When the sauce is ready, set aside, and cook the pasta in a pot of salted water for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve the pasta covered with sauce and sprinkled with oregano and black pepper.

title: apple rhubarb pies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a large baking tray with parchment paper.
Melt butter over medium heat. Add sugar, apples, rhubarb, lemon juice and vanilla bean seeds. Simmer, covered, for 8-10 mins, until just tender. Set aside to cool.

Cut out 16 - 4 inch fluted discs from pie dough. Place 8 discs on prepared tray. Distribute 1 tsp ground almonds over center of each, leaving a 1/3 inch border. Top with compote. Brush edges with egg.

Cut an 1/8 inch circle from center of remaining pastry discs. Cover compote with discs, pressing edges to seal. Brush with remaining egg and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Bake for 15-20 mins, until golden and crisp. Serve with custard.

title: fresh fruit punch
directions: Combine the sugar and water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the syrup is clear. Set aside to cool.
Combine the syrup, wine, and sparkling water and stir well. Add the remaining fruit and serve cold.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350
Combine all ingredients

title: sirloin steaks with potato gratin
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Heat 1 tbsp of the oil in a small saucepan on medium heat. Saute the onion for 2-3 mins, until softened. Add the cream and season with salt and a pinch of nutmeg. Bring to a simmer.
Arrange the potato slices in an 8-inch square baking dish. Pour the cream mixture over the top. Bake for 40 mins, until golden.

Season the steaks with salt and black pepper. Heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in a large skillet on high heat. Cook the steaks for 3-4 mins on each side. Transfer to a serving platter. Cover with foil and let stand for 5 mins. Add the tomatoes to the skillet and saute on medium heat for 1 min. Season with salt and black pepper.
Arrange the steaks and potato gratin on serving plates. Top with the tomatoes and arugula.

title: piri-piri chicken
directions: Place the cilantro, ginger, scallions, garlic, salsa, olive oil, lemon rind, and juice into the blender or food processor. Salt and pepper to taste and blend until smooth.
Place the chicken legs into a glass or plastic container and pour the marinade over them. Turn well to coat and let marinate for at least 6 hours.
Grill the chicken on medium-high until well-cooked and golden brown, approximately 20-25 minutes.

title: spicy turkey and mango salad
directions: Place the pepper in a large bowl with mango, onion, chili, pumpkin seeds and olive oil. Mix well. Season to taste with salt.
Divide the turkey between four plates. Scatter the mango mix over the plates. Drizzle with the chili sauce. Garnish with the cilantro (if using).

title: gluten free peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. With an electric mixer, cream the peanut butter, egg, salt and sugar, then mix in baking soda. Form about 24 balls from the batter. Place the dough balls on 2 baking sheets lined with parchment paper. Press the top of each ball twice with a fork (once vertically, once horizontally) to create a diamond pattern on the cookies.
Bake each sheet of cookies one at a time for about 10 minutes each. Remove and allow to cool.

title: apple pie with custard cream
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Spread dough in the pie mold, prick the bottom with a fork. Set aside.
Reserve.
Prepare the cream for the filling.
(I used the Thermomix machine, at the link of the original recipe you can view how it is done in the traditional fashion).

Place all ingredients in the cup of the cream and beat for a few seconds in speed 4. Then program 7 min., Temp. 90 speed 4. While the cream is cooking, peel the apples and place the well distributed slices over the puff pastry. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.

Place the cream filling over the apples and distribute the flaked almonds over it , sprinkling with brown sugar and cinnamon. Bake for about 25 minutes until the pastry is golden brown. Remove and let it cool.

title: apple pie rustica
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Place pie crust on a rimless baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Dust a rolling pin and parchment paper with flour and roll pastry to a rough 13" circle.

Place pie filling in center of pastry, leaving a 2" border all around. Grate 1 tsp. of lemon peel; squeeze 2 tsp. of lemon juice from the lemon. Sprinkle both over pie filling. Scatter butter over top.

Fold pastry back over pie filling to make an uneven edge of 11/2 inches, leaving center of pie filling exposed. Sprinkle sugar over pastry border. Bake 20 minutes until the filling is bubbly and the pastry is golden brown. Cool slightly. Serve with ice cream if desired.
Suggestion:
Use round cookie cutter for small individual rustic apple pies.

title: vintage lemon strawberry ice box cake
directions: Fold in 1 jar Strawberry Fruit Toppers and vanilla extract into 3 cups whipped topping.

Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with plastic wrap. Arrange 10 cookies, top side down on bottom of pan. Spread cookies with half of the strawberry mixture. Line edges of pan with 16 cookies, top side out. Top strawberry mixture with another 10 cookies, top side down. Spread cookies with remaining strawberry rmixture then top with remaining cookies, top side down. Press down slightly to push cookies into cream layers.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 8 hours or up to 24 hours.*
Turn cake upside down onto serving platter.
Blend 1 cup Strawberry Fruit Toppers with remaining 2 cups whipped topping and lemon peel. Frost cake on all sides and top.
Garnish with remaining Strawberry Fruit Toppers and sprinkle with nuts.
*Freeze a half hour before serving to make slicing the cake easier.

title: cookies & ice cream cupcakes
directions: Line 6-cup muffin pan with paper liners. Place 1 OREO(R) Cookie into each liner.
Evenly scoop Breyers(R) BLASTS! OREO(R) Cookies & Cream Frozen Dairy Dessert into each cup. Garnish with fruit. Freeze 2 hours or until ready to serve.

title: homemade ice cream bonbons
directions: Arrange cookies on wire rack placed on aluminum-foil-lined jelly roll pan; freeze 20 minutes.
Scoop Breyers(R) Vanilla, Chocolate, Strawberry Ice Cream with 1-1/2-inch ice cream scoop directly onto cookies; freeze at least 1 hour on rack.

Microwave chocolate at HIGH 1 minute or until almost melted. Let stand 1 minute; stir until smooth. Stir in I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!(R) until Spread is melted. Working quickly, spoon about 1 tablespoon warm chocolate mixture over each bonbon, almost completely covering ice cream and cookie. Freeze 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: pineapple ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, including firm jello.
Mix well.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Sift the flour and cocoa powder into a bowl.
Add the sugar and butter, and hand mix to a crumbly dough.
Add the whisked egg, a pinch of salt, and the orange juice. Stir well.
Cover with plastic wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Shape small balls, and space them out on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake for about 10 minutes. Remove from oven, let cool, and sprinkle with a little more powdered sugar.

title: giant chocolate-hazelnut shortbread cookies.
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Quickly toast the nuts for about 8-10 minutes and let them cool before using.
With an electric mixer, beat the butter and the sugar for 2 minutes until creamy.
Add vanilla, flour, cornstarch and salt. Stir until smooth.
Transfer the dough to a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and gently press it to form a disc of 20 cm wide.
Top with hazelnuts and chocolate chips lightly pressing on the dough.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let it cool slightly before cutting the shortbread in pieces.
Enjoy at room temperature or warm.

title: spicy tofu with lemongrass stir-fry
directions: Combine tofu, lemongrass, ginger, chile paste, lime juice, and rice wine in a small bowl and toss. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes. Mix coconut milk, broth, soy sauce, and sesame oil in a bowl; set aside. Coat a large saute pan with canola oil and set over medium-high heat. Add tofu and saute, stirring, for 2 or 3 minutes. Add carrots, mushrooms, and broccoli and saute, stirring, for another 2 or 3 minutes. Stir in coconut milk mixture and onions and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. (If using shrimp, toss in last, just long enough to heat.) Combine rice, broth, and bay leaf in saucepan over medium heat and simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until rice absorbs all liquid. Remove from heat. Discard bay leaf. Place equal portions of cooked brown rice on each plate and top with stir-fry.

title: good for you chicken broccoli bake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350*.
Coat the bottom of a baker with olive oil (about 2 tablespoons). Place the chicken inside and spice to taste.
Cover with foil and bake 20-30 minutes. Uncover and bake an extra 10 minutes.
(Chicken should be cooked through but still tender.)
While chicken is cooking, dice the onion and place in pot with broccoli and 1/4 cup of water. Cover and simmer until broccoli is dark green but still firm and onion is not yet opaque.
Drain and set aside.
(Broccoli/Onion should still be warm for next step.)
Remove chicken from baker and dice into bite-sized chunks. Drain baker and place chicken back inside.
Cover chicken with soup, cheese, breadcrumbs and broccoli/onion. Mix well and press down.
Top with more spices and a sprinkling of breadcrumbs.
(These spices give the dish a real kick and are good for you too!)
Cover with foil and bake for 15-20 minutes. Uncover and brown for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: curried carrot creme brulee
directions: Cut the carrots into pieces. Place them in a pan with a little salt, 3 cl of coconut milk and 3 dl of water.
Cook over low heat for 25 minutes, until they are tender.
In the bowl of a blender pour the cream, 10 cl of coconut milk, 1 large pinch of curry, cilantro (about 10 leaves) and eggs.
Add the drained carrots.
Mix until you have a very smooth cream.
Check for seasoning, add more salt or curry if you want a stronger taste.
Preheat oven to 200 ° F.
Pour the carrot mixture into ramekins and bake for 15-20 minutes.
The center of the cream should be a little soft, as it will harden as it cools.
For a single large cream, it will need to cook for about 40 minutes.
Let cool and place in the fridge for at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon of powdered sugar and caramelize with a torch.
I like to put them back to the fridge for half hour but no more because the caramel does not last long in the fridge because if they are prepared too far in advance it won't stay hard
Sprinkle with coconut and a pinch of curry to serve.

title: thai-style fish parcels
directions: Place each piece of fish on a 12 inch square piece of parchment paper. Combine onions, garlic, ginger, cilantro and chili then distribute over fish. Combine sesame oil, lime zest, lime juice and sugar then drizzle over fish. Fold parchment paper into parcels. Transfer to a bamboo steamer and cover with a tight-fitting lid.
Fill 1/4 of a wok with water and bring to a boil. Place bamboo steamer in wok and cook for 8 mins, or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.

Meanwhile, cook noodles in boiling water for 3 mins, or until tender. Drain. Distribute between serving plates. Arrange fish and juice from parcels over fish. Drizzle with soy sauce and serve with Asian greens.

title: thai fish and cilantro balls
directions: To make the fish balls, process fish, egg, basil, cilantro, sugar, sauce, chili, garlic and turmeric in a food processor, until a paste forms. Chill for 15 mins.
To make dipping sauce, mix sugar and 1/3 cup boiling water until sugar dissolves. Blend in white vinegar, fish sauce, garlic and red chili.

Using oiled fingers, roll fish mixture into 1 inch balls. Heat oil until a small amount of mixture sizzles as soon as it is added. Fry fish balls in batches for 2-3 mins, turning, until golden and cooked through. Drain on paper towel.
To make the salad, combine cucumber, cilantro and scallion. Whisk together lime juice, sugar and fish sauce. Drizzle over salad.
Serve salad and fish balls together. Sprinkle with nuts and accompany with dipping sauce.

title: chicken and chipotle chili quesadilla
directions: Heat a skillet on medium-low heat and place the tortilla on it.
Once hot, spread the hot sauce and tomato sauce.
Place the Mozzarella cheese and chicken nuggets over one half of the tortilla, roll it, and grill until the cheese melts and serve.

title: smoked turkey & bacon sandwich
directions: Evenly spread Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Light Mayonnaise on 1 bread slice, then top with remaining ingredients.

title: sticky spareribs with asian greens
directions: Preheat broiler to medium. For the marinade, combine sauce, honey and garlic in a bowl. Add pork, tossing to coat.
Place pork on a wire rack in a baking dish. Broil for 15-20 mins, turning and basting occasionally, until cooked through.
Meanwhile, add oil to a pan over high heat. Add the Asian greens and stir-fry for 2-3 mins. Serve with pork, along with green onions and steamed rice.

title: shrimp and potato tart
directions: In a Dutch oven, add the potatoes, onion, butter, saffron, and 250 milliliters of water. Season and cook on low heat until softened. Drain everything and mash them. Set aside.
Once cooled, add in the bread crumbs, eggs, cheese, parsley, and shrimp. Mix well and salt and pepper to taste.
Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
In a springform pan, add a sheet of phyllo pastry making sure it comes up the sides of the pan. Baste with olive oil. Repeat with 3 other sheets.
Add the filling leaving a 1 centimeter border on all sides.
Top with another sheet of phyllo pastry tucking the ends into the border created. Baste with olive oil and repeat with 3 other sheets.
Sprinkle the top with sesame seeds.
Bake 15 minutes until golden.

title: leek potato soup
directions: Bring water to a boil and add the chicken bouillon cube.
In a dutch oven, heat 1 tbsp. olive oil and saute leeks, potatoes, onion and garlic until tender. Add prepared chicken stock and simmer for 15 minutes.
Prick the potato pieces to make sure they are cooked.
In a blender, blend until smooth.
Add cream and milk, then blend again.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: stuffed pork meatballs
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine pork, bread crumbs, milk, basil, garlic powder, oregano and salt, mixing until well incorporated. Divide mixture evenly into 8 rough patties, about 3 inches across, and set aside.
In a medium skillet over medium heat, warm olive oil. Add chard, season with salt and pepper, and cook, stirring occasionally, until chard is tender, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat.

Spoon chard evenly onto 4 of patties, leaving a 1/2-inch border around edges, then top each with 1 tablespoon chevre. Top with remaining 4 patties. Seal edges of each patty "sandwich," then gently form sandwiches into balls.
Arrange meatballs on a non-stick rimmed baking sheet and bake until the internal temperature is 160 degrees F., 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from the oven and let rest for 3 minutes before serving.

title: red chicken curry
directions: Place the dried chili peppers, chopped fresh chili peppers, red onion, garlic, cilantro roots, galangal, lemongrass, salt, lime peel and shrimp paste in a food processor and process to a paste.
Heat oil in a wok or large skillet on medium heat. Add curry paste and cook for 1 min or until fragrant. Stir in the coconut cream, then the palm sugar and fish sauce.
Add coconut milk, crushed lime leaves and 1 cup water and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat to low. Add the chicken and pepper and cook for 15 mins. Stir in the green beans and cook for a further 5 mins. Add a squeeze of lime juice.
Divide among 4 bowls and garnish with chili pepper strips, shredded lime leaves and cilantro leaves. Serve with steamed rice.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 180°C (approximately 350°F).
In a bowl, mix sugar and butter until creamy and add the egg.
Slowly beat in the mixer, adding flour gradually until dough is soft and pliable.
Shape dough into small balls and roll in the cinnamon.
Place balls on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Bake in preheated oven for about 20 minutes.
Serve with coffee.

title: pecan and coffee liqueur tart
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a 9-inch tart pan with removable bottom.

Combine flour and butter in a food processor. Pulse until crumbs form. With motor running, gradually add 2 tbsp ice-cold water, until mixture comes together. Remove and form into a ball. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 20 mins.

Roll out pastry between 2 sheets of parchment paper to form an 12-inch round. Press pastry into prepared pan, trimming edges. Place a sheet of parchment paper on the pastry. Fill with dried beans or pie weights. Bake for 10 mins. Remove paper and weights. Bake for a further 6-8 mins.

Meanwhile, beat butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl with an electric mixer until pale and creamy. Add eggs and yolk, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in flour. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into pastry crust..
Bake for 10 mins. Reduce oven temperature to 325°F. Bake a further 35-40 mins. Cool in pan on a wire rack. Remove rim of tart pan. Dust tart with powdered sugar and serve with whipped cream.

title: fig jam #2
directions: Pour boiling water over figs; let stand 15 minutes. Drain and thoroughly rinse in cold water. Pat dry; remove stems. Crush and measure figs; place in large Dutch oven. Add 1/2 cup sugar for each cup of crushed figs. Add 1 quart water. Bring to a rapid boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 3 hours or until thickened, stirring occasionally.

Ladle hot jam into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace; add a slice of lemon to each jar. Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands. Process in a boiling-water bath 10 minutes. Yield: 8 1/2 pints.

title: jamaican curried chicken
directions: In a stew pot, heat the vegetable oil.
Add the garlic, scallions, pepper, curry, allspice, and ginger and cook for a few minutes.
Add the chicken and simmer, covered on low heat about 10 minutes.
Add the coconut milk and potatoes and continue to cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over hot steamed rice with a selection of condiments such as mango chutney, coconut milk & yogurt.

title: seafood paella
directions: In a large, wide skillet, saute the langoustines, jumbo shrimp, medium shrimp, squid, and mussels in a little oil. Remove from heat and set aside.
Now saute all the chicken. Remove from heat and set aside also.
Now add the garlic, bell peppers, and onion to the same skillet.
After 5 minutes, add the tomato.
Add the rice, saffron, and water and stir well.
When this mixture begins to boil, stir back in the langoustine, shrimp, squid, and chicken. Salt to taste.
Let the rice cook through and let sit a bit before serving. Decorate with the mussels.

title: sun-dried tomato and leek quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350F.
Coat four 5-inch tart pans with cooking spray.
Pulse flour, pine nuts,almonds,baking powder
In food processor until finely ground.
Whisk together almond milk, oil and salt in bowl.
Stir in flour mixture. Press into pan.
Bake 5 minutes, then cool.
Filling
Heat 1 Tbs. oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add leeks, and saute' 8 minutes, or until softened. Set aside.
Bring large saucepan of water to a boil.
Add tofu, and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and pat dry.
Whisk 3 Tbsp. oil, lemon juice, miso, garlic and salt in bowl.
Add tofu and blend with an immersion blender.
Stir in breadcrumbs,seasonings, sun-dried tomatoes and leeks.
Spoon filling into crust.
Bake 40 minutes, or until crust is browned.
Cool 5 minutes, then unmold.

title: warm sugared pineapple over ice cream
directions: Cook pineapple, brown sugar and liqueur in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat 2 minutes or until sugar is melted and liquid is syrupy.
Scoop Breyers(R) Natural Vanilla Ice Cream into 4 dessert dishes, then top with warm pineapple mixture and sprinkle with almonds.

title: easy garlic rice
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, bring water to a boil over high heat. Stir in Lipton Recipe Secrets Savory Herb with Garlic Soup Mix and rice.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 20 minutes.

title: whipped strawberry-lime butter
directions: BEAT preserves, butter and lime zest in small bowl with mixer on high speed until smooth and fluffy.
SPOON or pipe into small bowl to serve.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray 8" or 9" springform pan or 9" pie pan with non stick cooking spray. Sprinkle bottom with graham cracker crumbs. Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water and pour into blender. Add cottage cheese and cream cheese. Cover and blend at medium speed, scraping down sides occasionally, about 2 minutes or until completely smooth. Pour into large bowl. Gently stir in whipped topping. Pour into prepared pan. Smooth top. Chill until set, about 4 hours.
When ready to serve, remove sides of pan. Top cheesecake with pie filling. Makes 8 servings.

title: polenta mash
directions: Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Grease a baking dish with melted butter.
Place a layer of polenta into the dish and add a few spoonsful of milk.
Spread with salami, Fontina cheese, butter, and a generous sprinkling of Parmesan cheese. You can use a thin layer or thick; your preference.
Cover with another layer of polenta. Smooth the surface and moisten with a little more milk.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and a few tablespoons of butter.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until golden brown with a crunchy top.

title: salami, sage and parmesan pasta
directions: Cook pasta in a large saucepan of boiling, salted water according to package directions. Drain and return to pan.
Add Parmesan cheese and butter to pasta; toss until melted. Add remaining ingredients and toss. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and serve with crusty bread.

title: chicken in green tomato and chipotle sauce
directions: Place the chicken in a large pot along with the two garlic cloves, onion, bay leaf, thyme, oregano, lemon, and salt.
Fill the pot with enough water to cover the chicken completely.
Cover and cook the chicken on low for 15 minutes.

Once cooked, remove the chicken and set it aside for later use. Leave the water and the ingredients in the pot, turn the stove up to medium, and let the water heat up until around 2 cups of the liquid has evaporated.
Place the tomatoes in the water and let them cook until they become somewhat soft in texture.
Place the tomatoes, chipotle pepper, salt, and sugar in a blender and liquefy the ingredients.
Place another large pot on the stove, pour in the vegetable oil, and once the oil begins to heat up, add the tomato sauce and let it cook for 10 minutes.
Add the liquid from the other pot and the chicken into the second pot.

Cover the pot and let the chicken cook for another 10 minutes. If after the 10 minutes there is still a lot of liquid in the pot, let everything cook for a few more minutes (uncovered) until the texture thickens.
Serve the chicken over corn tortillas. You can also add refried beans and cotija cheese to give the dish a bit more flavor.

title: chilorio—pork meat chili
directions: Cook the meat in a large pot with the onion, salt, garlic, and bay leaf until it is lightly cooked. Do not discard the onion and garlic mixture.
Cut the meat into small cubes or shred it; place it into a separate pot with cooking oil and continue cooking.
While the meat is frying, place the chili peppers, the saved onion and garlic, vinegar, and salt in a blender. Mix everything well until a slightly thick sauce is made.
Once the meat is completely cooked, pour the sauce into the pan and mix everything well.
Add the cumin and pepper and allow the sauce to bubble slightly.
Taste the sauce before serving-if it is too bitter, add a pinch of sugar.
Turn off the stove and serve the meat alone or on flour tortillas.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Mix the butter and sugars. Once mixed, add the egg, a few drops of vanilla extract, and chocolate and mix again.
Shape into balls and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, being careful to leave enough room for the cookies to expand.
Bake for 10 minutes and cool on a cooling rack and serve.

title: afri’s cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Line a pie pan with about 20 centimeters of parchment paper.
Cream the butter and brown sugar together. Add the egg and continue beating until well combined.
Then add the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and chocolate. Mix quickly making sure not to overmix.
Pour the batter out into the pie pan and bake 25 minutes until the top is firm and golden but the inside is tender.
This is nice topped with heavy cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: fig and goat cheese tarts
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, salt, and flax seeds.
Cut butter into the flour until grainy.
Add water slowly, carefully moistening the mixture evenly, add water until the dough holds..
Cover the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Mix the ricotta, eggs, Parmesan cheese, chives, salt, and pepper in a large bowl.
Once the dough has rested, roll out on a floured work surface, and form 4 circles the size of the pie pans. Spread in pans.
Prick the pie crusts with a fork.
Optionally, pie crusts can be precooked for ten minutes.
Divide the goat cheese in each pie shell, add the egg mixture, and gently place half of fig on top.
Bake 20-25 minutes.

title: chopped salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a bowl and serve as a side dish to your favorite meals.

title: mashed cauliflower with parmesan cheese
directions: Cook the cauliflower in a steamer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove the cauliflower from the steamer and place it on a large bowl along with the butter and salt.
Mash the cauliflower using a food processor until it gets a soft texture.
Add the parmesan cheese to the cauliflower and mix.
Serve as a side dish with your favourite meals.

title: welsch cakes
directions: In a medium bowl, pour the flour, baking powder, add the butter cut into cubes.
Using your fingertips, incorporate the butter into the flour until dough resembles a coarse meal.
Add the egg, sugar, and raisins, keep mixing with your fingers to get a smooth ball of dough (if necessary add a few drops of milk, working the dough for 3 to 4 minutes, so it becomes more flexible).
Trun the dough onto a lightly floured surface and roll it to a 0.5 cm thickness.
Cut circles of dough with a cookie cutter.
In a frying pan, heat the butter, wipe the excess and fry the welsh cakes for 3 minutes on each side. Serve with a little butter and a good cup of tea.

title: rice pie with goat cheese
directions: Cut the tomatoes into sections and sprinkle with coarse salt to draw out the liquid.
Rinse the rice until the water comes out clear. Put in a pan with 1 cup water and cook, covered, until the water is evaporated. Leave covered and set aside for 20 minutes.
Mix the rice with the egg white, salt, pepper, and half a cup of the cheese
Coat a baking dish with cooking spray and fill with the rice mixture, pressing down slightly. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave for 2 minutes on medium power.
Place the tomatoes into a baking dish, sprinkle with the garlic, salt, pepper, and olive oil. Broil for 3-4 minutes, until slightly cooked.
Place the slices of turkey ham on top of the rice and cover with the tomatoes, the goat cheese, and the olives.
Mix the egg yolk with the egg, cream, and milk. Add salt and pepper. Spread onto the rice base and microwave at medium high power for 2 minutes.
Broil for 20 minutes until the surface is golden brown. Let cool for 20 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line a baking pan with foil.

Heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add zucchini, squash, onion and garlic. Saute 10-15 mins, until tender. Add taco seasoning and cook, stirring, 30 seconds, until aromatic. Stir in beans and tomatoes. Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring 2-3 mins, until sauce thickens slightly.
Slice tops off peppers and reserve. Remove seeds and membranes. Trim bottoms of peppers so they sit flat. Place peppers and tops on baking pan.
Spoon bean mixture into peppers. Drizzle with a little olive oil.
Bake 15 mins. Sprinkle with combined cheese and breadcrumbs. Bake a further 5-10 mins, or until tender. Top with cilantro leaves to serve.

title: spicy beef burritos
directions: Combine beef, onion, garlic, spices and hot sauce, if using, in a large bowl and mix well. Heat 2 tsp oil in a large frying pan on medium. Cook beef mixture, stirring to break up any lumps, for 5 mins, until lightly browned. Add tomato and cilantro. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 15 mins, until tender.
Meanwhile, heat remaining oil in a pan on high. Cook red pepper for 5 mins, until tender. Heat tortillas according to packet directions.
Top tortillas with salad greens, cilantro, spicy beef mixture, red pepper and sour cream. Wrap up to enclose filling and serve.

title: homemade vegetable broth
directions: Add the water to a large pot. Add the leeks, tomatoes, potatoes, turnips, celery, bell pepper, onion, cabbage, carrots, bay leaves, parsley, and a pinch of salt and black pepper. Bring to a boil and lower the heat to medium low.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Strain the broth and set aside.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix the mascarpone cheese, onion, lemon juice, lemon zest, and ground walnuts in a small bowl.
Cut a thin slice off the bottom of each tomato, and a slice from the top.
Remove the filling of each tomato using a spoon.
Stuff the tomatoes with the mascarpone cheese mixture, garnish with a walnut, put the top back in place, and serve.

title: orange julius
directions: put all ingredients in a large cup or a blender
blend till smooth
add a little whipped cream on the top if you want
Enjoy your Orange Julius!

title: spicy yogurt chicken
directions: Combine yogurt, cilantro, garlic, ginger and spices. Coat chicken with mixture then chill, covered, for 4 hours, or overnight, to marinate.
Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook chicken for 5-6 mins per side, until cooked through.
Meanwhile, to make the salad, combine cucumber, tomatoes, oregano and olive oil. Season.
Serve chicken with salad and black olives.

title: healthy fruit muffins
directions: Combine flours, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl mix buttermilk, oil, banana and egg.
Add dates, nuts and apply to dry ingredients.
Mix liquids into dry ingredients until blended.

title: beefy spinach and mushroom casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Heat a nonstick skillet over medium heat and add oil. Then add onion and cook 3 - 4 minutes to soften. Add ground beef and cook another 5 - 6 minutes until beef is cooked through.
Add garlic, rosemary, Worcestershire sauce, wine, soup and mushrooms. Cook another 5 minutes until heated through. Add spinach, and season with salt and pepper.
Mix Bisquick and water to form a soft dough. Add water in increments to keep dough from becoming too soft. Add more water if dough is too dry. Roll dough out to the size of your casserole dish.

Spray a medium casserole dish with cooking spray and spread out beef mixture. Top with dough and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 20 - 30 minutes until dough is lightly browned and cooked through.

title: small chocolate chip cereal bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees celsius.
Mix the flour, ground almonds, oatmeal, and baking powder in a bowl.
Mix in the honey, oil, and egg whites. Then, add the chocolate chips.
Form the mixture into a ball.
Spread the mixture onto a flat, lightly floured surface and cut into bars 1 cm wide.
Bake the bars for about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn oven off. Let bars cool for 10 minutes.
Return bars to the off, but still hot, oven and let sit until bars are crispy.

title: butter cookies
directions: Using an electric mixer or stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, cream together the butter and sugar in a large bowl until fluffy.
Add the flour, vanilla extract, lemon juice, lemon zest, egg white, and salt. Continue mixing until the ingredients are completely mixed.
Form a dough ball, cover it with plastic wrap, and refrigerate it for one hour.
Preheat the oven to 410 degrees Fahrenheit.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out the dough with a rolling pin to a thickness of about 1/4 inch. With a cookie stamp the cookies into desired shapes.
Place the cookies on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet and bake for 12 minutes.
Remove the cookies from the oven and let them cool completely.
Melt the chocolate using the microwave and dip the cookies in it.
Dust them with candy sprinkles and serve.

title: spicy cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in a saucepan of boiling salted water for 10-15 mins, until almost tender. Drain well. Cool and cut into thick slices.

Heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Cook potatoes for 5-6 mins, turning occasionally, until golden brown. Sprinkle with cheese and red pepper flakes and cook for 1-2 mins, until golden and crisp. Season to taste and garnish with parsley.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: In a medium bowl, combine chicken, pork, garlic, 1 tbsp peanut oil, soy sauce and brandy. Cover and chill for 3 hours, or overnight.

Heat 1/2 tbsp peanut oil in a wok or large frying pan. Working in batches, stir-fry chicken and pork mixture until browned. Set aside. Add remaining oil to wok and stir-fry carrot, pepper, green onions and celery until carrot is just tender. Add shrimp and cabbage. Stir-fry until cabbage is almost wilted. Return chicken mixture to wok. Whisk together cornstarch and chicken stock then add to pan along with oyster sauce. Bring to a boil and cook until thickened slightly.
Serve topped with fried noodles.

title: coconut curry chicken soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Saute onion, lemongrass and ginger for 2-3 mins, until tender. Add sweet potato and curry paste. Cook for 2-3 mins, stirring often, until fragrant. Add chicken stock and pepper. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to medium and simmer, covered, for 10-15 mins, until sweet potato is just tender.
Add coconut milk, chicken and rice. Simmer for 2-3 mins, until meat is just cooked through. Serve topped with fresh cilantro.

title: stuffed avocado
directions: Mix the tomato, jalapeno pepper, peas, panela cheese, mayonnaise, pepper, and salt in a medium bowl.
Cut the avocados in half, remove the bone and some of the pulp.
Pour lemon juice all over the avocados.
Remove the avocados carefully and skin using a spoon.
Garnish 2 plates with lettuce leaves and place the peeled avocados on them.
Stuff the avocados with the vegetables and cheese, and serve.

title: broccoli rabe empanadas
directions: In a heavy-bottomed pot, heat up the olive oil and saute the onion and bell peppers until softened.
Add the sweet paprika, tomato, and ham hock.
Add a splash of white wine and let the mixture simmer until it has thickened a bit.
Add in the broccoli rabe, salt and pepper to taste, stir everything together, and let simmer a few minutes more.
Set aside.
Make the dough.
Add a handful of flour to a large bowl, along with a pinch of salt.
Add the milk, white wine, sunflower oil, and 1 egg, and stir everything with a fork until you have a semi-liquid dough.
Keep adding flour little by little while mixing with the fork until the dough starts to pull away from the sides of the bowl.
When that happens, transfer the dough to a lightly floured work surface and start to knead it while adding in the rest of the dough. Knead until the dough is soft, elastic, and no longer sticky.
Preheat the oven to 190 degrees Celsius.
Line a baking tray with parchment paper.
Divide the dough into 4 portions and roll each portion out into the thinnest rectangle possible.
Place one rectangle on the baking tray.
Smear on half of the filling, leaving about a 1-centimeter border on all sides of the rectangle.
Top with the Brie cheese and chorizo sausage.
Place another dough rectangle on top of the first.
Cut off any excess and fold the bottom part of dough over the top part of dough. Pinch the edges.
Make a hole in the center of the dough so steam escapes, and baste the top with the beaten egg.
Repeat with the other 2 portions of dough and the remainder of the filling.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zorama cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 180C.
Combine the flour, potato starch, sugar, eggs, milk, butter, grated peel of 1 lemon, and the vanilla extract together and divide the batter into 2 bowls.
Add the powdered cocoa to one bowl and the chocolate chips to the other.
Butter a bundt or tube pan and begin adding the two types of batter in layers, first one type and then the other, and so on.
Sprinkle the top layer with powdered sugar.
Bake for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool the cake completely before removing it from the pan, sprinkle with powdered sugar, and serve.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Prepare the noodles in a large saucepan according to the package directions. Drain, return to the saucepan, and keep them warm. Heat oven to 375 F. Grease a 2 quart casserole. In a saucepan, over medium heat, melt the margarine; add the mushrooms, celery, and onion, cooking about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender. Stir in the flour until well blended. Gradually add the chicken broth and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce the heat to low; cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently,

Spoon the tuna mixture into the prepared casserole. In a small bowl, combine the potato chips, cheese, and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over the casserole, and bake for 25 minutes, or until hot and bubbly, and the top is golden.

title: curried yogurt marinade
directions: Pulse onion, ginger and garlic together in food processor to mince. Add yogurt, curry powder, salt and pepper and process into thin, rough paste. Pour into large, resealable bag. Add chops, seal bag and refrigerate for 2 to 10 hours.

Prepare a medium-hot fire in grill. Brush grill grate clean and lightly oil grate. Remove chops from marinade, shaking off excess marinade. Do not pat dry. Discard remaining marinade. Grill chops directly over heat, turning once, until internal temperature on a thermometer reads 145 degrees Fahrenheit, 8 to 10 minutes, followed by a 3-minute rest time.
Note: Insert the meat thermometer into the pork chops horizontally to get an accurate reading.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 220 degrees Celsius.
Whisk together the water, honey, and sugar until the sugar dissolves. Add the egg yolks.
Sift the flour with the baking soda and allspice and add to the liquid mixture. Mix well. Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

Remove the dough from the refrigerator and set aside for 5 minutes. Roll out with a rolling pin until approximately 3 millimeters thick. Cut into desired shapes with a cookie cutter or drawn paper pattern.
Place the shapes onto a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven and cool on a baking rack.
Make the frosting by beating the egg white until foamy and then adding the powdered sugar until it reaches the consistency of toothpaste.
Spread the frosting onto the cooled cookies.

title: super chocolate tart
directions: Crush the cookies in the food processor, and mix with the softened margarine.
Use your fingers to spread this dough in an ungreased pie pan, covering the bottom and sides. Place in the freezer while you prepare the topping.
