For the topping, slowly heat the cream in a small pan. When it begins to boil, remove from heat, add butter and crumbled pieces of chocolate. Stir until dissolved, and the cream is shiny.
Pour on the pie dough, and decorate as desired (the rest of the biscuits, nuts, or candies).
Store in the refrigerator until serving.

title: beer battered fish and chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Place potatoes on prepared tray. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle with paprika. Toss to coat. Bake 40 mins or until tender and golden brown.
Meanwhile, place flour in a medium bowl. Gradually whisk in beer until smooth. Season. Cover with plastic wrap. Chill 30 mins.

In a large heavy-based saucepan, heat oil (oil is ready when a cube of bread crisps quickly without absorbing oil). Dip fish pieces into batter to coat. Shake off excess. Deep-fry fish, in batches, for 4-5 mins or until cooked and golden. Drain on paper towels. Reheat oil between batches.
Serve with potatoes, lemon wedges and tartar sauce.

title: panela cheese and vegetables toasts
directions: Preheat a big skillet with olive oil on medium-high.
Add the onion, garlic, and green bell pepper to the skillet. Stir often while seasoning with soy sauce.
Once the onion becomes transparent, add the broccoli and soy sauce. Put the lid on the skillet and let it cook for 2 minutes.
Remove the lid, add the mushrooms, and let it cook for 3 minutes.
Turn off the stove and serve, adding more soy sauce if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut each fillet into strips going with the grain of the beef.
In a large pot, heat up either some olive oil or butter. Add the beef and brown it on all sides.
Add the onions and saute them until softened and transparent. At that point, add the mushrooms and stir everything together.

Add the mustard, tomatoes, wine, and bay leaves and stir everything together. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer on low heat for about an hour or until the meat is tender. Occasionally check to make sure all the liquid has not evaporated out. If it looks low, add a little water.
Once the meat is tender, stir in the cream and simmer another 10 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with fresh parsley and on a bed of steamed rice or pasta.

title: one-bowl chocolate cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and flour an 8-inch round cake pan.
Place butter, sugar and milk in a large saucepan on medium heat. Stir for 2-3 mins until melted and combined.
Sift flour, cocoa and soda together into the saucepan (or bowl if using a microwave). Stir in ground almonds, eggs and rum extract until smooth. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 50-60 mins until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on a wire rack.

For the ganache, place chocolate and cream in a small saucepan on low heat. Stir for 2-3 mins until melted and smooth. Transfer to a small bowl. Cool until ganache thickens slightly. Spread over cooled cake. Serve in wedges with whipped cream, if desired.

title: playin' hooky
directions: In a large water pitcher combine BACARDI(R) Mixers, BACARDI(R) Superior Rum, and the juice of 2 limes.
Add ice.
Cut remaining two limes into wheels and add to pitcher
Add can of club soda and stir gently to mix.

title: mini carrot cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Cake Preparation:
Butter 8 small cake pans.
Whisk the coconut oil, sugar, and egg in a small bowl until the mixture is thick and pale.
Add the maple syrup.
Sift the flour, baking soda, ground cinnamon, Sichuan pepper, and nutmeg together.
Transfer maple mixture to larger bowl and add the grated carrots, walnuts, raisins, and mix well.
Mix in the sifted dry ingredients.
Pour the mixture into the molds and bake for about 20 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before removing from molds and placing on cooling rack.
Prepare the icing by whisking the butter and cream cheese until the mixture is smooth.
Continue whisking, add the icing sugar and vanilla.
Ice the cool cakes using a pastry bag or directly using a small spatula.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.

Combine the cookies, walnuts, cinnamon, sugar and butter together to form the crust and press into a cake pan. Bake until lightly golden, approximately 10 minutes. Remove from oven and lower the heat to 150 Celsius.

Beat the cream cheese with the sugar until smooth. Add the pumpkin and mix to incorporate. Add the piloncillo, ginger, nutmeg, nutmeg, sour cream, and the eggs, one by one. Beat until homogenous and without lumps.
Pour over the crust into the cake pan and place in a larger baking dish. Pour hot water into the baking dish. Check during the baking to make sure the water doesn't evaporate completely.
Bake approximately 90 minutes, when the surface is firm to the touch but still wobbly in the middle.
Let cool in the pan for approximately 2 hours at room temperature. Remove from pan and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: s'mores
directions: Heat the marshmallow over an open flame until it begins to brown and melt. Sandwich the chocolate and hot marshmallow between two New York Style Cinnabon(R) Sweet Swirls crisps.

title: tamal roll
directions: In a bowl, beat the butter.
Once fluffy, add the dough and continue beating.
Add salt and orange juice.
Wet a kitchen rag, which will be used to make the roll.
Place the rag on a flat surface and spread the dough on top.
Add a layer of the desired filling (poblano chili strips, cheese, or beans).
Using the rag, roll the dough. Close both ends with strings. Be careful to stretch the kitchen rag to avoid creases on the roll.
Cook in a steamer for at least 1 hour.
Remove the kitchen rag while the roll is still hot.
Slice and serve with cream and sauce (optional).

title: mango chicken
directions: Heat half the oil in a large frying pan or wok on high. Cook chicken in batches for 3 mins, until brown and cooked through. Remove from pan and set aside.
Heat remaining oil in same pan. Cook pepper and chili for 1 min. Add rice, peas and scallions. Stir-fry for 2 mins, until rice is heated through.
Combine chutney with 1/4 cup water. Add to rice, then add the chicken. Toss for 2 mins, until heated through. Remove from heat, stir in mango and cilantro and serve.

title: grilled turkey sausages with a simple tomato salad
directions: Cook the sausages on the grill with a pinch of salt.
While they are on the grill, finely chop one of the garlic cloves, or put in a mortar, along with the parsley and a little olive oil, grind to a pulp and set aside.
Cut the tomatoes as desired (I cut the green colored ones very thin, and the cherry tomatoes into 4 equal pieces).
Place them in a bowl along with the olives and a dash of olive oil and a few drops of balsamic vinegar. Chop the other garlic clove and add it as well. Top with some parmesan shavings.
After the sausages are well grilled, break them into small pieces and add them to the tomato mixture along with the parsley and garlic mixture from the mortar.
Serve it with small pieces of bread and enjoy.

title: varese salad
directions: Place the bacon slices between sheets of paper towel. Microwave on high for 2 minutes.
Add the lettuce, cheeses, onions, and croutons to a bowl and mix well. The quantities may vary according to taste.
For the dressing, in a bowl add a drizzle of oil, a few drops of vinegar, a tablespoon of honey and a dollop of mustard. Mix well.
Plate the salad and pour the Varese dressing on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius.

Make the crust by creaming the butter and sugar together with the salt. Add the egg and, once incorporated, add the flour. Mix just enough to incorporate. Cover the ball of dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 or 2 hours.
Roll out the dough on a floured surface and cut into circles. Line muffin tin cups with each. Refrigerate.
Blend the maple sugar, butter, eggs, and vanilla together in the blender.
Place the pecans in the bottom of each muffin tin cup. Spoon the filling over each, leaving a space of 1 centimeter between the filing and the top of the muffin tin.
Bake for 30-40 minutes until the crust is golden around the edges. Remove from oven and allow to cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix the powdered sugar, flour, and butter with your fingertips until obtaining a mixture close to a "crumble" (coarse sand).
Set aside.In a saucepan, cook the blueberries in 2 tablespoons water over medium heat for 5 minutes.
When the blueberries have burst, turn off the heat, and mash coarsely with a fork.
Let cool.
Preheat oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit.
In a bowl, mix the flour, baking soda and a pinch of salt, and make a well in the center.
In another bowl, whisk the egg and the sugar until the mixture whitens.
Add the butter and the oil and mix gently.
Finally, add the buttermilk and the vanilla, continue mixing.
When the mixture is smooth, pour in flour, and mix gently with a spatula.
Do not mix too hard and too long: as soon as it is smooth, stop.
Finally, add the remaining fresh blueberries.
Pour a teaspoon of dough into each baking cup (you need to keep half the dough), then evenly distribute the crushed blueberries into the cups.
Then cover with with another tablespoon of dough and top off with the streusel dough.
Bake for 15-20 minutes: muffins should be golden, to test doneness, a knife should come out clean after being inserted in a muffin.
Cool on a rack.

title: apple-spice upside down cake
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a glass 9x12 pan
Arrange apples in bottom, I made 2 layers alternating the angle, and sprinkle with cinnamon lightly.
Melt the topping ingredient together over medium heat until the sugars dissolve, but bot to a boiling point, whipping nearly constantly so sugars make a Carmel like mixture .
It will be smooth, then immediately pour over the apples evenly. ( be aware of the area needed to be covered as you can not spread the Carmel)
Make the cake as instructions and pour over apple/ carmel layer.
Bake as per box 350 degree, for 30-35 min.( no .longer) top will look dry, but not to worry
Place on cooling rack, for about 10-15 min, to set, then place serving tray,
I used a glass 10x14 and held both together and inverted cake onto serving plate.
Scrape any remaining carmel onto the now "top" pf cake . Serve with a dollop of cream .....super delicious the next day cooled... The carmel saturates the cake & soooo moist:)

title: fruit salad tart
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll pastry on lightly floured surface to form a 10- x 14-inch rectangle. Arrange pastry on cookie sheet; pierce with fork. Bake 12 minutes or until golden. Cool completely on wire rack.
Meanwhile, combine cream cheese, sugar and lime peel in medium bowl; evenly spread over cooled crust.
Spritz fruit with Wish-Bone(R) Salad Spritzers(R) Raspberry Bliss(R) Vinaigrette Dressing in large bowl, then toss to coat; evenly spoon over crust. Chill, if desired. To serve, cut into 24 pieces.

title: cold orange pudding
directions: Put the gelatin leaves in cold water to soak for 3 minutes.
In a saucepan, bring water to boil. and then add the drained gelatin sheets, stir well until dissolved.
Whip the cream.
In a bowl, combine the condensed milk, orange zest, and the 400 ml. of orange juice. Gradually, add the gelatin and cream. Mix everything well.
Pour into a bundt cake mold.
Refrigerate for 5 hours until pudding solidifies.
Mix all the ingredients in a sauce pan.
Simmer for 20 minutes over low heat until the syrup thickens.
After the pudding solidifies, immerse the mold for a few seconds in hot water.
Unmold.
Drizzle with syrup, and the pudding is ready to serve.

title: bread salad
directions: Add the bread slices to a bowl.
Cover with water and set aside for 20 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, onion, cucumber, and celery to a salad bowl.
Add the basil and toss well.
Strain the bread and crumble into the salad bowl with the vegetables.
Season with oil, vinegar, salt, and black pepper.
Set the salad aside for a few hours until ready to serve to allow the flavors to infuse.

title: cheese and vegetable sandwich
directions: Mix the zucchini, carrot, cheddar, onion, and salsa together in a bowl. Salt and pepper slightly.
Prepare the sandwiches by placing half the vegetable mixture on a slice of bread, covering with the other slice of bread, and placing onto a skillet previously spritzed with the cooking spray.
Place a heavy object, such as a pan or plate weighed down with cans, on top of the sandwich to press. Cook for 2 minutes, flip, and cook for 2 minutes more.
Remove from the skillet, cut the sandwich in half, and serve.

title: strawberry coconut lime spa water
directions: Pour the coconut water into a large pitcher.
Add the limes, strawberries and mint leaves to the pitcher.
Fill the pitcher with water and stir well.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving. Pour into glasses with ice and enjoy!

title: rostinciana
directions: Grease the slow cooker with extra virgin olive oil.
Add the meat, wine, and ground spices, carefully stir to season well.
Place the lid on the slow cooker and set it to high for 6 hours.
Serve hot.

title: baked chicken tortellini
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Boil the tortellini in salted water for about 12 mins. Meanwhile, beat the egg in a bowl, stir in the cream and add the parmesan. Season. Drain the tortellini, and place in a baking dish. Distribute the chicken slices evenly around the pasta, then pour the creamy cheese mixture over top. Bake for 15 mins. To serve, garnish with the chives and chopped spring onion.

title: jaguar sundae
directions: Place 2 tablespoons chocolate chips in small freezer bag and squeeze out air; seal bag. Microwave at HIGH 15 seconds. Remove from microwave, knead and repeat until chocolate is melted and smooth. Cut small corner off bag and squeeze 1 chocolate dot on each green candy to make ''eyes''. Outline inside rim of waffle bowl with melted chocolate, then sprinkle with blue sprinkles; let stand to set.

Arrange Breyers(R) Cookies & Cream Ice Cream in waffle bowl. Press in twist pretzel "ears"; arrange remaining 2 chocolate chips in center of 'ears'. Top Ice Cream with caramel topping. Pipe 2 small dollops whipped cream side-by-side for "mouth", then press chocolate kiss upside down between the whipped cream dollops for "nose". Arrange gum drop below dollops for "tongue". Stick pretzel sticks in whipped cream for "whiskers", then sprinkle whipped cream with blue sprinkles. Arrange green candy for "eyes". Enjoy!

title: healthy carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes on high.
Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan coated with spray.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-50 minutes.
Done when pick comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and green bean rice paper rolls
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions; drain and coarsely chop. Combine noodles, beans, bean sprouts, herbs and sauces in a large bowl
Dip 1 rice paper wrapper into a shallow bowl of warm water. Shake to remove excess water and place on a clean tea towel.

Place 1 shrimp 3/4 inch from edge of wrapper. Top with 1/4 cup filling. Fold edge of wrapper over filling. Roll tightly, folding in sides. Place on a platter. Keep covered with damp paper towels to prevent rolls from drying out.
Continue with remaining shrimp and 1/2 the filling. Follow same method with tofu strips and remaining filling.
For the dipping sauce, combine all ingredients and 1 tbsp water in a small bowl. Serve with rolls.

title: bbq chicken wings
directions: Preheat grill 400°.
In a large saucepot bring water, salt, red pepper flakes and garlic to a boil until salt dissolves; immediately chill. Add wings and let sit 2 hours. Remove wings from water and pat dry.

Combine Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Real Mayonnaise, hot sauce, BBQ Sauce and lemon juice in a large bowl. Add wings to mayonnaise mixture and marinate in refrigerator for one hour. Remove from marinade and grill turning frequently until chicken is throughly cooked, about 25 minutes.

title: sunday cannelloni
directions: Place the oil, shallot, tomato puree, water, Vin Santo, a pinch of salt, a pinch of sugar, and a few basil leaves in the slow cooker and cook on high for approximately 1 hour.

In the meantime, prepare the bechamel sauce by melting 2 tablespoons butter in a medium saucepan. Add the flour, and stirring with a whisk, slowly incorporate the milk. Season with a pinch of salt and a pinch of nutmeg.
Place the cannelloni in the slow cooker with the tomato sauce, cover with the bechamel sauce, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and replace the lid on the slow cooker.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
Serve hot.

title: viennese hot chocolate with cinnamon
directions: Refrigerate a metal bowl and whisk for 1 hour.
Pour the cream into the cold bowl and beat. When it begins to get fluffy, add powdered sugar and vanilla extract.
Stop beating when the cream forms stiff peaks. Refrigerate.
Heat milk in a saucepan.
Add cocoa powder and cinnamon to the bottom of the mugs (for 1 mug: 3 teaspoons chocolate and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon).
Pour boiling milk through a sieve into mug, and gently mix.
Then, using a piping bag, garnish the hot chocolate with a ball of whipped cream.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon and white chocolate chips.

title: hot cocoa bowls
directions: Place the cocoa powder and sugar in a small saucepan. Add the milk and whisk to combine.
Heat on medium heat until hot. Divide among 2 bowls. Serve hot with marshmallows on the side.

title: ovomaltine pudding
directions: Heat the milk with Ovomaltine.
Sprinkle with agar powder, and let boil, stirring constantly, for a minute or two.
Remove from heat, add the remaining ingredients.
Beat with an electric mixer in order to get a mixture with no lumps.
Pour into jars.
Let cool before serving.

title: sticky pulled pork sandwiches
directions: Score skin and underside of pork at 1/2 inch intervals, to 1/2 inch depth.
In a small bowl, combine spices. Rub evenly over pork to coat. Season to taste. Cover and chill for at least 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a medium, heavy-based saucepan on high. Saute onion 1-2 minutes. Add pork skin side down, and cook 3-4 minutes. Turn and cook 2-3 minutes, until browned all over. Remove.
Add water, barbecue sauce, vinegar and sugar to same saucepan. stirring to dissolve sugar. Bring to a boil. reduce heat to low. Return pork to pan, turning to coat in sauce.

Cover with a cartouche (parchment paper cut to fit inside saucepan) directly over pork, to retain moisture; cover with saucepan lid. Simmer gently 1 1/2 hours, until meat is very tender and falls apart easily.
Remove pork from sauce and use 2 forks to roughly shred. Set aside.
Increase heat to high and bring liquid to a rapid simmer. Simmer uncovered for 8-10 minutes, until reduced by two thirds.
Fill dinner rolls with cheese, tomato slices, shredded pork, reduced sauce and pickles. Serve immediately.

title: tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil and saute the onion, mushrooms, ham, garlic, and paprika. Once the onion is transparent, add the chickpeas, water, powdered bouillon, and tomatoes.
Cover the saucepan and boil for 15 minutes. Turn the heat off and let the soup cool for a few minutes. Puree until smooth using a hand mixer or in the blender.
Garnish with the panela cheese and serve.

title: spicy turkey-ranch salad
directions: Combine turkey, lime juice, cayenne pepper sauce and 1 tablespoon cilantro.

Arrange lettuce on large serving platter. Top with turkey, tomatoes, carrots and cucumber, arranging in rows. Just before serving, drizzle with Wish-Bone Light(R) Ranch Dressing, then sprinkle with remaining cilantro and chips.

title: pumpkin cappellacci
directions: To obtain the pumpkin pulp, place the pumpkin, with its skin but with the seeds removed, wrapped in aluminum foil, in a very hot oven.
Bake the pumpkin for 20 minutes, then remove it from the oven and let it cool.
In the meantime, prepare the sheets of dough, by placing the flour on a work surface and making a well in the center.
Place the eggs in the well and begin incorporating them by kneading for approximately 15 minutes without adding water or salt.
Roll out the dough with a rolling pin (you may also use a pasta machine), it should not be too thin. Keep in mind that the dough should be elastic, and that is done by kneading it thoroughly.
Once the sheets of dough are ready, let them rest for 15 to 20 minutes.
In the meantime, prepare the filling by removing the skin from the cooled pumpkin and mashing the pumpkin pulp to a coarse consistency.

Add the eggs, a pinch of nutmeg, breadcrumbs, grated Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to the mashed pumpkin. The filling should be quite thick. If necessary, add more breadcrumbs and cheese until it is of the right consistency.
Next, cut the sheets of dough into squares 5 or 6 centimeters long and place a tablespoon of filling in the center of each square.
Close each square by folding one corner to the opposite corner making a triangle, then bring together the two ends into a ring and seal them closed.
Boil the cappellacci in a stockpot full of boiling salted water and complete with a ragu.
Serve with grated parmesan cheese.

title: grape bonbons
directions: Wash the grapes and remove the seeds. Dry, and set aside.
Heat and stir, the condensed milk and butter, until obtaining a very creamy mixture.
When cold, gently add the grapes to the milk and butter mixture, and place in the serving platter.
In the microwave, or in a water bath, heat the cream and chocolate, until it melts and becomes a creamy mixture.
Let cool, and pour on the condensed milk and grapes.
Garnish to taste, and refrigerate for at least 2 to 3 hours.
Serve fresh.

title: dried fruit "sausage"
directions: In a blender, finely chop the almonds. Set aside.
Also chop the figs in the blender so they form a thick and sticky paste.
Add the almonds and mix.
Add the chopped walnuts, apricots cut into small pieces, brandy, and honey. Mix well to obtain a very thick paste.
Roll the dough into a sausage and wrap it in a piece of parchement paper. The paper will prevent it from drying out. Store in a cool place. It can be made 2 to 3 days in advance.
To serve, cut into slices.

title: green bean harissa salad
directions: Cook the beans in boiling water for around 8-10 minutes.
In a bowl, mix together the harissa with the mayonnaise.
Drain the beans and toss with the mayonnaise harrisa mixture.

title: hamburgers au gratin
directions: Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
In a bowl, mix the beef, onion, garlic, parsley, paprika, and salt and pepper to taste.
Divide into 4 portions. Shape the hamburger patties and in the center add 1 cube of Manchego cheese per portion. Cover with meat from the same patty.
Heat a skillet and cook the patties until golden brown on both sides and cooked on the inside.
Place in a baking dish, pour the tomato sauce, and sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake for 15 minutes, until the cheese melts.
Remove from the oven and serve warm.

title: party bowl of trail mix
directions: Mix all together and divide into two medium-sized bowls.

title: pineapple coconut cooler
directions: Place all ingredients, except sherbet, in blender container; cover. Blend on high speed until ice is crushed. Add sherbet; cover.
Blend until smooth. Garnish with pineapple slices and cherries, if desired.

title: rice noodles with bbq pork
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and chilies and stir-fry until tender.
Add barbecued pork, shrimp, squid and sausage and stir-fry over high heat until seafood is cooked, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add bean sprouts; toss lightly.
Remove from wok.
Cut rice noodles into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Heat remaining oil in wok.
Add noodles and stir-fry until very hot, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soy and oyster sauces and mix well.

title: green rice gratin
directions: Rinse the rice in cold water until cleaned, about 5 minutes. Drain.
Blend the water, parsley, cilantro, onion and garlic in a blender until well mixed, approximately 2 minutes.

Place a little oil into a pan and add the rice, stirring slightly for 30 seconds. Add the blended mixture and allow to come to a boil before lowering the heat to low and covering. Allow to cook for 20 minutes.
Grease a pan with a little bit of butter and melt the rest of the butter, adding it to the rice along with the cream and half of the grated cheese.
Place the entire mixture into the baking pan and place the rest of the cheese on the top, in slices.
Bake 20 minutes on 180 C until the cheese browns.

title: homemade peanut butter
directions: Put the peanuts, sugar, and fennel in the blender.
Gradually add oil, grinding well.
Check if you need more or less oil, it all depends on the desired consistency.

title: homemade ketchup
directions: Add the oil to a skillet on medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and saute for 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes and simmer on low heat 15 minutes.
Add the vinegar, honey, cayenne pepper, cinnamon, paprika, cloves, and mustard. Simmer for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add everything to a food processor and puree until smooth.
Strain the ketchup through a mesh strainer.
Cool at room temperature 1 hour and then refrigerate.

title: idiazabal cheese salad with mustard vinaigrette
directions: Coat the cheese cubes with beaten egg and bread crumbs twice. Fry in plenty of hot oil.
Separately, whisk together the oil, vinegar, whole grain mustard, and salt in a bowl to make a vinaigrette.
Mix together all the remaining ingredients and cover with the vinaigrette. Place the fried cheese cubes on top of the salad and serve.

title: kasspatzle
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, the whole eggs, the egg whites, and the milk to obtain an even dough. Add salt at the end.
Allow the dough to rest for 10 minutes.
Heat a large pot of water.
Grate the dough with a cheese grater over the hot water.
Let the dough cook in the water until the pieces float to the surface.
Drain and rinse with cold water to stop the baking.
In a frying pan, heat 30 grams of butter.
Sautee the chopped onion in the butter for 5 minutes.
Add the diced ham and mix.
Add the pasta and cheese.
Mix with a wooden spoon until the cheese melts.

title: easy irish stew
directions: Layer meat, carrots, onions, cabbage and potatoes in a Dutch oven. Season each layer and add thyme and bay leaves. Add stock then cover and simmer over medium heat for 1 hour. Adjust seasoning and serve garnished with parsley.

title: sweet and sour rice salad
directions: Cook the rice in boiling salted water according to package instructions. Drain and let cool. To cool faster, add cold water to the cooked rice and drain.
Wash and cut the red pepper, green pepper, and yellow pepper into thin slices. Grill them lightly. Let cool.
Peel the cucumber, cut in four lengthwise, and remove the seeds. Chop finely.
Wash the grapes, cut them in two and remove the seeds.
Fry the bacon until crispy.
Prepare the vinaigrette in a bowl with honey, olive oil, garlic vinegar, pink Himalayan salt, and Sichuan pepper.
Mix everything together.
In a bowl, place the rice, vegetables, and fruit.
Sprinke with the crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with the vinaigrette.
Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: turkey meatloaf with strawberry salsa
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Squeeze out bread then mix with turkey, egg, parsley and 1 onion. Season then add cheese and shape into a loaf. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 1 hour.
For the strawberry sauce, mix strawberry puree with diced strawberries, vinegar, oil, thyme and remaining onions. Season and add a pinch of sugar. Serve with turkey meatloaf.

title: almond chicken
directions: Grill the tomato and blend it together with the onion and garlic. Set aside in the blender.

Add the clove, cinnamon, bread, and almonds to a skillet with the olive oil. When slightly browned, remove the mixture and blend it together with the tomato, adding the jalapeno if desired. Set aside.
Remove any excess oil from the skillet and brown the chicken until cooked thoroughly. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the puree to the chicken and lower the heat. Add water if the mixture seems very thick. Cook for 5 minutes, covered.
Serve along with tortillas or white rice.

title: tiramisu
directions: In a bowl, mix together the egg yolks with half the sugar.
Once mixed, add the mascarpone cheese and beat well until there are no lumps.
In another bowl, add the egg whites and whisk until stiff peaks, then add the rest of the sugar.
Fold the 1st mixture into the 2nd mixture slowly so as not to lose volume.
One by one, soak the ladyfingers for 3 seconds each in the coffee and make a layer of them in the bottom of a baking dish.
Cover the ladyfingers with a layer of cream, and smooth out with a spatula. Sift cocoa powder onto the cream.
Repeat all 3 layers one more time.

title: ricotta-filled squash scones
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Cook the squash in a steamer basket.
Let it cool and blend it, until it turns to a puree.
Pour flour, Parmesan, baking powder, and cumin seeds in a bow. Mix.
Make a well in the center of the bowl. Add 125 milliliters of buttermilk and the pureed squash. Feel free to add more buttermilk if the puree is too thick.
Mix to get a nice ball of dough. Place it on your floured surface.
Separate it into 2 equal portions and flatten slightly using the roll to form 2 identical circles.
Place the first of them in a pan.
Spread ricotta cheese with a knife, add the grated mozzarella, sprinkle with salt, and cover with the second disc of dough.
Put the egg yolk in a small bowl, add 1 teaspoon of buttermilk, mix, and then coat the scone with a brush.
Sprinkle with pumpkin seeds and sea salt.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spicy coconut chicken soup
directions: Place noodles in a heatproof bowl. Cover with boiling water. Soak for 5 minutes until tender. Drain well.
In a large saucepan, heat oil on medium. Add curry paste and cook, stirring, for 1 minute until fragrant. Add chicken, cook 4-5 minutes.
Blend in 1/2 cup water and coconut milk. Simmer 5 minutes. Add broccoli and simmer another 2-3 minutes.
Divide noodles among serving bowls. Ladle soup over noodles and top with bean sprouts, cilantro and chili. Serve with lime wedges.

title: sloppy joe with potato wedges
directions: Cook the potato wedges in a preheated oven according to package directions.

Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add the onion, pepper and celery and cook for 5 mins, stirring, until soft. Increase heat to high. Add the ground beef and cook for 10 mins, breaking up lumps with a spoon, until no longer pink.
Stir in tomato sauce, mustard and vinegar and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring occasionally, for another 5 mins, until slightly thickened.
Top potato wedges with sloppy joe mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and green onions to serve.

title: chicken meatballs
directions: Preheat the oven at 232C.
Heat the butter and the hot sauce in a deep skillet on medium until the butter melts, and let it cool off.
Grease a cooking tray with cooking spray.
Mix the butter sauce, chicken breasts, celery, egg, and breadcrumbs in a large bowl.
Form the meatballs using your hands and place them on the cooking tray.
Place the tray in the oven and let it cook for 15 minutes.
Remove the cooking tray from the oven and let the meatballs cool off for 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate and coconut pop cakes
directions: Once the cake is cooked and completely cooled, crumble finely in a bowl. Add the mascarpone and mix until the dough forms a ball. If necessary, add a little more mascarpone. Take small chunks of dough and shape them into balls the size of a large walnut. Place in the freezer for 15 minutes.

Melt 80 grams of chocolate in a double boiler. Chop the remaining 40 grams of chocolate and place in a bowl. Once the chocolate is melted, pour on top of the chopped chocolate in the bowl and mix until smooth.

Dip the end of a lollipop stick in the chocolate and then stick into a dough ball (a little less than half way, so that the ball doesn't break in two). Proceed in a similar way with all the cake balls. Then completely dip each ball into the melted chocolate and stick the pop cake in the styrofoam. Once all the pop cakes are covered with chocolate, sprinkle generously with grated coconut and let harden for at least one hour. Place in the refrigerator for a slightly crunchy chocolate shell.

title: white chocolate-raspberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Melt white chocolate in a double boiler.
Combine the melted chocolate, butter, sugar, then add the beaten eggs.
Add flour and yogurt.
Whisk gently.
Pour the mixture in a greased cake pan and arrange the raspberries on top.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes with the oven turned off.
Let cool for about 1/2 hour, then refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Remove from fridge 30 minutes before serving.

title: pan fried cabbage rolls with spiced lamb
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boil on medium heat. n a big bowl, toss in the Lamb, the spices and the all the other ingredients (including the egg) and mix really well for 2 minutes (with your hands preferably) to make sure you have a really smooth stuffing mix.

Let it rest for 15-20 minutes. In the mean time, chop off the stem of the cabbage and peel and discard the top 2 layers (if dirty). Then carefully extract as many large sheets of Cabbage as you can, making sure not to snap or break them.
Blanch each leaf for 2 to 3 minutes, making it pliable and easier to work with, and also half-cooked. Repeat for all sheets/leaves (gosh, what are they really called?!) and set them aside.

Slice off the tough spine that runs almost half way into the leaf, making a V-shaped cut and the base. Add a handful of stuffing, starting at the top of the leaf and rolling once. Then fold in the sides inwards and roll it out all the way. Tie with a piece of twine on both ends. Repeat till mix runs out for all other rolls.

Bring a medium pan up on low heat. Add 1 tbsp oil when the pan is hot. Place the rolls in carefully and let them caramelize for 3 minutes per side for a total of 12 minutes or so making sure the lamb gets cooked through all the way. Repeat the process.
Quick yogurt cilantro chutney: add all the chutney ingredients in a food processor, blender, Vitamix, Fruit Ninja or even a coffee grinder which I used and puree. Chutney is done!
Remove the rolls from the pan, and cut the twine. Dip them generously in the Chutney and you're done!

title: buffalo chicken bites
directions: Melt 1/2 tablespoon Promise(R) Buttery Spread in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat and cook chicken, turning once, until chicken is thoroughly cooked, about 8 minutes; cut into 3/4-inch pieces and keep warm.
Microwave remaining Spread with cayenne pepper sauce in medium microwave-safe bowl at HIGH 15 seconds or until melted; stir until blended. Add chicken; toss to coat.
Alternately thread celery, tomatoes and chicken on 36 wooden skewers. Arrange skewers on serving platter and serve with Dressing.

title: pan-fried lamb and potatoes with spiced carrots
directions: For the potatoes, heat 4 tbsp oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. Add the potatoes and fry for 15-20 mins, until tender. Reduce the heat if the potatoes begin to burn. Season with salt.

For the carrots, melt the butter in a saucepan. Add the carrots and onion and saute for 3-4 mins. Mix in the cumin, cloves and coriander then stir in the orange juice and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil then mix in the raisins. Cover and simmer for 10-12 mins, until the carrots are tender.
Heat the remaining oil in a frying pan, add the lamb and fry for 3-4 mins, turning, then season. Divide the potatoes, carrots and lamb between 4 plates, then serve.

title: roasted broccoli and olives
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Line a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with a silicone baking mat or parchment; set aside. In a small bowl combine garlic and 1/2 tsp. of the kosher salt. Using the back of a spoon, muddle garlic and salt until garlic begins to release its oil. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Stir in olive oil. Set aside.

Trim broccoli stems; cut stalks lengthwise into halves and/or quarters. Place in prepared baking pan. Pour garlic oil and olives over; toss well. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 tsp. kosher salt. Roast 20 to 25 minutes, tossing occasionally, until tender but al dente. Transfer to a serving dish.
To serve, sprinkle with flaked sea salt; drizzle with additional olive oil. Squeeze lemon juice over. Makes 8 servings.

Nutrition Facts (Roasted Broccoli and Olives)
Per serving: 134 kcal cal., 10 g fat (1 g sat. fat, 1 g polyunsaturated fat, 7 g monounsatured fat), 0 mg chol., 427 mg sodium, 10 g carb., 4 g fiber, 2 g sugar, 4 g pro.
Percent Daily Values are based on a 2,000 calorie diet

title: almond and lemon express pastry galette
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.

Mix flour, water, salt, and 375 butter in a bowl. Mix until dough forms a ball. On a lightly floured surface, roll out the dough to a thickness of 1.5 mm. Cut out 2 circles of dough, 1 a little larger than the other. It is important to cut them with a sharp knife so that the dough rises while baking.

In a bowl, mix 150 grams butter and sugar, add the ground almond, cornstarch, lemon zest, eggs, and rum. Mix with a spatula (do not use a whisk to avoid incorporating air, which would inflate the almond cream). Fill a pastry bag with the cream (1 centimeter round nozzle).
In a small bowl, mix egg, sugar and milk. mix the ingredients for the gilding, guild the cake with
the brush, store in the cool for 30 minutes then gild it a second time

Moisten the edges of the smaller dough circle using a brush. Squeeze the almond cream in a spiral on the larger dough circle, seal the two layers of dough. Press firmly so no air is caught between the layers. Brush the icing on top. Slit the top of the cake with a knife, being careful not to pierce the dough. Refrigerate the galette for 30 minutes. Brush with icing a second time.
Bake for 35 minutes until it is golden brown. Let cool before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180.
Combine the granulated sugar, brown sugar, and the butter in a bowl.
Once they have been combined well, add the egg, flour, vanilla extract, and baking soda.
Last, add the chocolate chips.
Shape the cookie dough into rounds the size of a golf ball and place them on a wax paper-lined cookie sheet, leaving some space between each cookie.
Bake for approximately 13 minutes.
Cool the cookies completely before removing them from the baking sheet. The cookies can be stored in a metal canister for up to a week.

title: roasted asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Mix nutmeg, garlic salt and red pepper in small bowl. Place asparagus in single layer on foil-lined 15x10x1-inch baking pan. Drizzle asparagus with oil; roll to coat. Sprinkle with spice mixture; roll to coat.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until asparagus are tender-crisp, turning once.

title: whole wheat vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 230 Celsius.
Mix the yeast with the sugar, water, and salt. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside in a warm place for 10 minutes.
Combine the whole wheat and white flours and add the yeast mixture. Add the olive oil and continue to mix until the dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in a lightly oiled bowl, cover with plastic wrap, and set in a warm place until it doubles in volume, approximately 30-60 minutes.
Tap the dough so that it deflates and divide into two sections. Form each into a circle approximately 20 centimeters in diameter and place onto a pizza pan or stone.
Bake for 5 minutes and remove from oven.
Saute the vegetables and garlic in the olive oil until tender.
Spread the sauce evenly over the pizza crust, sprinkle with olives, layer the vegetables, and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven and bake for 8 minutes at 220 C.

title: fish pie
directions: Make the mashed potatoes.
Meanwhile, boil the fish, broccoli, and eggs.
Once cooked, drain the fish and broccoli very well.
Cut the fish into small pieces, and slice the eggs in thin circles.
When the puree is ready, spread half in the baking pan.
On top, put the broccoli, then the fish, and finally the sliced boiled eggs.
Sprinkle generously with olive oil, preferably one flavored with garlic and herbs.
Cover the top with the remaining puree, and sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
Bake to a gratin.

title: encik kebin chicken
directions: Add dried red chile pepper, coriander, cumin, clove, cinnamon, black pepper, and turmeric to a food processor or spice grinder. Mix well.
Add the spices, ginger, salt, and coconut milk to a large bowl.
Cut the chicken breast into small, bite-sized pieces. Place them in the spice mixture and toss well.
Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and set it in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
Add a small amount of vegetable oil to a pan and heat on medium heat.
Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the chicken breast pieces and cook them until they become a golden brown color.
Serve on rice and slices of cucumber and tomato.

title: california wrap'n
directions: Spread It: Spread Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Real Mayonnaise on tortillas.
Stuff It: Layer chicken, avocado, red pepper, red onion and salad greens down center of each tortilla.
Wrap It: Roll and fold the filled tortilla.

title: chicken, corn and avocado tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Heat oil in a large frying pan on high. Saute pepper and onion for 3-4 mins, or until tender. Add chicken. Brown well for 4-5 mins, breaking up lumps with the back of a spoon.
Add taco seasoning, stirring well. Mix in sweet corn and 3/4 cup water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 2-3 mins, or until slightly thickened. Gently stir in avocado.
Meanwhile, place taco shells on a baking sheet and warm in the oven according to package instructions.
Fill tacos with chicken mixture. Top with lettuce, cheese, salsa and sour cream.

title: vanilla met chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350*F. Oil and flour dust an angel food cake form.

With an electric mixer, mix eggs and sugar until white and fluffy. Mix flour with baking powder and add the mix to the egg mixture. Add melted butter and fold. Divide the cake batter into two equal portions. Add vanilla instant pudding mix to one part and chocolate instant pudding mix and cocoa powder to other half. Pour chocolate batter into angel food cake form first, than carefully spread the vanilla batter over it.
Bake on the middle rack for 40 - 50 minutes. I always check my cake after 30 minutes, so I can cover it and prevent over browning.
After the cake is done, let it cool for10 minutes, take it out if the cake form, and let it cool completely on a cookie rack.
Serve in your preferred way and enjoy with a cup of coffee or tea.

title: wuffle truffle sundaes
directions: Blend chocolate hazelnut spread with cream in small bowl; set aside.
Toast waffles until golden brown. Chop 1 waffle into 1/4-inch croutons. Mix croutons with hazelnuts in small bowl; set aside.

Evenly spread hazelnut mixture onto warm waffles. Arrange waffles on dessert plates, then top with Breyers(R) BLASTS! Waffle Cone with Chocolatey Chips Frozen Dairy Dessert. Drizzle with chocolate syrup, sprinkle with croutons, then dollop with whipped cream.

title: chocolate spritz and hot chocolate spoons
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.
In a bowl, briskly whisk the powdered sugar with the vanilla extract and the softened butter.
Add the eggs and whisk again.
Stir in the flour and ground almonds in several increments.
Put the dough into a pastry bag fitted with a large star tip.
On a baking sheet covered with parchment paper, form the cookies by drawing closely spaced zigzags patterns (about 4). Space the cookies well as they tend to expand while baking.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. After baking, let cool on a rack.
Melt 120 grams of chocolate in a bain marie.
Once melted, add an additional 30 grams of chocolate and stir so that the whole mixture is homogeneous.
With a brush, cover half of each biscuit with chocolate. These biscuits will keep for a week without a problem in an airtight container.
To prepare the hot chocolate sppons, start by melting 150 grams of chocolate in a bain marie.

When melted, add the remaining 50 grams of chocolate and stir to make the mixture homogeneous. If you wish, you can add a pinch of cinnamon and cardamom at this time. Pour the melted chocolate into paper liners.
Stick in a small wooden spoon and "block" it straight, using the marshmallows. Once cold and hardened, unmold the tins and wrap them individually. Just dip the spoon in a cup of hot milk!

title: slow cooker vegetable beef soup
directions: 1. In slow cooker, combine all ingredients. Cook covered on LOW 8 to 10 hours or HIGH 4 to 6 hours or until beef is tender.

title: apple and cream cups
directions: Saute the apples in a skillet on low heat with the sugar, butter, and cinnamon. Stir carefully until softened and slightly golden. Remove from heat and set aside.
Whip the cream together with half the sugar until it thickens. Beat the other half of the sugar together with the mascarpone until smooth and homogenous.
Mix the cream and mascarpone mixtures together and refrigerate.
Divide the cream mixture between small serving dishes and top with apple. Sprinkle with brown sugar and caramelize with a kitchen torch.

title: layered cake with nougat topping
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Mix the eggs and the sugar, add the flour, spices, baking powder and the milk and at last, the melted butter.
Mix well and cook for approximately 40-45 minutes.
Let it cool.
In a saucepan heat the sugar over high heat just enough to get a light caramel, remove from heat and add dried fruit stirring well to let them get well coated.
Pour them quickly over a parchment paper, cover with a second layer of paper and then roll with a rolling pin to flatten down.
Allow to harden slightly and cut into the desired shape.
Reserve.
Remove vanilla ice cream from the freezer and work it with the spoon on top of the nougatine slices.
Put it back in the freezer until serving time.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Sift together the whole-grain flour, white flour, baking powder, a pinch of salt, the ground cinnamon, and the sugar.
Add the apple.
In another bowl, mix together the milk, egg, and butter.
Mix the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients until fully absorbed.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 of the way up and sprinkle ground cinnamon and brown sugar on top.
Bake for 20-22 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 355 degrees Fahrenheit.
In a large bowl, mix the flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Set aside.
In another bowl, mix the eggs, oil, milk, sugar and 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract.
Mix together the two preparations, then add the nuts, carrots and coconut.
Pour the preparation into a buttered mold and bake for 1 hour.
In the meantime, prepare the icing: mix the cream cheese with the icing sugar and the remaining teaspoon of vanilla extract. Whisk well so that hte frosting is smooth.
Once cooled, unmold the carrot cake on a pretty serving dish and spread the icing on top.

title: german americkaner cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 180 Celsius.
Cream the butter with the sugar, vanilla sugar, and vanilla extract. Add the eggs and mix well. Add the flour, baking powder, and milk, beating well.
Using a spoon, place small mounds of batter onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake for 20 minutes and remove from oven to cool.
Melt the chocolate and spread over the cookies, sprinkling with the coconut.

title: chili con carne
directions: Overnight let the red beans soak in cold water.

The next day, drain and gently rinse the beans. Cook the beans in a large volume of unsalted water. First bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and bring to simmer for 2 hours. Warning! Make sure there is enough water during cooking, and do not hesitate to add some as needed.
In a pan, fry the finely chopped onion in a little oil over medium heat.
When it begins to brown, add 2 cloves of chopped garlic and the meat.
Drain the tomatoes and keep their juice. Cut the tomatoes into pieces and add to the meat with the juice set aside.
Lower the heat to minimum and add the beans, spices, salt and pepper.
Cook it covered for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the red pepper last and add a little salt if needed.
Serve it with rice.

title: turkey and baby corn noodle soup
directions: 1) Marinade the turkey in the soy sauce and honey.
2) Fry the turkey in a saucepan to brown.
3) Pour in the stock and let it bubble for a few minutes.
4) Turn the heat right down. Add the noodles, baby corn and spring onion.
5) Let it simmer for 15-20 minutes until all is piping hot.
If you want the soup a bit thicker, just mix in some cornflour.

title: chocolate almond cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.
Using a food processor, crush the almonds with the sugar.
In the microwave, melt the chocolate with the butter.
In a bowl, beat the egg yolks. Add the almond and vanilla extracts, baking powder, and salt. Mix well.
Whisk the egg whites until stiff and add to the egg yolk mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes. Then, reduce heat to 170 C and bake for 40 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: guacamole
directions: Add the salt, green chili pepper, and garlic to the mortar and grind them up.
Once everything is ground up, add the avocado and mash all of the ingredients together.
Add the juice from the lemon into the avocado mixture and mix everything well.

title: autumn burger with sweet potato chips
directions: Mix ground beef, chopped onion, mustard, breadcrumbs and milk in a bowl. Season to taste then form into 4 burgers. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan, add burgers and sear for 8-10 mins, turning occasionally, until cooked through.
Meanwhile, heat remaining oil in a deep-fat fryer or pot to 350°F. Add potato slices, in batches. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. Season with salt and keep warm.

To finish, fry bacon for 4-5 mins until crispy then drain on paper towels. Spread applesauce over burger buns then add lettuce, burgers, sliced onion and bacon. Serve with sweet potato chips and mayonnaise (if using).

title: steak with mushroom sauce, french fries and roasted tomatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large frying pan and saute the tomatoes for 2 mins. Remove and set aside. Add the steaks and cook for 1 1/2 mins on each side. Season with salt and black pepper. Place the steaks and tomatoes on the baking sheet and roast for 8 mins. Remove from the oven, wrap the steaks in foil and allow to rest for 4 mins. Season the tomatoes with salt and black pepper and keep warm.

Meanwhile, for the sauce, add the mushrooms to the hot pan and saute for 2 mins. Add the onions and season with salt and black pepper. Pour in the stock and cream, bring to a boil and simmer for 5 mins.
For the french fries, heat the frying oil in a deep fat fryer or large saucepan and fry the potatoes in batches until golden. Drain on paper towels and keep warm.

For the breadcrumbs, melt the butter in a frying pan and fry the bread until golden. Arrange the steaks on serving plates, top with the mushroom sauce and sprinkle with the breadcrumbs. Garnish with basil and serve with the french fries, tomatoes and a green salad.

title: skewered stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. To assemble the skewers, place an olive in each pepper, then fill with sausage meat. Press down lightly and replace the pepper tops. Thread onto 8 wooden skewers, 2 per skewer, alternating with the onion wedges and bacon.
To cook, heat the oil in a large frying pan and brown the skewers in batches, turning. Transfer to a roasting pan and pour in the stock. Bake for 15-18 mins.
To finish, beat the sour cream until smooth and season with salt and black pepper. Arrange the skewers on plates, garnish with parsley and sprinkle with black pepper. Serve with the sour cream.

title: barbacoa-style chicken
directions: Place the ancho and Guajillo chilies in a saucepan with boiling water. Boil for 5 minutes. Turn the stove off and let them rest for 30 minutes.
Remove the chilies from the saucepan, then devein and seed.
Place in the blender and add the clove, pinch of cumin, pepper, cinnamon, oregano, garlic, and salt to taste. Puree to obtain a thick sauce.
Cover the chicken with this sauce. Cover with plastic wrap and let it rest overnight in the refrigerator.
The next day, preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Heat the banana leaves to soften. Place on a baking tray lined with aluminum foil, then add a layer of avocado leaves and the chicken on top.
Wrap with the same banana leaf.
Bake at 180 C for 20 minutes. Then, open the banana leaf and bake uncovered for another 10 minutes. The chicken must be done on the inside.
Let the chicken cool for 10 minutes before serving.
Serving suggestion: refried beans, avocado, lime, and tortillas.

title: buttermilk and chocolate pops
directions: Melt the chocolate in a bain marie. Soak the gelatin in warm water for 5 minutes.
Warm the buttermilk and sugar in a small saucepan.
Add the chocolate and liqueur.
Strain the gelatine and add to the pan, stir until dissolved.
Whip the cream and add to the mixture.
Fill Popsicle moulds with the creamy mix and the sticks. Place in refrigerator for at least 5 hours.
Before serving, remove popsicles from the molds and dust with crushed toasted hazelnuts and chocolate or colored sprinkles.

title: no-bake lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix together crumbs, sugar, and cinnamon. Add melted butter and blend. Set aside 2 tablespoons of mixture. Line bottom of 9-inch pan with crumbs.
Refrigerate. Beat cheese until fluffy, blend in milk then add lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into chilled crust. Sprinkle with set aside crumbs.
Regrigerate at least 3 hours before serving. May be doubled and put into a 9x13-inch pan.

title: christmas cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 180C.
Put the ricotta cheese through a sieve and mix it with the raw sugar. It is possible to use an immersion blender, blending until the mixture is smooth and creamy.
Add the softened butter and the eggs, one at a time.
Add the rum and the soy milk.
Combine the two types of flour with the baking powder and add them to the batter, next add the walnuts.
Stir just enough to combine.
Butter and flour a bundt pan and pour the batter inside.
Bake the cake for approximately 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove the cake from the oven and allow it to cool completely.
In the meantime, melt the chocolate with some milk and a drop of rum (optional), it should not be too liquid.
Pour it directly over the cooled cake.
Let the icing cool and serve.

title: ricotta cheese and chocolate swirl squares
directions: Preheat the oven to 170C.
Beat the eggs with the sugar for 3 minutes with an electric mixer.
Incorporate the ricotta cheese completely, add the vanilla seeds and the flour and continue mixing.
Butter a square cake pan measuring approximately 20 x 20 centimeters and then coat it with the breadcrumbs, eliminate any excess.
Pour 2/3 of the mixture into the cake pan and add the cocoa to the remaining mixture, stirring well.
Pour the chocolate mixture on top of the plain mixture and use a fork to make the swirls in the two mixtures.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes.
Remove the pan from the oven, let cool completely, cut into squares and serve sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: mascarpone treats
directions: Prepare a creme anglaise with the sugar, egg, cornstarch and the milk. Cook the cream in a medium saucepan until it thickens, add the white chocolate while the cream is still hot.
Let the cream cool, then add the mascarpone cheese and incorporate it well.
Place the ingredients in the bread machine bowl as they are listed.
Set the bread machine.
At the end, add the add the chocolate chips.
Bake the bread at 180C until done.
Remove the bread from the oven and let it cool.
Place a disk of cake or bread on a plate, add a generous layer of cream to the cake with some dark chocolate shavings, top with a second disk of cake, and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peach melba parfait
directions: Combine peaches and yogurt in freezer safe container. Freeze until frozen.
Place thawed raspberries, sugar, and orange juice in blender. Mix until smooth.
Place raspberry mixture into sieve, reserving puree.Discard seeds and chill.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of puree into parfait glass. Top with fresh raspberries and yogurt.

title: simple sweet bread
directions: Make the buttermilk by mixing warm milk and lemon juice. Let stand for 10 minutes,

Using an electric mixer, or bread making machine, add the ingredients in this order: eggs, warm buttermilk, oil, sugar, salt, flour, and yeast. Mix for 10 minutes to get a smooth but sticky dough. If necessary, add a little more flour or warm buttermilk. Place the dough in a plastic bag, close tightly, and let rise for 2 hours.

Place the dough on a floured surface, and knead lightly to expel air. If the dough is too soft and sticks to your hands, add a little more flour, but not too much otherwise the bread will be tough. Shape the bread loaf or loaves, and place on a large, greased baking tray. Use a sharp knife to make a few diagonal cuts on the top of the dough. Let dough rise for 40 minutes more.
Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Bake the bread for about 1 hour, or until golden.
Cool on a wire rack, and store in an airtight container.

title: carne asada
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl. Pour mixture over steak in a large shallow nonaluminum baking dish or plastic bag and turn to coat. Cover, or close bag and marinate in refrigerator about 30 minutes. Remove steak from marinade, discarding marinade.
Grill or broil steak to desired doneness, turning once. Let stand loosely covered about 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve sliced steak in tortillas. Garnish with your favorite taco toppings, such as shredded cheddar cheese, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and sour cream.

title: savory beet salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl. Chill until ready to serve. Season, if desired, with salt and black pepper.

title: gluten free pancakes
directions: Pour the milk, oil, maple syrup, vanilla extract, and eggs into your KitchenAid(R) Power Plus(R) blender container, secure the lid, and process on variable speed 3 for 3 to 5 seconds just until combined. Add the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt, and process on variable speed 3 for about 5 seconds until well combined. Remove the center lid cap, insert the tamper, and scrape down the sides of the container to incorporate any flour residue, and process for 3 to 5 seconds more until any lumps are fully blended. (You don't want to over process.)
Allow the mixture to sit for 5 minutes before cooking.

In a small skillet over medium-low heat, warm 1/2 teaspoon of grape seed oil, and then ladle 1/3 cup (80ml) of the pancake batter in, and distribute into the pan evenly. Cook for about 3 minutes until the top of the pancake is bubbling and the edges are beginning to dry. Using a spatula, flip the pancake, and cook for another 2 minutes, or more, until cooked through.
Repeat this process with the remaining batter.
Serve the pancakes with maple syrup, and topped with fresh fruit, shredded coconut, crushed nuts etc.

title: raspberry crunchy granola tartletts
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the syrup, butter, and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat, add oats and stir to coat with the syrup.
In a cupcake tin, pour a teaspoon of the batter to cover the bottom.
Refrigerate until set.
With an electric mixture, beat whipping cream cream with sugar until stiff.
To serve, unmold the shells, fill with whipped cream and decorate with raspberries and chopped pistachios.

title: vegan vanilla cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line muffin pan with cupcake liners.
Whisk the soy milk and vinegar in a measuring cup and set aside a few minutes to get good and curdled*

If using margarine, sift the flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a large bowl and mix. In a separate large bowl, use a handheld mixer a medium speed to cream the margarine and sugar for about 2 minutes until light and fluffy, but don't beat past two minutes. Beat in the vanilla, then alternate beating in the soy milk mixture and the dry ingredients, stopping to scrape the side of the bowl a few times.
If using oil: beat together the soy milk mixture, oil, sugar, and vanilla in a large bowl. Sift in the flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and salt and mix until no large lumps remain.

Fill cupcake liners two-thirds of the way full and bake for 20-22 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Transfer to a cooling rack and let cool completely before frosting.

title: red white & bacon vanilla cupcakes
directions: Line 12-cup muffin pan with 8 paper cupcake liners. Combine pretzels, Spread and sugar in medium bowl. Evenly spoon pretzel mixture into cups and press into even layer with bottom of small glass. Freeze 10 minutes.

Crumble 2 strips bacon; cut remaining 2 strips into 8 pieces. Evenly scoop Breyers(R) Natural Vanilla Ice Cream into each cup. Press a piece of bacon into each cup like a "flag", then sprinkle with crumbled bacon and sprinkles.
Freeze 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: coconut shrimp
directions: Preheat oil in skillet or wok on medium heat to 350 degrees.
Mix flour, curry, coconut, salt and pepper.
Dip shrimp in egg mixture then roll in flour mixture. Repeat.
Cook about 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: tuna and ham sandwiches
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar. Season then whisk in oil. Add diced onion. Set aside.

Fill both loaves of bread with lettuce. Fill wholewheat baguette with tuna, pickles, tomato, onions and mayonnaise. Garnish with dill. Fill rye baguette with ham, cheese and mustard. Drizzle dressing over both sandwiches.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate shots and ice cream sandwiches
directions: Combine chocolate and cream in a small saucepan. Stir on low heat for 2-3 mins, until smooth. Remove from heat and stir in hazelnut spread and liqueur.
Allow to cool slightly, then stir in three-quarters of the candy bar.
Spoon mixture into shot glasses. Sprinkle each with remaining candy bar. Chill for an hour or until ready to serve.
For the ice cream sandwiches: Scoop ice cream onto 6 cookies. Spread thickly.
Top with remaining cookies to form a sandwich, molding and scraping ice cream to finish.
Arrange on a metal tray. Freeze until firm.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat the oven to 150C.
Melt the butter and the chocolate in a small saucepan over low heat.

Place the sugar, eggs, and salt in the mixer bowl and combine until well incorporated. Add the melted butter, chocolate mixture, flour, and vanilla extract and combine on low speed. Last, add the nuts, setting some aside for the garnish, and combine.
Pour the batter in a buttered and floured rectangular baking pan and bake in a preheated oven for 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove the brownies from the oven, let cool and cut them into squares.
Melt the chocolate with the hot water over a double boiler, add the butter and let the mixture cool.
Add the egg, sugar, and vanilla extract. Stir well to incorporate.
Spread the icing over the brownies and sprinkle with the nuts set aside earlier.

title: zucchini stuffed with quail egg. poaching eggs the easy way
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Add half of the oil to a skillet on medium heat. Cut the zucchini into 7- to 10-centimeter thick slices and cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
In another skillet, add the remaining oil and saute the onion and bell pepper for 5 minutes. Add the minced meat. Cook for another 5 minutes and set aside.
Once the zucchini are cooked, partially remove the insides using a melon baller, leaving a solid bottom in each.
Use a knife to open the quail eggs, being careful not to break the yolk.
Place 1 quail egg in each zucchini round, 6 in total.
Continue to fill with the minced meat.
Cover with grated Parmesan cheese and bake for 5 to 7 minutes until the cheese melts.
Loosely cut pieces of plastic wrap and place each over a glass. Open the rest of the eggs and put each on top of a piece of plastic wrap, add some oregano and salt.
Close the plastic wrap with some wire, creating a small bag.
Cook for 2 minutes. Let them cool before removing the plastic wrap.
Place the poached eggs on top of the zucchini for garnish.

title: coconut chicken curry
directions: Heat a deep, nonstick frying pan over high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring, 2 mins, or until starting to brown. Reduce heat to medium. Add onion and curry powder and cook, stirring, 2 mins, or until onion is soft and curry powder is fragrant. Stir in coconut milk and tomatoes. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 mins. Add broccoli, peppers and green beans. Simmer, partially covered, 5 mins, or until vegetables are just tender. Spoon into shallow serving bowls, sprinkle with cashews and serve with rice.

title: chicken and broccoli tagliatelle
directions: Cut the chicken breasts into thick strips and season them with lemon juice and salt. Let them marinate for at least 15 minutes.
Boil water and a pinch of salt in a saucepan. Once the water begins to boil, add the tagliatelle.
Cook the tagliatelle for 5 minutes, then add the broccoli.
Once the pasta is cooked, the broccoli will also be finished.
While the pasta is cooking, heat 5 or 6 tablespoons of olive oil in a frying pan.
Put a saucepan with water and salt to boil. When it starts boiling, add the tagliatelle. After 5 minutes, add the broccoli. When the pasta is cooked, the broccoli will be too.
While the pasta is cooking, heat 5 or 6 tablespoons of olive oil in a frying pan. Once hot, add the chicken breasts and stir in the garlic with a wooden spoon.
Let the chicken brown well on one side and then turn it to brown again.
Drain the pasta and the broccoli very well. Place it in a large bowl and add the cooked chicken, removing the garlic.
Add the olives and stir gently.

title: west indian pork
directions: Slice tenderloin crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Flatten slightly with heel of hand. Melt one teaspoon butter in large skillet over medium heat, brown pork quickly on both sides, about 4-5 minutes. Remove pork from skillet, keep warm. Melt remaining butter in pan, add bananas and saute 2-3 minutes. Add brown sugar and brandy, cook and stir until sauce is thick and bubbly. Return pork to pan, heat through.

title: green banana curry
directions: First heat the oil in a large saucepan and fry the onion with the ginger for about 8 minutes until it is softened and golden.
Then add the tumeric and chilli powder cardamoms and fresh chillies and cook everything for about 1 minute.
Next peel the bananas you need to do this with a small sharp knife as they do not peel like ripe bananas at all; the skin needs to be removed rather like peeling a cucumber.
Cut the bananas across into slices about 8mm thick.
Then stir them into the onion and spice mixture and allow them to brown slightly.
Now add 225ml water stir everything and then cover and cook gently until soft about 10 15 minutes.
Finally stir in the yoghurt and garam masala and continue to cook gently for a further 2 minutes. (Add a little additional water if you think that it needs it.)
Lastly taste season and serve hot.
Serve with spiced pilau rice and a tomato and onion salad dressed in lemon juice.

title: curried zucchini and onion burgers
directions: Grate and salt the zucchini. Place in a colander. Set aside.
Cut the onion in very small cubes and fry in a pan with a little oil.
Beat the egg.
Press the zucchini in the colander with your hands to release the water that will be drawn-out by the salt.
In a bowl, mix zucchini, egg, and the cooked onion. Add two tablespoons of cornstarch and curry to taste. Mix well. Check the salt and pepper.
In a pan with very little oil, spoon out round portions of dough. Cook for two minutes on each side.

title: milk and almond cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Heat the milk with the butter, and lemon peel, set aside.
Beat the eggs, egg yolk, and sugar together. Add the Chinese pudding powder, and mix.
Gradually, add the flour, almond powder, and warm milk mixture.
Stir well to obtain a homogeneous mixture, with no lumps.
Pour in pie pan, but do not fill completely.
Bake for about 25 minutes.

title: coconut ice
directions: Place the sugar and 1 cup water in a saucepan and simmer for 5-10 mins, until thickened. Allow to cool. Stir in the coconut milk and lemon juice. Fold in the cream. Freeze overnight.
Scoop into balls and sprinkle with the coconut and powdered sugar. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: green tea & blackberry mango lassi
directions: Process all ingredients in blender until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: mango smoothie
directions: Place the mango, yogurt, lime juice and sugar (if using) in a blender and puree. Pour the smoothie into an ice-filled glass. Sprinkle with the lime peel.

title: ranch potato salad primavera
directions: Toss all ingredients in large bowl. Season, if desired, with salt and ground black pepper. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Thaw frozen blueberries in a colander. Collect the thawed juice.
Preheat oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit.

Let the dough rest for an hour, then roll out on a floured surface, and spread in a scalloped pie pan. Sprinkle the bottom of the pan with the ground almonds to absorb the excess fruit juice while cooking. Spread the blueberries on the dough, and sprinkle with sugar. Bake for 20 minutes.

If desired, make homemade blueberry syrup with thawed juice. Weigh the fruit juice. Measure out half the weight of the fruit juice in sugar. Mix the juice and sugar in a saucepan and boil for about 10 minutes, skimming from time to time.

title: chocolate dipped oranges
directions: Wash and thinly slice the oranges into circles.

Place the oranges along with the water, sugar, and cinnamon into a saucepan and cook on low heat for 75 minutes. Remove the oranges from the pan, place onto a baking rack, and let cool for a few hours.
Melt the chocolate and butter together in a double boiler. Dip the orange slices halfway into the chocolate to coat.
Store in freezer.

title: glazed chicken with coriander
directions: In a bowl, mix the cumin, garlic, ginger, soy sauce, sherry, egg yolks, salt, and black pepper.
Stir, then cover with plastic film and leave to marinate in the refrigerator overnight.
Strain the liquid from the marinade. Place the chicken in a dish with flour and coat them well.
Heat a drizzle of oil in a deep frying pan. Fry the chicken in batches until golden. Set aside.
In a wok, heat on low the sugar and stock.
When the sugar is dissolved, add the chicken, coriander and vinegar.
Cook on low until the sauce thickens and the chicken is tender.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: pumpkin spice muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Line a muffin tin with muffin papers.
In a large bowl, add the flour, baking soda, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, and five-spice powder.
Make a well in the middle, and add the oil, pumpkin, and eggs. Carefully mix everything together being careful not to overmix.
Fill the muffin molds 3/4 of the way full and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the middle of the muffin comes out dry.
While the muffins are baking, prepare the glaze. Whisk together the powdered sugar and maple syrup.
When the muffins have cooled slightly, pour the glaze over them and top with crushed hazelnuts.

title: cookie cake with lemon cream
directions: Cut the butter into cubes, and add the sifted sugar.
Whisk until getting a grainy batter.
Add the egg yolks, and continue whisking until getting a smooth cream.
Add the lemon zest, and 2 tablespoons of coffee.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add the egg whites to the cream without stirring.
Wet the cookies in the coffee, and spread them on the bottom of the tray, or plate.
Cover the wafers with a layer of cream, and repeat until all the cookies have been used.
Finally, cover the whole cake with cream, sprinkle with a grated cookie, and garnish with strawberries.
Refrigerate.
Serve well chilled.

title: sweet berry cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 Celsius degrees.
Grease a bundt cake pan with butter, and sprinkle with flour. Set aside.
In a bowl, whisk eggs and sugar until whitish.
Add the yogurt, margarine, and jam. Whisk well.
Finally, add the flour and baking powder, stirring, without whisking.
Place the dough in pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini cake snax
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line bottom of 9-inch square cake pan* with parchment or wax paper, then spray with nonstick cooking spray with flour; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine flours, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; set aside.

In large bowl, with electric mixer, beat Promise(R) Buttery Spread with sugars until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each addition. Beat in yogurt. Gradually beat in flour mixture, then zucchini, just until blended. Evenly pour into prepared pan.

Bake 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. On wire rack, cool 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely. Slice into 16 squares and sprinkle, if desired, with confectioners sugar.


*To make MINI ZUCCHINI SNAX MUFFINS, spray mini muffin pans with nonstick cooking spray with flour, then fill 2/3-full with batter. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in centers comes out clean. On wire rack, cook 5 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely. Sprinkle, if desired, with confectioners sugar. Makes 3-1/2 dozen.

title: banh mi
directions: For the Vietnamese Sausage Patties: Combine all patty ingredients, form patties and cook through on a griddle or grill
For the Pickled Vegetables: Combine water, vinegar, salt, and sugar in a small saucepan and bring to a simmer over low heat, letting salt and sugar dissolve. Pour over vegetables and reserve

title: lebanese garlic sauce
directions: Put in blender (NOT a food processor) and blend until smooth on medium.
Add in an extremely slow stream, 3 to 4 cups of Puritan oil.
Blend constantly on about medium.
It should become like a thick white mayonnaise consistency.
Store in refrigerator in a glass container.
Serve with meats, as a seasoning in salad dressings or on pocket bread sandwiches.
This is a tricky recipe.
Sometimes it "breaks".
That is, it stays thin instead of the mayonnaise consistency.
The flavors remain the same.
If it separates in storage, just stir or

title: peach galette
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

In a food processor, process ground almonds, sugar, egg, butter and vanilla to a smooth paste. Place sheet of puff pastry on prepared tray. Score 1/2 inch from the edge with a sharp knife. Spread inside the border with paste. Brush border with extra egg.
Spread peaches over almond paste. Sprinkle with sliced almonds. Bake 15-20 minutes, until golden. Serve with cream or ice-cream.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Line two trays with parchment paper and set aside. Preheat oven to 360°F.
In a bowl, place the sugar, butter and peanut butter and beat until creamy.
Add the egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add the flour and baking powder and mix until combined.
Incorporate the chocolate chips.
Form walnut-sized balls and flatten with hands.
Place on the baking sheets, leaving space between.
Bake for about 12-15 minutes. Remove while still soft but golden. Cookies will get harder after cooling. Once cool, store in an airtight container.

title: mazola heritage sweet salad dressing circa 1950's
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed, paprika, salt and tomato sauce in a 1-quart jar and cover with lid. Shake to combine; add onion and oil. Continue to shake until mixed well. Let sit 30 minutes for sugar to dissolve and flavors to develop.
Store in tightly sealed jar in refrigerator for up to 1 month.

title: lentil citrus salad with goat cheese
directions: Combine Hellmann's(R) Organic Original, vinegar, salt, ginger and pepper in medium bowl.
Add lentils to bowl and toss to coat. Arrange on serving platter, then top with beets, oranges, goat cheese and cilantro; toss.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini JUST UNTIL TENDER. Drain. Cook carrots and onions in a LITTLE water for about 5 minutes. Drain. Melt butter in saucepan and add carrots and onions.
Stir in chicken soup and sour cream and mix in zucchini carefully.
Mix in 1 cup stuffing mix. Pour into 7x10 inch casserole.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup stuffing mix over top and bake at 350 degrees. Bake 30 to 35 minutes uncovered. Use stuffing mix dry as is.

title: sweet almond pasta
directions: Bring a pot with water and some rock salt to a boil.
Break the pasta in half, and add to the boiling water.
Boil for 3 to 4 minutes, then drain well. Rinse in cold water, and set aside.
In a saucepan, mix the milk, cream, cornstarch, egg yolks, lemon peel, cinnamon stick, orange flowers, sugar, honey, and crushed almonds.
Mix well, and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When hot, add the vermicelli, and continue cooking, stirring until sauce thickens slightly.

title: spice roasted pork chops with coconut corn sauce
directions: For the corn sauce, preheat a sauce pan or nonstick pan over medium heat with the oil. Add the red onion, garlic, ginger, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper to the pan. Cook for 5-7 minutes until the onions are soft and translucent, then add the corn and cook another five minutes. Add the stock and cook until only a few tablespoons are left in the pan. Carefully transfer the corn mixture to the KitchenAid(R) TorrentTM Magnetic Drive Blender, add the coconut milk and blend until consistency is smooth. Put the sauce back into the pan, add the lime juice and check for seasoning, you will probably need more salt. Cook sauce over medium-low heat until the consistency is that of slightly loose gravy, about 3-5 minutes. If sauce is too thick add a little more stock.

For the pork chops, preheat the oven to 450 degrees and mix the cumin, paprika, coriander and cinnamon together in a small bowl. Season both sides of the pork chops with 1/4 teaspoon of kosher salt, a couple cracks of pepper, and a generous amount of the spice rub. Let chops sit at room temperature for 20 minutes. Pre-heat a cast iron pan over medium-high heat with 1-2 tablespoons of vegetable oil. Sear the chops for two minutes on the first side, flip and transfer pan in the oven for 8 minutes or until the internal temperature of the chops is 145 degrees. Take chops out of the oven and transfer to a plate, cover with foil and let rest for 5 minutes so the juices can redistribute.
